The menu selections are bright and robust, loaded with flavour, prepared nightly by Mama Rosa from guarded family recipes many generations old. With an open kitchen, the food and chefs are the stars of the show.

reviews.text: We got a family style meal that started off splendid. The three salads with calamari was the best part of the meal. The three pastas were good but they all tasted the same. Portion of each pasta was small. The main course was the worst we ever had. The lamb chops were no bigger than a bottle cap each. The veggies that came with the main is 5 strands of asparagus with half a plate of more salad... Except this time the salad was without any dressing or toppings. Lastly, the service was definitely slow. No one checked on whether we wanted another drink or water throughout the entire meal. Definitely not impressed. We came here because it was noted to be the "most authentic Italian in the city". The taste might be authentic but the experience was far from a good European time.
This place is delicious! Recommend for sure..... Usually a wait if after 7..... Authentic home made Italian food..... Talk to Rosa cooking in the front as you walk in!

Awesome experience. Our server was excellent, very welcoming and funny. We went with his wine suggestion and it paired great with our meal. Atmosphere is very cozy, you really feel at home here.

And the food.. Amazing. I left stuffed and beyond satisfied.

reviews.text: Attended a work function here for dinner in the downstairs wine cellar. Excellent service, and great food paired with very good Portuguese wines. Would recommend both for group events as well as intimate meals.

Probably the best dining experience I had in Toronto. The quality and the freshness of the ingredients make for a dish full of flavors. The service is impeccable, the wine selection is interesting. A delight from the appetizer to the dessert.

We went here for a family wedding anniversary. Atmosphere is very inviting and the stuff are excellent! I had the mushroom risotto and it was to die for, absolutely delicious. Everyone was satisfied with their meals and a bonus was that our waiter spoke Portuguese, great for my in-laws who's English is limited!

Two of us had dinner here tonight, and enjoyed the meal. Some real positives - attractive interior, comfortable table, friendly service, and quite reasonable prices (three-course plus coffee prix fixe for $45 pp, a wine list that had a lot of choices in the $36-42 range). The meal started with a complementary amuse-bouche. A basket of various breads with olive oil and olives were provided. Our romaine salads were excellent, a cut above the usual. Our mains (salmon and chicken breast) were both excellent, with great vegetable accompaniments. We both had gelato for dessert - tasty and presented with fresh fruit garnish. The only disappointment in the meal was the coffee - really weirdly weak, almost transparent, lacking in flavour (like what you get in the Midwest U.S.). One of us ordered decaf, the other regular - both coffees were the same in appearance and taste. Too bad - a weak ending to an otherwise perfect meal.
I had the Fettuccine with tiger shrimp.. enjoyed it ...and service was prompt yet not overbearing. Overall good experience for business lunch.

lic_profile: A quaint, neighbourhood restaurant, Aiolio is located in the heart of Cliffside Village not far from the Scarborough Bluffs. The menu features dishes from the South of France, such as confit de canard, and classics from Italy with a touch of Mediterranean flavour, all using local and regional ingredients. Friendly service and personal attention by the chef and staff set the stage for a wonderful meal in this charming bistro.

reviews.text: Always beyond impressive. My husband and I moved to Scarborough from downtown Toronto and we are used to the top fine dining restaurants in the city. This restaurant absolutely without a doubt takes the cake both literally and metaphorically speaking. I put this restaurant on par with five star restaurants in Toronto, at a third of the price.

Obsessed with this place. Amazing food and atmosphere. Chef Henri is so personable, they really know how to make you feel comfortable and at home here. Staff are extremely attentive! Will definitely be going back. :)

As far as "good food" goes, coupled with an eclectic atmosphere, you cannot go wrong with Aioli Bistro. While not quite a Scarborough gem and I can envision parking being problematic, Aiolio's prices are reasonable, and their wine list is sufficient. The service tipped towards being slightly over attentive. My wife and I enjoyed the braised lamb shank, along with a bottle of Italian red wine. We were satisfied and definitely will be dropping in again in the not too distant future.

lic_profile: Most appropriately named, music lovers and food enthusiasts have made Alleycatz a popular dining and party destination. A menu with Mediterranean flair, a varied martini line-up and after dinner entertainment in the form of salsa, bachata, and live bands playing blues & top 40's dance music. Warm and convivial in red oak and exposed brick, Alleycatz sets a comfortable and fun environment for their guests.

reviews.text:
Ordered a appetizer and entree both arrived at the same time.  The bartender who delivered the food offered to have a new burger made.  Had to ask about the burger, the server ask what the problem was & when it finally arrived it was clear that it was the original burger that had been left under the heat lamp too long.  The lettuce and tomato were both cooked.  When questioned about that he said that the meat patty always cooks the lettuce and tomato like that and that it is normal.  He finally took the burger off the bill.  There were 5 of us and we had asked for separate bills except for 1 couple who wanted theirs together.  When he brought the bills out the wrong two people were together.  When we all took out cash he did not take the cash and left to take care of other customers.  He did not return for about 10 minutes and then took about 15 minutes to return with our change.  We were here to celebrate a birthday but decided to go elsewhere to complete the evening due to our servers bad attitude and service.  We were told that Gerrado was new by the bartender.
On a positive note we did love the band and the rest of the food was excellent.

Great food, good music the night I was there and good service. Prices for drinks and food was very reasonable. Good mature crowd, and comfortable seating for lounging and having a good time time with friends.
Great food and atmosphere! My boyfriend and I got a groupon for their dinner and it was tasty and filling. I would definitely recommend üòä

I've been going there for several years and it's a great place to go to enjoy the live bands, the dancing (although the floor quickly becomes packed), and food. We've usually ordered appetizers like mussels and some other items...they tasted great. Bar staff is very friendly, but they do get incredibly busy, so it's your typical bar...you may have to wait and it's difficult to talk since it get's noisy. I think if you get there after 9 pm, there is a cover...sometimes a bit inconsistent on the cover charge. I'm always amazed by the stupid men and women who either stand on the dance floor, but do NOT dance, or have their drinks or large purses with them. If you want to "stand", then move to off the dance floor so others can dance. If you're worried about your drinks, then finish them, before dancing and buy another one later...don't be cheap.

The food was very good. The space was way too small for the amount of people that came for the entertainment. The band was amazing. My only complaint is that my husband witnessed a waitress handing used drinking glasses to the bar tender that used a towel to wipe them and used them again. In my opinion, that is not sanitary. Other than that, I enjoyed spending time with my family.

lic_profile: Amano Pasta, a new underground restaurant at Toronto‚Äôs Union Station is an open concept, handmade pasta bar inspired by Italian heritage, but not defined by it. Chef Michael Angeloni combines classic Italian cooking techniques taught to him by his nonna, with locally sourced, often unexpected ingredients. While the dishes are Italian, many of the ingredients (like black sesame, jalape√±o, and tahini) are not. Amano offers classic Italian eats like Fat Tubes Rigatoni Bolognese with local Ontario beef and pork, with the focal point of the menu being a section Chef Angeloni has dubbed ‚ÄòNot Your Nonna‚Äôs Pasta‚Äô. Amano‚Äôs wine list includes Italian classics but is rounded off with Canadian offerings, which either focus on Italian wine making techniques or grapes themselves.

reviews.text: I can‚Äôt say enough about Amano Pasta in Union Station's lower promenade. We've been approx. once a month since they opened December 2017. Safe to say, it‚Äôs our spot. I honestly can‚Äôt say which is better, the fresh pasta, made in-house, or the warm and inviting atmosphere and staff. Sometimes it can be hard to find delicious vegetarian-friendly restaurants in the city, but Amano is not lacking in meat-free dishes. Although the appetizers are unbelievably simple and delicious, the stars here are the fresh pasta dishes, made in-house. To be honest, I don‚Äôt think I have had more delicious pasta ever. The restaurant‚Äôs philosophy is to make Italian food approachable, so the dishes are named after the shapes of the pasta, and not the official pasta names. The portions are big enough to feel satisfied, but not too heavy that you have to roll yourself out of the restaurant. The ingredients are fresh and local, which is what makes the meal so enjoyable. I have to say, I think Amano may be the best restaurant we‚Äôve ever been to in Toronto. I can't say enough about the restaurant, the food and the staff. To Chef Mike, Kristina and the entire team, keep up the amazing work that you all do!

So much more than just dinner: Amano is an experience. Unexpected authentic Italian comfort inside Union Station, with incredible fresh handmade pasta & a mouth-watering menu full of traditional fare with a twist. Fabulous higher-end wine selection & wonderful, welcoming service. A special thanks to the manager for seating us at the pasta bar: watching the chefs cook live was mesmerizing & truly transformed this amazing dinner into an unforgettable experience. We WILL be back!

I really enjoy coming here. Location is super convenient inside of union station and the few times I came the service was great. All their pastas are made well and all their dishes are super tasty! It never disappoints. 

If you are looking for happy hour, this is your spot!
$1/oz wine and $6 cocktail specials.

Definitely recommend Amano if you're in the area!

Good pasta, bad service ! 
This restaurant definitely serves good quality Italian food. The pastas are absolutely amazing and their menu is extensive! The prices are a bit high but is it expected given the location. They are located inside the union station, which is extremely convenient if you want a quick eat before the train or before grabbing the UP. However, they are positioned more like a fancy sit down restaurant and it‚Äôs Hard to get this nice night out feel when you eat inside a train station... I have been to the restaurant a few times and the service is a hit or miss. Some waiters are extremely nice and make sure you get the level of service you have in a restaurant in that price range. However, some other servers forgot to bring our drinks, bread, never apologized for their lousy service and are simply rude... Nevertheless, I believe this place deserve 4 stars for their great pastas!!

One of my favourite new additions to the Union concourse. Their food is made fresh in house and the prices are very fair, especially for the portions, though what truly takes this place a step higher is the excellent service with a personal touch. The staff are all friendly, welcoming, and efficient, and I definitely appreciate the latte art in my morning cappuccino. Would definitely recommend!

Aria is owned by Guido Saldini and Elena Morelli the proprietors of Noce Restaurant which has helped set the standard for Italian cuisine in Toronto for almost 20 years.  "Aria" means "air" in Italian but also references the most Italian of art forms - opera.  Both themes are evident inside Aria which boasts a dramatic 35 foot ceiling and is situated adjacent to the Air Canada Centre and Maple Leaf Square. Aria has dining capacity for 130 people and can accommodate private parties in a variety of formats.

And the atmosphere was contemporary are neat. Tall two storey wine cellar on display also.

You can see the white part inside the uncooked pasta. And to boot, it wasn't very tasty or worthy of the price.

We went for New Year's Eve. The restaurant is designed very nicely. The staff is very nice. The restaurant website failed to advertise that the menu would be limited tonight and that everything would be extra highly priced. This, however, is a minor gripe because the food was the biggest disappointment.

My wife could barely swallow her entree (octopus) and my meal left me feeling nauseous. Very disappointing.

reviews.text: Had dinner here with my family.  Authentic Greek cuisine.  The ambience was good though you may not want to bring children here if yours are a bit noisy as this is a more upscale restaurant.   Staff are professional and prices are moderate.  I will return and try the other entrees....they all look so yummy :)

Absolute worse experience of our lives. Reservation was made and we arrived on time and the restaurant was busier than normal as it was Mothers day but still quite a few tables that were empty. The service started out slow as the waiter did not take our order until about half an hour of us sitting there. Finally when he took our orders as he wrote them down we thought maybe things would change. However an hour into waiting we still had not yet received our appetizer and so we decided to ask. A lady came to our table and said the kitchen had been backed up and our food would come shortly. The food arrived after another 10 minutes, two of the orders was a steak, one of them supposed to be medium rare but came practically raw and the other was supposed to be medium well but also came pretty rare. The one order was supposed to be with rice as opposed to mashed potatoes. The worse possible service we could have ever gotten. We ate what we could and left as soon as possible. After we left, not long after 2 of the people who had ordered the fish did not feel good after and ended up with food poisoning for the rest of our night, one of them being my mother. Thanks for ruining our mothers day dinner. I don‚Äôt see us returning ever again.

This was my second visit here and while the food was good the service or lack of it was very dissapointing and poorly executed. Being Mother's day the restaurant was busy but not to the extreme. Other patrons came after us and left before us. There was some mix up with our order apparently but we didn't find that out until we asked a few times after waiting for an hour or so. Our appetizers and main course took forever to come. The portion sides that came with our dinner was very small considering the prices. It kind of took away a bit from being out with family but we didn't let it totally ruin our evening.

The place is very nice and I highly recommend it. The only reason it doesn‚Äôt get the full five stars is because I think they change their menu and removed the potatoes From the chicken souvlaki dinner. Which leaves you feeling it‚Äôs a rather expensive dish. 

Otherwise food is excellent. And the staff are always courteous and caring. Perhaps the best Greek restaurant in Scarborough

reviews.text:
The service was excellent!
We had a small celebration for our wedding with our family there. From the beginning it was great, they helped us choose the details and guided us all the time.
Food was awesome and everything felt like it went so smoothly.
The place is beautiful.
It can be of course pricey but it's worth it!

Wonderful place to experience with family and friends.  Great food, great service and beautiful atmosphere. Portions are on the smaller side but the  freshness, quality and taste of the various dishes was wonderful.  I enjoyed the steak immensely, cooked properly,  no overwhelming taste of excessive spices.

Got married here 10 years ago and recently went back to celebrate our anniversary. Service and food is still impeccable and the place is just as beautiful as ever. Our favourite restaurant in Canada. It's a little piece of France in the big city.

Super food in a very beautiful restaurant with widely spaced tables, low noise and fabulous service. Really a delight! It's not inexpensive, but given what they offer, it's quite reasonable value. So, all in all, recommended!

As a couple we were celebrating a birthday and decided to take to the patio for a dinner reservation.  The climate in the restaurant was just right, and the patio was very nice.  The patio took you to another place perhaps a back patio in France with nice decor, greenery, landscaping and stone work.  The restrooms were clean and well maintained.

We had an entree each and shared two sides including the salad and mushrooms.  The monkfish was delicious with the texture of lobster, but even better in my opinion.  The lamb with black garlic custard was tender throughout with absolutely no "tough" or gritty areas and nothing stuck in-between the teeth by the end of dining.   There was just the mildest and almost unnoticeable scent typical of lamb.  The meat was cooked medium rare and was of high quality.  A bottle of wine paired very well with the dinner and I recommend it for an occasion.   To sum it up: everything presented in each entree was art with harmonious flavours of the components.  Savoring every bite at a relaxed pace made this the perfect experience.  The plump olives were pickled in-house, and the bread was very fresh.  Unfortunately we were too stuffed to attempt dessert.

Chad was our charming and attentive waiter who never let our glass of water or wine deplete more than 1/3rd of the way to the bottom.  His suggestions were great and we took his word on the sides.  Andrew was assisting and also attentive and a pleasure to talk to.  They ensured that we were satisfied at all times, and they succeeded!  Their smiles were genuine as they enjoyed seeing us happy.

The 45m car ride at 6pm was well worth the occasion at Auberge du Pommier.  Thank you for making this one of my best dining experiences in a very long time!  Management, chef(s) and servers.

reviews.text: My husband and I have been here a couple of times. Each visit we had superb and friendly service, the food was fresh and tasty, and the prices were very reasonable. Their patio isn't the best, but their indoor decor is interesting. During our last visit we were served by Maria, who was absolutely lovely and went above and beyond. We ordered a soup to share. Which they were happy to divvy up into separate bowls. I ordered the prosciutto pizza which was really good and my husband had the burger which he said was very tasty. I loved the small coke bottles too!

Looks can be deceiving. From the outside, and yes the dated inside, you may want to walk on by or leave, if already entered, DON'T! Grab a seat an indulge your taste buds. My lovely wife and I dined there earlier this evening before taking in a show at a nearby theatre. We had hummus, beet salad, PEI mussels, gluten-free pizza and a succulent lamb shank dinner. A must stop for sure if you're in the area.

Saturday brunch at this warm and welcoming Mediterranean restaurant was a pretty relaxing experience. We went around 1.30PM in June. The restaurant wasn't very busy, the waiters attentive but non-intrusive, the food delicious and the ambience comfortable for weekend brunch. I would go again and Highly recommended

Nice cozy atmosphere, extremely friendly staff and excellent food. We had a small party of five, and we all had a diverse selection of mains, mine being the slow roasted lamb. We all thoroughly enjoyed our meals, as they were top notch

What got me was the friendly and warm staff, and regular patrons. This felt like a business that prides itself on good food and warm at-home atmosphere. Cannot recommend enough!

reviews.text: Food was awful. We ordered the Seared Tuna Tacos, Chorizo and Andouille Flat Bread and Dill Salmon. The tuna was so bland tasting we couldn‚Äôt finish it and the pizza was luke warm and tasted like the stuff you get from a grocery store. We were so upset that by the time the salmon came around, we had had enough. We tried one bite and left it; bland just like the tuna.  They had asked if we enjoyed the first half of the meal, to which we replied ‚Äúit was very one note, not that good‚Äù and while she offered another dish, we ended up paying full price. You‚Äôd think because we left a taco, almost all of the dill and some of the pizza, the server might of clued in we early did not enjoy our meal but that was not the case. We paid almost $150 (full price even for the tacos which they knew we highly disliked) for our meal (3 drinks included) and I‚Äôm infuriated at myself for doing so. I have no problem spending money on good food but this was the worst meal I‚Äôve ever had out.

Hotel looks quite dated from the outside. I liked how azure was right in the lobby near the main entrance with soaring windows. It's probably gorgeous during the day with the sunlight pouring in. 

We had dinner there and were served by William. He was truly an amazing server who was extremely competent and was happy to cater to every whim of ours regarding our dietary needs.   The dips platter was not that fantastic but we enjoyed the Atlantic char fish. Oxtail was pretty good too.  A staff member like William is a true credit to the hotel.  Pity I can't say the same about some of the other staff at the hotel. 

The mains portions were pretty good and we enjoyed the breads and starters as well. I'm.not a huge fan of pumpkin so the pumpkin tart was a bit lost on me.

A nice restaurant. Ambience was nice and there is ample seating as well. It‚Äôs located in the lower level of the hotel. I had the shrimp linguini and calamari. The food is great but on the pricey side‚Äîthe pastas were ranging close to $30

Food - 2/5
Service - 4/5
Ambiance - 3/5

Underwhelming to say the least. If you are looking for good food, and can leave the hotel lobby - be adventurous! It felt like a crime to eat at this restaurant with all the delicious restaurants within walking distance.

I was here for a recent conference at Metro Toronto Convention Centre. It is very conveniently situated next to the Convention Centre. We had a sweet potato soup which was OK, but the pork shoulder was divine! Great ambience for a meeting, both casual and business. Apparently their chef has won certain awards... not sure what kind it is. Average, expected price for the location, food and ambience.

reviews.text:
Took a while for me to write them a review, but here it is. 

I have been to the restaurant three times for brunch (when they still served weekend brunch)...
Perhaps it was the type of foods that we ordered (we opted out of the carte blanche menu due to different tastes, preferences, and dietary restrictions of...
I'm so sad to report that I really didn't love the food here. We spent $125 on the cote de beouf and it was so burned on the outside to the point of tasting...

Brought a group of colleagues and visiting physicians to Bacchanal for a get-to-know-you supper.  We had the menu option which was served family style.  The seafood tower was delicious - oysters were very fresh and prawns cooked just right.  Marinated duck breast, ravioli.  It was all tasty and the service was excellent.  Recommended.
It's also a pleasant spot for a dinner for two - good for date night.

I'm really surprised with all the people raving about the food. I'd have to agree with the reviewer who said the food was boring and bland, especially for the price.  At that price point there are far better options in toronto.  We were a party of 8 so we had an opportunity to try quite a few things from the menu.  Nothing impressive at all. Based on the reviews I was excited to try it, but it was a real let down.  That being said, aside from the food, service was good, the wines were good and decor is nice.  But likely will not go back.

Nicely decorated. Great food and lovely staff. Well portioned and priced. 
They have a spacious private area right by the kitchen where you can sneak in chef‚Äôs secret touches !!

Great restaurant and bar at convention location. Very nice French style cuisine, the menu only features around a total of 25 dishes all included but what a selection. Everything we had was cooked to perfection with fresh ingredients and great flavour. The wine selection added to the great experience.  Not to forget the fact that the very nice guy behind the bar has competed  in and won several drink competitions around the world. The combinations of ingredients in his cocktails made my head spin in more ways than one. There is a parking garage located beneath the restaurant ensuring easy access. 
If you enjoy high quality food and drinks served by knowledgeable and attentive staff this is the place to go.

It is hard to give four‚≠ê to this gem. Food was absolutely awesome deserve 5/5. The service was more like 2 üåü. When we came in the server who greeted us was on his phone texting. When he took our order his phone was beeping all the time! He carefully slipped his hand in his pocket to make it silent. VERY UNPROFESSIONAL. Ownership please take action before this place getting more bad reviews.

FOOD

We came here for a work function lunch, and it being my first time visiting Bangkok Garden, I was pleasantly surprised by how delicious their food was. 

We...

Excellent service from the moment we walked in.  Greeted warmly and assured our dietary restrictions would be accommodated.  By the time our server came to our table, she had already been informed of our dietary restrictions and reviewed the menu with us, pointing out what items could be modified accordingly.  Great service, delicious food, child-friendly.

Brought the family which includes 2 young children here for dinner. The kids plates from the kids menu are large enough to split but we ordered a pad Thai and a chicken fried rice which come with a spring roll each. These plates came first and both kids loved them. Having taken a sample of each, they both very flavorful and very good indeed.
Wife ordered a curry plate and I took the pad sew ew (large rice noodles) and both were off the chart good. Came for a weekend visit to Toronto, would definitely recommend this restaurant and would definitely come back next time in town.

Very tasty Thai food. Good menu with some unique combinations. Very attentive service. Even though we did not have reservations the staff were able to seat us within 15 minutes despite it being a very full and busy night for the restaurant. So glad the maitre'd at the Marriott recommended this place.

Came for the lunch buffet on a weekday with a few colleagues. Decor is outstanding compared to most Thai restaurants. More of a higher end feel for sure. The buffet was a modest size with a custom noodles station as well. It definitely more than made up for it in quality for what it lacks in quantity. Pad Thai and both the red and yellow curry were outstanding. Noodle station although small is great as well. Not many dessert options but I didn't even have any room for it anyways. Would definitely come back again and my colleagues agreed.

Went for the buffet lunch($17.95 pp)
The cold glass noodles were amazing. I liked the green veggie curry as well, as it was just spiced enough for my liking.  A fair number of customers were getting the soup from the noodle bar, I did not try it though.
A nice small selection ( not Mandarin) but that's a good thing as the quantities are freshly made to refill the buffet. 
The dessert is fresh fruit and banana sweet potato fritters.

reviews.text: Very nice restaurant cozy place to enjoy a tasty meal. Family friendly with high chairs for children. Healthy meals on the menu creative presentations. My first time going there and would definitely go back with friends. Good service with a friendly staff. Located next door to the Bay on Queen st/ across from Eaton Centre.

This spot is a very accommodating, accessible restaurant located right in the Eaton Centre! There's ample space for sitting and eating-in, and you can order from a diverse menu that isn't overbearing in choice. Service is quick and very friendly, and the servers do a great job at making recommendations for your meal. It's worth making a reservation, as the restaurant tends to get pretty busy in the evenings. Definitely worth trying if you're in downtown Toronto!

We were a large group (12 people) this morning for lunch. Our server was excellent. Thank you! The food was fine though not inspired. I would return for the capacity to manage a large group with ease and accuracy.

Long wait for a table and the place was half empty. Once seated we were well looked after. Our party ordered fish and chips, pizza and spaghetti meatballs. All delicious. Would have scored 4 stars but for the long wait.

Everything is so good! Even the simple dishes like the grilled cheese and pancakes are delicious. We enjoyed the vibes and beer for a chilly Sunday brunch. I love the layout of the restaurant with the wine side and dine side. Perfect for anytime!
Came in between 3-4pm on a Saturday. Service was a little lack luster in the beginning. It took forever to get a water... and when it came it was in a rocks...
The poutine pizza ahhh ... carbs overload!! Combination of pizza and poutine defs will give you food coma - but was pretty tasty! The crab cakes and bannock...
I was disappointed in Bannock on a recent lunch visit. I should have known I was in for it ordering the "griddled fishwich" but I forged ahead nonetheless....

reviews.text: The food at Banu was so delicious!! Even something simple like bread was so good - it had a nice crunch and chew. Went for my first time and I will go back! The pink lady cocktail was perfect too! Not too sweet

One of the best Persian cuisines in Toronto. The waitstaff is great and takes care to explain and the service is on point. The flavours were very well combined and the food is delicious. This small Persian place packs a punch!!

Wonderful dinner last night with a colleague.  First time dining at Banu. The meats were over the top delicious. Cocktail menu exceptional.  Price is on par for neighborhood and quality.  Will return.

I have been here 3 times in the last 2 weeks. I love the flavours of the food and the drinks. Not something you find at other restaurants and I bought their sour cherry jam which they makes themselves and it was amazing. I love this place a lot and would highly recommend it.

Just amazing from start to finish. The staff is so helpful and know the ingredients very well even thoguh some of them are not Persian. The meat here is really melt in your mouth. My friend is vegetarian and had the Okra stew and he loved it. Also make sure you have their Persian saffron and pistachio ice cream - it was so good. It was my first time coming here but I will be back very soon. Merci banu.

My first time here : October 5th 2018
I ordered Chenjeh. It was good. I ordered an extra Koobedeh. It good too. I had glass of Dough. I can't compare with...
Came here for Summerlicious - worth a try to get a taste of Iranian food! The Cold Cucumber Soup was nice and refreshing. Vegetables Stew was quite hearty.
My friends & I just had it's Summerlicious 2018 dinner menu last night! Worth a try, great tasty Persian food! You have to call to make a reservation, there...

reviews.text: I was here with a group of friends on the weekend and our table got the bottomless brunch option. I think we tried almost everything on the menu and it was all delicious. Service was extremely friendly and prompt. I'll definitely be back soon.

I popped into Bar Altura Bar for a drink and was immediately blown away by the quality of service and food / drink offerings. Perfect spot for a classy but unpretentious date or dinner with friends. We went for their Thursday for some buck a shuck oysters and half priced bubbly and are excited to return for their Wednesday Pizza deal. Cozy and clean atmosphere! Definitely one of the nicer spots on Queen and I would recommend it. 5/5

Wow! Great little restaurant with a lovely menu, delicious food, great drinks (talented bartender) and great staff. If you're ever in the mood for a high quality bite with a little flare this place is a must go. And don't come unless you're hungry, the portions are perfect you won't want to let anything get cold!

Beautiful bar with cozy and yet modern interior which was one of the reasons I wanted to check this place out. Good quality of service and calm ambience make you very relaxed. Gave 4 star instead of 5 as their 1$ oyster deals on Thursdays was not ideal. size of the oysters were very small, so a bit disappointed for that.
I went here for my friend's wedding reception. I enjoyed the Risotto and the pizzas! Great atmosphere and attentive staff.
This place does not have good food. Nothing special or memorable. Average price point with food that reflects it. I really don't have much more to say....
Possibly the best brunch in Toronto. Do not hesitate to come here to indulge in some excellent freshly squeezed bottomless mimosas paired with some...
I loves the arugula watercress pear salad - it was bitter from radiccio, peppery, sweet, creamy from brie and crunchy. The arancini were also very good but...

reviews.text:
This was a great restaurant. The food was delicious and the place was trendy without being pretentious. The prices were also very reasonable.

The pizzas...

Overall enjoyed all the menu items. Service was good. Cocktail was exceptional! 

Yes, price point is definitely high but all Buca locations are generally...

Two words: greasy and overpriced. I paid $48 for my dish, dessert, and ros√© (not including tip). 

I had the gnochetti as my "main". The portion was small....

Had a wonderful time at Buca!
Went for a Birthday Brunch and the food was absolutely incredible. This place really knows how to make eggs in many many ways. The restaurant is super cute with excellent pastries. Not a whole lot of seating so you might have to prepare to wait. The service was alright, but even that couldn't take away from the delicious items. Would definitely go back either to this location or another one in the chain.

Nice cafe, wine list and small but substantial menu. They have communal tables for sit down. Good selection of pastries and coffee. They also have gelato! Downside is the portions are on the smaller side.

In a nutshell, not going back. 

1.	In today‚Äôs day and age, it‚Äôs not that difficult to have a system in place to text or call people who are on a waiting list. Instead, in this place you would have to wait around inside the restaurant/bar. In our example, we had to wait for 1.5 hours. I‚Äôm sure this is to ensure that you are not spending a dime outside of this place while you are waiting. I would have preferred the option so I could go across the street for a beer sitting down instead of drinking cocktails standing around a high table. 
2.	Food taste and portion sizes don‚Äôt justify the price. In addition, at the price you pay for some of these plates (and I mean tiny plates here) you expect to get perfect dishes and they are not! The short rib skewer had 4 small pieces and 2 of them were mostly fat and very little meat. 
3.	When we first started to order food, we were told that they were out of pizza doughs for the night. In about an hour after we ordered bunch of dishes, the waiter comes by and says they have 6 pizza doughs!!! Could it be that they wanted to make sure we maximize our spending and then offer dishes that are more filling???!!! I would think so‚Ä¶we ended up ordering a couple of pizza and again back to point #2, not worth it‚Ä¶.

A pretty terrible dining experience. I went with 6 girlfriends and they only have 3 six person tables, two people were sitting at one ü§¶üèª‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è so we were given this wobbly makeshift thing that can't even be described as a table because it was only a foot wide. We didn't have enough room for plates on the fada thing!

I ordered an arugula salad (literally was just greens with nothing else) and the salmon (salmon covered in pesto with no sides, just the fish) and a water (tap!) And it came out to $40. The food was fine but not worth the money. 

The restaurant only has high tops with really uncomfortable chairs, so if you're looking to sit and enjoy, go somewhere else.

The service was horrific. Our server was rude and arrogant. If we asked him a question about the menu he gave us a look like he couldn't be bothered and we were annoying him. 

Overall, a terrible experience. I would never go back. All of my friends were extremely disappointed.

We usually go there in the mornings so it isn‚Äôt that much crowded, very attentive staff and managers. Always greeted with us with smiles.
Their Americano is the best in the city, small but powerful!!, their selection of pastries are great.

Had a delicious birthday dinner for my mother with my sister and her boyfriend here. My mom ordered the steak, which she said was fantastic and I got a chicken breast, also fantastic. Each plate of food was worth every dollar. Great selection of wines as well.
Ate lunch here today out on the patio. Absolutely delicious. Warm spinach salad, Eggs Benedict, omelette, trout.... everything was wonderful, and the service was great. Thank you!
Barista & Chef is a hidden foodie gem!! AMAZING food and the owners are so welcoming and friendly!  They also have a wonderful patio, which is perfect for the warmer weather.
Amazing experience with a large group.  Owner was very accommodating and a great host. Delicious! Had a great time and will come back!

Good burger, good beer on rotation. 

I ate at Batch a couple weeks ago during a work related trip to TO with a colleague. We were craving a good burger and...
My fianc√©e and I came here for our last meal in Toronto with my best friend and her boyfriend. We were looking for something casual and easy. Batch happened...

I came here for Winterlicious and had no idea what to expect. Glad to say I left tastebuds satisfied and belly full!

Batch has a great atmosphere; it is...
The Crispy Chicken Sandwich changed my life. Great selection of beers too. Location is nice as well that it‚Äôs tucked away but in a central location.

The food was good, it's an upscale place which I really liked and the portion sizes were good too. It's really loud though, so you're going to have to really speak up if you're coming here to have a conversation. üòÖüëå

I had their chicken wings tossed in spicy sauce (forgot the name) and it was amazing! I have an abnormally high spice tolerance, so nothing fazes me. However, the spicy wings were tasty and actually pretty spicy. Appreciated the friendly and chill service. The interior design is gram-worthy, so if that matters to you, you'll enjoy your visit. I had an overall fantastic experience and will be visiting again!

As most pubs go, their beers are better than their food, and Batch is no exception. They have more than a dozen home-brewed beers, most of them are worth trying, especially their fruitier drinks. Their food is mostly just for filler; get their chicken wings to-go if you're looking for a late night meal. 

It's pretty loud indoors. They also have ping pong tables in the basement but expect a lineup to play those. At their prices, it's worth going to try out the beers on tap.
Good in house beer selection. The food was excellent, especially the lamb briyani. Staff checked on us often because he knew we had a show to go to, and he was super friendly.

The mac & cheese was good & a good portion size. The restaurant has an open kitchen concept with chic decor. The staff is attentive & friendly. Fine dinning for this area.

Fantastic dinner for 3 course! Good taste wine! Becca is the best waitress because she learns how sign language for deaf people.  We ate so impressed that she signed. thank you and welcome  . She is so wonderful person

Very nice restaurant, good service but not always the fastest.  Expensive.  Snacks really mean a small plate good for one person or two seriously light eaters if thinking of them as appetizers!  But they were all very good... The corn one, calamari and the baked brie were all awesome.  Had the fettuccine, got full looking at it.  So saved room for the creme brulee instead!  All very good.  Drinks are also very good here too.

An absolute must stop when in the area.  The food is always incredible and the ambience always upscale and relaxing. The daily soups are incredible and the mains wonderfully put together. Kyle was attentive and knowledgeable as our server and the front of house so welcoming. Highly recommended.

EDIT: Since writing this review management have gotten in touch with me to apologize which they didn't have to do and I have returned for another event since. 

---------------------------------------------------------

Went recently for a birthday brunch, nice interior, seated timely, seemed like it was going to be a fine experience. 

The burger arrived with mayo which it did not say it would have, other menu items specifically noted if it had mayo, no big deal I'll tell the server and it'll be dealt with. 

"Excuse me this has mayo, and I didn't want mayo"
"You didn't tell me that" 

Was pretty taken aback by that response, told him it didn't say it was on the burger, after a little heated debate eventually it was conceded the burger would be replaced, guess that's nice of them. Then the experience was ruined as the attitude pricked up more than once over very simple requests that no one at the table was angry or in a rush over. 

All in all the food WAS good, maybe a bit overpriced, maybe a little bit too portion controlled, but it was good. 

The overall experience though was bad, no one in our party will be returning.
the decor and ambience was so so...but the FOOD stood out.  THE PB&J for 2 desert was amazing and that peanut butter was like REESE'S lol.  I had the lamb...

Friendly service but sometimes felt a bit stuffy. Maybe it was the atmosphere. 

Meal was pretty good but nothing stood out. O&B definitely has better...

lic_profile: Located in the heart of Little Italy, family owned and operated Bella Vista brings together all the traditions and authenticity of Italian cuisine into a contemporary, yet relaxed dining atmosphere.  Comfortable seating, soft colours, and a bar that illuminates a warm glow create an inviting atmosphere. Combine that with friendly staff and authentic Italian cuisine, and what you get is a unique dining experience, each and every time.

reviews.text: Came here a few months ago to celebrate my recent engagement with some girlfriends. We had such an amazing time! Our server, Roberto, really made the night special for me. He recommend some amazing meals and his friendly and personable personality was really quite a treat. The food was amazing, the service was incredible, the atmosphere was lovely. I will definitely be going back and recommending it to anyone looking for a nice Italian meal.   Oh, and the cocktails were unique and delicious.

Came June 4th. Hospitality was wonderful. We were greeted as soon as we walked in. Restaurant is clean and has a warm, rich atmosphere without feeling stuffy. We were given various recommendations regarding our orders when we asked questions, which all turned out to be perfect choices. From our appetizers to our wine, and meal selections. The fresh pasta is a little extra in cost but 100% worth it. Rich and buttery. Looking forward to returning.

Great food and one of the most amazing service I have ever received. The server was beyond welcoming and had great recommendations! I would highly recommend. The place even has TVs for those of you who want to watch the game while having a nice date/family night.

My husband and I found Bella Vista by accident and I'm so glad we did!! Right away we both noticed how peaceful and perfect the ambience was. Roberto and Pat were absolutely wonderful hosts and the service was fantastic..the food was even better!! Best pasta ever!! The tiramisu was simply incredible!!! Go visit, you won't be disappointed!! We loved the experience and this will definitely be our go-to spot!

The atmosphere is warm, classy and inviting. Fresh pasta and seafood is amazing. Drinks are tasty. A nice bar for sporting events and a beautiful dining area for special celebration big or small. Service is professional and friendly. We will be back soon.  Prices are fair. It‚Äôs a hidden gem on college st.

Slow and inept service, weak drinks, and bland, minimal-effort food.

lic_profile: A Japanese steakhouse experience in the heart of Toronto, Benihana lets you enjoy the excitement of teppan cooking right at your table.  Instead of using conventional kitchens, Benihana's highly skilled chefs present and prepare the freshest beef, seafood and produce at a 'hibachi' table (a flat 4'x 3' grill), around which, up to eight guests are seated. A fast-paced performance of chopping and juggling creates an exciting teppanyaki-style dining experience for guests of all ages.

reviews.text:
Unique Teppanyali experience in Downtown Toronto inside at the Fairmount Royal York Hotel. 

My wife arrived earlier and I was late due to traffic. They...
Not the Benihana experience I know and love. I have been to so many Benihana restaurants and normally it is the highlight of my trip. This fell short in...
We came as a party of 7 and ATE IT UP! Toto was a great chef. Very entertaining and very experienced. He's been with Benihana's all over the world. Connie...

Terribly over rated

This was my first visit to the famed Benihana. Made famous decades ago for their then unique Hibachi grill (table side open grill), the concept is now much, much more common and indeed can now even be found in many vacation resorts in many southern sun destinations. 

Concept aside, the room is basic and while the service was polite, attentive, and responsive to issues, of which there were a few - both with our meals and neighboring guests, the food simply is not worth anywhere near the prices asked which are close to fine dining. The quality of the ingredients and worse, their preparation was very mediocre at best. 

If it's Japanese food you crave, there are many much better examples to be found, especially here in Toronto. 

In the absence of a unique experience and solid quality food, save your $$$, not a repeat and not recommended.

I liked this place and the food was great but I kinda expected a bit more pizazz from the chef.  He did a few typical fire tricks and tried to toss food in my wife's mouth (took 5 attempts) but I was expecting a bit more for a Saturday night in the Royal York.  I'd still go back.
I love this place. I been there with my first,second, and third wife.I love their food so much i,m getting divorced, and coming again with my forth .
Amazing experience, great food and helpful staff! I loved every moment here and can't wait to go back.

Shrimp and veggies were good.
Filet mignon plain, same with chicken.
Good show for one time.

Me and my sister are new visiting Toronto, so we relied on reviews and word of mouth for restaurants. Well we found  an absolute gem in this restaurant,...

Lovely quiet dinner place. We met friends for dinner and we arrived only an hour before the kitchen closed but they stayed to ensure we got our food including dessert. It was quiet and allowed us to carry on a conversation. The salmon was very nice. They don't offer chicken.
A great Italian restaurant offering all the classic dishes. Food is excellent as well as the service. A classy restaurant for anniversaries, birthday's or special events.

We have eaten at Biagio a few times now. The service is always gracious and discrete.  The food is outstanding. Whether you dine during Winterlicious or on a quiet night, the food is consistently good. This evening I had the veal medallions. They were tender, minimally seasoned. They were cooked to medium rare and absolutely delicious. My husband had pasta and raved about it. The wine list is extensive & a bit pricey, but keep in mind there are half bottles available as well as house wine which is available by the glass. We will definitely be back again.
Quite possibly the best meal we've ever had. The lamb shanks were perfect and my wife loved the fettuccine. Dessert was fantastic and a very extensive wine list. We will be back!
Most amazing lunch experience! The ambiance was magical, the food was delicious, and the service was the cherry on top! Great restaurant for a special occasion, visiting really felt like a treat!

reviews.text: I took my mother to Bier Markt for her birthday and we had a really nice time.  Our sever Katherin was awesome! She let us try a couple beers before picking the one that we really liked.  Our food was delicious and the beers were too.  We were surprised with a little chocolate brownie as a birthday dessert. :) Great Time!

Love the Bier Markt, lots of parking in the lot, staff are friendly and the food is great. I suggest the duck wings ($15) and sharing platters! I wish the sharing platters came with crackers as well as the bread, but otherwise love this place. Its never been busy when I've been there so great for large groups as well.

The selection of beer and drinks here are great as they have options for everyone. Food is mediocre and they recently changed the menu and increased the prices a bit, unfortunately this did not increase the quality of the food. The service is always hit or miss. One time I was waiting 30 + minutes for a drink and another I was served within 5, both times they were equally as busy. Last time I went I also waited over 45 minutes for an appetizer. Nice place, but be prepared for mediocre quality food and long wait times.
We had a delicious lunch on the patio and the service was great. The young lady at the front (Alexa) was so kind to direct us around the shopping plaza after our lunch. Nice place.

Great place for beer food and shareable dishes. Great selection of beer and three options for non-alcoholic beers. I really enjoyed their fish and chips among other main entrees. This is a good place for big group gatherings.

Salad is fresh and delicious....

reviews.text: Have been to Biffs many times for dinner and had wonderful experiences, this time however we never got the chance. Came in on a whim for lunch. It wasn't very busy, but took forever for someone to greet us. The young hostess approached us and said she would be right with us. She proceeded to walk to the back and returned with a drink, and was just chatting and laughing at the bar. She then went to a table and took away their dishes and did not return. We waited another minute and just walked out. 5 minutes without anyone acknowledging us. Extremely disappointing. We went to the Cafe Grill next door and had a wonderful time. I really enjoy Biffs, but this left a sour taste in my mouth

Food and service at lunch were great as usual, Lucy is amazing. But first impressions as we walked in, was the hostess, texting as we walked in, not even acknowledging us. No hello, and an unimpressed look on her face as she sat us. Oh and she dropped our soup spoon on the floor and put it back on the table. Had to ask another staff member for a new one. GROSS.

Will be back, but hostess needs some training in professionalism.

Food and service for lunch were great. When we eventually got seated. Young hostess at the front was more preoccupied chatting and laughing at the bar than greeting guests. When she finally came over, she was rude, condescending and unprofessional. As we were venting our frustration at the table, the table next to us agreed, as their experience at the front was much the same. First impressions matter when you walk into a restaurant. On this occasion, she didn‚Äôt seem to care. 4 stars for service and food, 0 stars for customer service.

Classic french food that always delivers. The service is great, the space is refined and clean and the food is awesome. The terrine makes me salivate, I always get it as a starter! My friend had the french onion soup and said it was the best she's ever had in her life.
Best Duck Confit I have had from Paris to Texas. Very classy atmosphere. Great service

One of the best Indian restaurants in Toronto Downtown. You can go there for good ambience and quality Indian food. Will definitely go there again. Chef is good and serving staff is very friendly. Overall had a good experience.

Wow ..amazing bistro. Presentation, food, taste, ambience all in one package. I couldn't believe even samosa as starter was in house where most of the restaurant provide outsourced. Curry taste is so great and roti was soft and dissolving..overall excellent.

I took one of my very good friend to the city. It was her first time in Toronto and we had lunch at this restaurant. It was such an amazing experience. I have a thing for sitting arrangement and I must say the arrangement was comfortable. You could sit outside and see the beautiful view of the city. 
The food on the other hand was delicious. It was actually my first time trying Indian food and I'm literally obsessed. I ordered the butter chicken and I love the taste of the spice and the smell of the aroma. 

Overall, I would definitely recommend this restaurant to anyone!!

Went with some colleagues on a weekday...they loved it as it was their first experience  to try Indian cuisine ... the restaurant environment  was better than other Indian restaurants. .kind of high end.. maybe that's why the dishes were expensive too.. foodie alert: food portions are small.

The decor and atmosphere of the restaurant was really nice, and the service staff is friendly. The food was served hot and delicious, however it felt more like it was catered towards looking trendy then making it taste as great as possible. I would still recommend Bindia for a date night, but if you're looking for the best Indian food, there are some other places for it.

Friendly staff and interesting food. We liked lunch so much we are going back to try dinner! Okay.... we went back for dinner and it was even better. Paella and stuffed chicken exceptional. Pedro is a great waiter. The calamari so so but everything else was so good, who noticed.

I rarely give 5 star reviews but I felt substantial value. The place is mid to high priced so don't expect any cheap meal here. When we arrived, they overbooked and we had to be squeezed in but they certainly took care of us that's for sure. The owner made us feel important and made a solution for us. The food took a while because they said it was fully prepared fresh to order so don't come VERY hungry. The wine glass for a reasonably 6oz starts at $12. In the end, we were full and the food was exceptional. It's an inviting place to eat.

Tried it today. Food was fantastic! You can tell that they didn't rush every dishes that are coming out from the kitchen. The paella is the best! Will recommend it to others and definitely not our last time to be here. We will definitely come back! Very welcoming as well as they greeted you at the door and ask you for your coat to be hanged by them.

I only take the time to write review when I believe the food is below standards despite the high ratings or I feel getting low value for money. 

For Bloom Restaurant, the food and service was good but it's overpriced for what you get and the ambiance & setting doesn't match up to the menu price. Some food portions seemed small (e.g octopus), some dishes were fairly simple (e.g. Cuban special, enchiladas ) and some dishes shouldn't command a high price of $30++.   

Bottom line:  Overpriced
Delightful hospitality to compliment the wonderful food. Quality ingredients and brilliant preparation.

lic_profile: On the quiet eastern front of Yorkville, set back behind a brick fa√ßade, Blu is an Italian restaurant featuring authenticly classic yet contemporary cuisine.  Executive Chef Massimo Callovini originally from Trento, Italy and Chef de Cuisine, Eric Bucher from California, created a menu where traditional Italian flavours are presented with a contemporary fresh Californian influence.  Impeccably served in an upscale dining room with warmly lit stone walls, grand mirrors, and cozy leather seating, and enhanced by soothing live music Friday and Saturday, dinner is a truly memorable experience.

reviews.text:
Really not sure why we had not been to Blu before, and are already planning our next dinner there.
We booked Blu for a Birthday party dinner for 8, and the great experience started before we even arrived.  Alfredo was very helpful in setting up Antipasto and Dessert recommendations for the group in advance,  and we knew we were going to be in good hands.
Our experience from arrival, through closing it down was fantastic, with each and every staff member working together to create a great atmosphere based on exceptional service.
Great food, great atmosphere, great music, and we were fortunate enough to be there on an evening that Sara Dell was performing.  Don, and the rest of the wait staff ensured that we had a great night, and the kitchen kept delivering great food.  Yes, you should add the Veal Chop to the Menu!
Looking forward to our next meal and exploring the menu some more.
Thank you Blu!

Spent our Anniversary night there, and Wow! Have to say the staff was extremely friendly. Everyone from our waiter Michael to the person that poured our drinks wished us for the day. Food was delicious and the ambience brilliant! Thanks guys for making our day. We will be back!

Great place to take a date. The ambiance is absolutely amazing and the live music was fantastic  touch. Just the right level to enjoy your company and the music. The service was above my expectations. Fast, personable and friendly.

We hosted a dinner event for 100+ entrepreneurs in Toronto. Everyone had a fantastic experience. We host these dinners in different cities and this was by far one of the best. Everything from the food to ambience to service was impeccable. Alfredo and team went above and beyond. We will be back.
Undoubtedly, the best Italian food in the town. Delicious Italian dishes. Amazing decor. Service is top notch. Really appreciable.

reviews.text:
Had brunch on the patio, food was excellent. I had the lamb burger it was up there with the best gourmet burgers I have had to date and I eat out a lot. 

Service was great, our server was very polite, professional, knowledgeable about the menu and attentive.

Menu is quite extensive and has great options to choose from. They have a fixed 3 course brunch or order the regular way whatever you want. They also have drink specials charging mimosa's for $5 which is better priced than the regular $10 per glass.

Patio is decent size with lots of umbrellas which is ideal for the summer weather.

Highly recommend and will certainly be back again. Most definitely telling my friends about this place!

Thanks for an amazing brunch!

Loved it! The food was excellent! Really nice ambiance and excellent service. My table was very chatty but the waitresses still found a way to get their job done exceptionally without being too intrusive. Really well done.

Absolutely love this restaurant. Great place for lunch or dinner. Incredible venue for groups and parties. Unlike other restaurants downtown they don't require a deposit or family style menu. They have prix fixe menus at different price points to cater to a wide range of dietary preferences. Their service is top notch. I always try to select this venue for any work related or personal events from just their service alone. The food is also delicious, in the wide range of dishes I've tried in all my visits. I'd highly recommend, their mushroom risotto and their lamb shank. For dessert, a slice of their pecan pie with ice cream is highly recommended.

Beautifil space, great servers and a lovely patio.
The food is pricey but worth it and they have a discounted time from 3-6pm.
Strong recommend.

Exquisite food! Went for lunch or a coworker's birthday and the place was very nice! The overall decor was seemed quite French inspired and the service was wonderful! Definitely looking forward to coming here again.
Thank  you for a wonderful meal. We ordered through UberEats. First of all, everything was well-packaged, the vegetables separate from the steak, the salad...

reviews.text: Hands down the best meal I've eaten out in the last 12 months! All the flavours were perfectly balanced and delicious. The trout and the salmon were cooked...

Pop in for a quick lunch

Love heading to Boland's for a nice lunch.  They serve lunch size dishes that are perfect size and always something a little...
We randomly stumbled into this neighbourhood gem for lunch, and were pleasantly surprised. Although I had heard of Chef Boland and his Kitchen for several...

My girlfriend and I came here for our anniversary. It was great! We ordered the duck appetizer which was superb. She also had the souffle, which she personally didn't like, but I gave it a try and it was good!

I ordered their venison wrapped in prosciutto, as it was their special of the night. It was absolutely exceptional. I had it medium rare and the second you cut into it, you know it's perfect. It had this delicious red hue and tasted very fresh and wonderful. The prosciutto also greatly complemented the dish. The dish comes with some roasted peppers and mushrooms, and is served on mashed potatoes and gravy.

The waiter was also extremely friendly and attentive.  I loved his enthusiasm. We had a great time, and would definitely be back.

I am giving a 2 star today due to the experience. I am willing to go again and re-rate but for my first time there, it was worth a 2 star.

Starting off at the greeting at the door. Walking in, the whole front part of the restaurant was full due to a large party that had a reservation. Nothing bad. Just caught off guard. The waiters seemed confused by our presence. Granted we were multiple minutes early for our reservation. But it was still an awkward situation.

We ordered beverages. I tend to create cocktails on the fly depending what selection of liqueur the bar has. The staff seemed to be unfamiliar with the liqueur I had selected even though it was displayed on their bar rack. The creation  I made was quite delicious. I thank the bar tender who added the raspberry garnish. Good choice!
A sample of appetizers were offered with bread, while we waited for our food. I am a picky eater so my opinion on these samples will not be helpful to anyone. As for the main course, I ordered the beef rib. The beef itself was a little overcooked, the seasonal vegetables were good, but nothing particularly special. The mashed potatoes were creamy but a little on the dry side. What probably saved the dish was the delicious sauce it came in. Seriously just mix the sauce into every bite.
During our meal, a few empty plates and used cutlery were dropped on the way back to the kitchen. When it was time to pay, the bills were mixed up and not the typical distribution error, the order on the receipt was mismatched. Ratified quickly in any case.

Overall, just an awkward first impression. The ambiance of the place has a warm cozy feel to it, and even if the staff seemed confused, they were good and dutiful.
The atmosphere was homey very European hospitality.  The food and the wine were excellent with the host very animated and passionate about both. A great experience

I was excited to try this restaurant but I left disappointed. The staff, although the service was fine, seemed stiff and emotionless. The food, although the ingredients seemed fresh, were cooked without much seasoning, making the dish bland and flavourless. I don‚Äôt know if we went on a weird day, but I won‚Äôt try this place again, and would recommend others stay away.

Incredible meat selection with every dish, plus a healthy portion of veggies when they're a side. The venison was spectacular. Also a great wine selection. Great decoration and sophisticated yet warm atmosphere

This is a friendly neighborhood bistro tucked away on a side street off Yonge south of St Clair. A long history of serving Rosedale regulars. Someone said...
Nice atmosphere. I didn't love our waitress, rushing us to order. No cocktail list. Main courses did not come out all together so we sat and waited. I had...

Fantastic service, delicious food. This was advertised as a Hidden Gem on Open Table, and they weren't wrong! Our server went above and beyond to make sure we enjoyed our food, and accomodated our requests. Will definitely be coming here again, so many good dishes to try!

We had dinner at this restaurant, and we had such an incredible experience. The food was delicious, and we wanted to complement the chefs on the high culinary standard of the dishes coming out of their kitchen. The squid starter was one of the most perfectly cooked seafood dishes I've had. The service was perfect. We couldn't love this family run restaurant more.

I brought my date here on Valentine‚Äôs Day and from the moment we walked in through the doors, to the time we were leaving, their service was impeccable! 

We ordered the flank steak with mashed potatoes - the steak was cooked to perfection and I had the best mashed potatoes ever!! We also ordered the angel hair pasta - this dish has become a favourite of mine!! They always made sure our glasses were never empty! 

I can‚Äôt wait to come back to Brownes Bistro! Thank you!

My dining experience at Brownes Bistro was overall wonderful. The service is amazing and the food is exquisite. We were greeted by friendly staff and were seated very quickly. The menu was easy to choose from, and the meals were prepared perfectly. Highly recommended!

Spent my Valentine's Day dinner at Browne's and my experience was nothing short of exceptional. Despite a super busy day, the staff went above and beyond to make sure our time there was an enjoyable one. The food was amazing and their extensive wine list gave us plenty of options. Our waiter, Jerry, was also very knowledgable about the perfect wine pairings for our meals. Will definitely recommend this gem to friends and family and will be back soon. Cheers

reviews.text:
Home to one of the best burgers in the GTA is this venerable lunch and dinner spot in the middle of the financial district. It has the feel of an upscale speakeasy due to its location in the basement of the TD centre. It has no windows but the decor of dark woods and dim lighting certainly makes it feel cozy. Nice place to have a business lunch. 

They've tried to change it up with an aged burger but still go for their classic burger which is topped with mushrooms and truffles for $40. The patty is cooked medium and is just right to keep the meat moist and flavourful. The fries are also excellent.

Came here for a Winterlicious lunch. The service was attentive and not too bothersome. Quality of the food is amazing. Presentation was very nice as well - most dishes were very dainty and pretty to look at. The caramel apple cheesecake was a great way to finish the meal.

We went there for a Winterlicious lunch. It was one of the best meals I have ever had. The service was exceptional and the food was sublime. I am not much of a dessert person, but the caramel apple cheesecake was one of the nicest things I have ever eaten. I would have given it 6 stars if I could.
Amazing! They even put a birthday candle in the steak as per my special request! I was so surprised it worked. Amazing service and food. Nothing else I can ask for.

Wonderful evening to celebrate my birthday. Service was attentive but not intrusive. Tyler was very informative about the offers and made some great recommendations. We loved our dinner - tacos, salad, braised shortribs and scallops with shrimp. All great. The dessert offers were great with a genius idea "a plate of cookies" loved it. Want to go again soon.

reviews.text: After seeing our play we were meandering back to the international continental and happened in here. Boy am I glad we did. Our server, Selena was delightful and very efficient and hard-working. The food was excellent and prepared and brought us in a timely fashion. I can highly recommend this restaurant particularly if you‚Äôre fortunate to have Selena is your server. The only thing I would change would be how loud the music was

Had a business lunch here and I loved everything about the Cactus Club. When my colleague and I arrived here, we were greeted by the hostess and a waitress brought us up to the deck area where they reserved our table. It was cold the day we went and thank God they had heaters everywhere on the deck to keep us warm. Not to mention, the natural lighting that comes through the ceiling gave an overall cool and happy vibe. I ordered some truffle fries and the butternut shrimp ravioli (around $30) and would pay another visit just to eat these two dishes again. Our waitress was also very nice, she kept coming back to fill our cups with water even when it was rush hour lunch time. I‚Äôll be back!!!

Bring from British Columbia, cactus club cafe has to be my favourite. It‚Äôs given since it‚Äôs a BC family owned restaurant. 
I‚Äôd chose cactus club over any other restaurant any day. Even though I‚Äôve been there thousands of time.
I love everything about them, their food, drinks and the ambiance. 
They have super friendly staff. This particular location has three floors. Their rooftop is amazing, it‚Äôs like bar up there. Great music and great people. 
Do visit if your in downtown. It‚Äôs 5 min walk from Nathan Philip centre

The restaurant is gorgeous and upscale in the financial district of Toronto. The food was incredible and the service matched. There were plenty of options for all dietary restrictions including vegan and vegetarian. I was so pleased with my experience there, it was a perfect place to bring my mother for her birthday. I would suggest dressing up a little as most people are coming in business attire from work. And I would also suggest making a reservation because they‚Äôre often at capacity for reserved tables. The food is good value for money and they give a reusable bag and cardboard takeaway container for take away.

Staff are super attentive and friendly here. Always around to help you and refill your water, even when it's very busy (we came to watch Game 6 where the Raptors won the championships). 

Food was delicious as well. Had the Millionaire's Cut and the steak was so tender. Shrimp was well seasoned, and the mashed potatoes were smooth and creamy. Dessert was also a generous portion size and wasn't too sweet. 

A great experience overall!
My friends and I had a great time at Cactus Club's rooftop patio.  When the weather is nice, there aren't a lot of other rooftop bars to pick from in this...
Upon arriving, if you don't have a reservation they ask for your preference (indoor or rooftop) & will text you when a table becomes available. We decided...
Went to Cactus to see the raptors game. A reservation was made at 9:30pm 2 weeks prior.  We also got 2 emailed and one we confirmed via text message and...

Service here is outstanding. I really wanted to have steak, which would have been great if it wasn't overcooked. The server came over and I casually mentioned it to her; she took it immediately, apologized, confirmed my comment, and took action to rectify it.

Top-notch service. I had an amazing experience thanks to the server.
Cappuccino was wonderful, and service was excellent. I had the eggs Benedict though - just average, really underwhelming. Would have expected much more from Boulud. I didn‚Äôt even take a photo!!

Expect $100 - $150 for lunch and a couple glasses of vino. For an upscale place the seems to execute on all levels its an experience you should check out.

reviews.text:
This is a really cozy place that‚Äôs great for date nights.

The service is good. The servings are huge and the price is reasonable.

The only downside is that the food takes a long time to come out. My friends and I allocated plenty of time for dinner before an appointment, and the food took about 30 minutes to come to the table. 

Overall, I would recommend this place to people looking for a quiet, cozy place with hearty food.

I have been here for several times. I really like the environment (both inside and the patio). The used to have duck pizza, which is very tasty since you don't get a lot of dishes with duck meat. Great for small gatherings.

I love food and ambience. Two things that I didn't liked out the place was firstly there are not too many vegetarian options and secondly there was only a single waitress for around 30-40 people. So serving becomes difficult. Having said that she wasnt smiling that much or wasn't that friendly,  I guess work load.  A single üç¥üç± meal with bear might cost around 25-30 CSD

We love this place! It‚Äôs been a treat for us to go for over 8 years now. Always outstanding service and one of our favourite places to bring friends. The lighting is perfect, the size of the restaurant quaint, and Dave always knows our order. Grateful for this little gem!

A quaint and charming restaurant located downtown but hidden on a side street, allowing for a quiet place to dine. The food was very good and the prices were reasonable. The photos display the Omelette du Jour, and the Western Sandwich.
The food was amazing, my best friend took me out for a wonderful Winterlicious lunch. The restaurant was nice and cozy. It was a great experience.
Very disappointing experience tonight. My parents made Winterlicious reservations on Jan 10. Whey they called on Jan 27 to confirm, the manager had no...
Came here for a work lunch. Caf√© A Gaffe is one of the many popular restaurants on Baldwin street. Not a huge restaurant so space is definitely limited...

reviews.text: The staff were really friendly and were quick to help. The breakfast food was great and had a lot of options. I was quickly full after two plates. The one weird thing was their payment system seemed to be quite old. It turns out they don't have chip or tap available. I had to sign some paper slips which I have never encountered before.
We had a few drinks while staying at the hotel. The bartender did a great job. My wife had a hamburger and fries which was very good.
Came in for the Winterlicious. The Nicole Burger was so good! Our server was just the sweetest thing. Made our dining experience even better.

I did not have any expectations but I must say I was presently surprised. Dinner service was wonderful, the red curry was ok however the pork ribs was utterly amazing. Had their breakfast buffet and it was one of the best buffet I ever had. The choices were decent and even unique than some of most North American luxury hotel's breakfast. I think it edged out the breakfast at Fairmont Royal York even.

Stayed at the Novotel for training this past week. Ordered dinners from Cafe Nicole out of convenience and I was pleasantly surprised! Food was amazing, everything I ordered (rib dinner, chicken Caesar salad and creme brule) was amazing!  excellent customer service, which I found refreshing as it is lacking nowadays. Hotel also provided breakfast, lunch and snacks during training as it was held in one of their conference rooms. High quality meals, specifically the lunch options.

We originally were going to another restaurant with my mom to try their winterlicious menu but we had to cancel. So my girlfriend and I were still in the...

Loved the selection of food, there is something for everyone. The drink choices were really good as well, listing a number of options for wines, beers and cocktails. I ended up getting the short rib mac and cheese, which was really well done. Added a little pepper to it but otherwise really happy with it. Not a cheap restaurant but for an app, two drinks and two mains it was about $70 after tax. You do get what you paid for though.

Loved the place. Loved the food. Loved the service.our server was so attentive and knowledgeable. He gave amazing suggestions where to go and what to eat/drink in Toronto. Will be back for sure. Thank you guys
Great spot for a quick sit down lunch when you are downtown. Servers are friendly. Prices are high but food is always good.
Good food. Good service.  Great spot to go for a quick meal before the Toronto Symphony at Roy Thompson Hall

What an amazing surprise! This menu really caters to vegetarian/vegan and it's delicious. The jackfruit pulled pork was amazing and with the size of fries it was the perfect mouth feel. I asked for mustard, but would be great if they served with a bit of BBQ dipping sauce. I will go back to explore the rest of the menu.

lic_profile: An elegant French Bistro, Caren's Rosedale boasts a relaxed formal atmosphere that is as sophisticated as it is welcoming. Chef David Nang Nang delivers authentic French classics and daily specials with a Parisian flare, blending new menu items and favourites from Caren's Wine and Cheese Bar in Yorkville. The chic, contemporary setting is perfect for a romantic evening, dinner with family or a night of cocktails with friends at the bar. The open air frontage provides a patio-like feel in the warmer months while the fireplace inside is wonderful to cozy up next to in the winter. The grand piano and live music add flare and fun. Caren's Rosedale provides a multitude of experiences all under one roof and is certain to leave you with a feeling of joie de vivre!
