reviews.text: Food is decent. But the onion soup we ordered came with a disgusting elastic band. Understood it‚Äôs just an accident however seems no one‚Äôs giving any explanation until we asked for it. My friends came here before and it was nice so we decided to come again for birthday celebration. Yeah you do cancel the bill for the soup(only) but we do expect a better feedback like a word SORRY instead of making it all seems like normal. Simply ruined everything.

Second time Carens after a few years, this  place is classic and lovely. Beautifully decorated, the skylight in the area at back with fire place is just beautiful. Service is friendly, attentive but not over, just perfect. Went for a Wednesday lunch, 2 of us fish stew and mussels plus a starter and 2 glass (wine Wednesday with $5 glass) just under $120 all included. The fish stew is really good, the only thing if I would complain is there are 2-3 mussel is a bit out of taste. While it happen to mussel some time. My friend did not complain her mussel so it probably just I got a few bad ones. Will definitely order fish stew again minus mussels. 

Btw I love the outdoor sitting can‚Äôt wait summer is back.

I‚Äôm giving Carens five stars and recommend this place to anyone who has , good taste in food and appreciates value . My husband and I very much enjoy having brunch at Carens on Sunday‚Äôs.In fact ,when I compare it to a weekend brunch we had at Four Seasons ...hands down both of us agree the breakfast brunch at Carens is definitely much better. The food ,presentation and value by far make this a Five Star Rating !

I didn't get approached for about 10 minutes and in that time waiting I was overwhelmed with a smell I could only describe as sewage, emanating from what I presume was the kitchen/back of restaurant?  When I finally got my food, I ordered the French Onion soup, which was the worst I've ever tried in my life and I've tried many.  Sadly I will not be returning.

Fondue Sunday includes two different types of fondue, a classic with gruyere and a blue cheese one. Both paired with proper apple, chorizo, prosciutto and bread.  Great selection of wines. Also great personalized attention. Desert had plenty of options but we went for chocolate fondue and it did not disappoint. Definitely recommended.

reviews.text: What a nice and cozy restaurant! It is a very authentic Filipino restaurant with a great atmosphere. The service is a nice and friendly, along with the management too! The menu has lots of fantastic options for both food and drink. We had a wonderful meal with great drinks and tasty food. The portions were awesome and worth the price! You have to come here if you want to try some awesome Filipino food.

Everything you read on the reviews is TRUE!Very kind staff  & the service is on point. Wonderful menu selection & delicious menu options. Wish I ate here sooner. Verdict: Bring a friend or family member to this gem. You won't regret it.

This is your go-to Filipino restaurant. Friendly service and they are on top of your orders. Food is authentic and very well executed. Like all real Asian restaurants, there is a nice buzz of excitement (loudness) in the atmosphere. Pig trotter is a must try and we loved their coconut ginger sauce. Some dishes were a tiny bit too salty though. Will definitely go again.

It's a Philippino restaurant, I'm gluten free but there's a lot of variety that suitable for me. I was so happy n hope the other restaurants can do the same thing.

Staffs n the manager are so friendly. I recommend.

Great restaurant with very friendly staff. We were here for a birthday celebration, and they presented their food with great presentation! The kamiyan was brought out to drum beats, and they sang the birthday girl a birthday song with sparklers. The food was also amazing, with a great variety of flavours. Would definitely recommend for birthday parties!

An interesting place. The food is quite good. I always prefer good quality of wine. & This place serves the best. The staff are professional. The service is quite extraordinary.

From Cibo's industrial chic vibrant bar area to the casual Yonge Street patio, every corner turned offers a distinctly different experience. The ambience and d√©cor is nice. The staff is...
Good hip place, but service is just ok as my fiancee asked for perrier and it never came. i think it would be a short life restaurant that will stay open...

Came here for mother's day dinner. Food was ok, nothing that stood out as good or great food. Definitely not worth what they are charging.
Service was wonderful for a busy night. They made a few mistakes with our orders but they apologized profusely and took those items off the bill and offered us a free dessert. Ambiance was beautiful as well.

I have order the veal. And what i have got is fried veal socked in oil and uncooked. The rest of the table got what they ordered and it's was good but definitely way over price.
First time for me in this restaurant and definitely last. There is so many good restaurants in Toronto. Don't compromise!!!!!

I was very excited to go to Cibo for date night; however, I left quite disappointed. The portions were very small compared to other Italian restaurants in the area- my boyfriend and I had to go get food after because we were still hungry! The pasta was mediocre at best, they charge $3 for bread (what???!!!) and the wine was super expensive. Despite the disappointment with the menu, the server was prompt and friendly, made timely check ins on us and brought our food out at a decent time.
Cibo was a great date night spot. Service was attentive but not pushy.  I would recommend to friends.
Spareribs dish was good. Sauce was too salty though, but easily able to take off. Also service was inconsistent throughout the night.

lic_profile: Clay - the original restaurant collaboration between The Food Dudes and Gardiner Museum - offers elegant lunches in a breezy, breathtaking atmosphere. Shaping the Clay menu with the changing seasons in mind, Chef Bianca Azupardo imbues the restaurant with simplicity and warmth. With a focus on vegan and vegetarian-friendly options, and something on the menu for everyone, Chef Azupardo highlights locally sourced ingredients in creative easy-to-appreciate recipes. The restaurant's floor-to-ceiling windows provide stunning views of Queen's Park. Mirroring the ceramic focus of the Gardiner's collection, the interior design of Clay contributes to an inspired restaurant setting. Bathed in welcoming natural light and laid out for a comfortable dining experience, the space offers a worthy accompaniment to a day spent at the museum or shopping in Yorkville. Serving a fresh menu with a sophisticated Food Dudes twist, Clay is the perfect choice for an impeccable lunch.

reviews.text: Clay Restaurant is a fresh and modern revival of the restaurant on third floor of the Gardiner Museum, replacing "a la Carte at the Gardiner", and offers up...
Located inside of the Gardiner Museum. Very nice layout with friendly staff. Truly enjoy the atmosphere and the surrounding. If you don't mind paying a...
Delicious food, the Fish 'N Chips was the best that I ever had.  Customer Service is excellent and attentive to details of your order.  Highly recommend this place if you are in the area.

I would recommend making a reservation! The restaurant is located on the 3rd floor, the lighting in here is great. When coming here, it is super close to the subway station and if your driving you will need to park on the south side where Charles St is or you can get to the various parking garages. When entering the building, don‚Äôt wait in the line for the actual museum but just walk through and if they ask, tell them your here for Clay Restaurant. 

So let‚Äôs get started with the service. Super awesome people that work here. They greeted us and the then around with your ordering with food is in great timely fashion. The decor of this place is super modern and comforting. 

The food itself, it‚Äôs super awesome. We ordered the following:

Parsnip soup (soup of the day)
Mushroom toast (OUT OF THIS WORLD!!!)
Ricotta gnudi
Burger
Chocolate Cake

Everything we got was amazing. I highly recommend coming back and dining again!

Came back for the second time to try their new spring menu. Oh WOW! Every dish is noms.

Amazing food! Great place to hang out, floor to ceiling windows makes this place feels fresh. Bread baked in house daily. Vegan and gluten free friendly.

Lean, mean first-rate menu. Chefs are experienced. This establishment has the potential to be a landmark eatery. Inviting atmosphere and unique location. Unfortunately, we experienced a series of slights by a server:

(i) He did not describe the day's special until prompted (but did so -- unprompted -- at neighboring tables).
(ii) He spilled some water on the table (that another server had the good sense to wipe clean).
(iii) He did not provide forks for a dessert we shared. When we requested forks, he obliged us, but also stated: "Usually people eat these with their fingers -- that's why I didn't bring you any." 
(iv) He did not ask about our meal until the latter part of the meal, so I had 2/3 of my fish and chips without ketchup.
(v) He did not offer cream or milk with our teas, until prompted.
(vi) Upon our paying the bill, he maintained the iPad in his hands as we selected the tip amount. This had the effect of rushing our decision, and we observed how he would offer the iPad TO THE CUSTOMER at neighboring tables.

These inconsistencies were irritating albeit small, but in accumulation, left us distracted by the level of service. The timing was unfortunate as we were also celebrating a belated Mother's Day. We still recommend this establishment as the pros outweigh the cons by a long shot.
Just enjoyed a lovely lunch overlooking a great view of Bloor and Avenue Rd. Clay is elegant, not too pricey, great atmosphere and most of all service and food is fabulous. Will definitely be back.

Quick summary: I loved the decor of the place perfect for date nights or a classy brunch but was disappointed with my meal due to it being dry and a bit stale. However, I would definitely come back to grab a delicious cocktail or two but would probably avoid getting a steak.

Came here for Mother's day brunch(small tip: call a week or two in advance for reservations this place fills up quick.

First let me start by saying this place is beautiful the decor is clearly French cafe inspired which gives off a classic and romantic atmosphere. A perfect place for date nights or if you want to treat someone to a nice place.

The staff from our server to the hostess were pleasant and a joy to talk to. They were honest of their favourite things on the menu and were incredibly helpful when we had questions.

Unfortunately the food is where I start to take off some stars. I ordered a steak and eggs, the eggs cooked perfectly no complaints there. However, if anyone is a steak lover you know that you should not cut a steak before serving since it dries out the meat. 

On top of that the fries were definitely a bit stale. But the garlic mayo that accompanied the fries were amazing and would dip everything in it.

To end off the meal I decided to randomly try a cocktail. The cocktail was delicious and almost made me forget my disappointment in my meal.

reviews.text: I just had the most amazing experience working with Elizabeth, Janella, Chris and the entire team at Colette Gran Cafe at Holt's in Yorkdale. I decided to host my baby shower there and it did not disappoint. Leading up to the day of the event, Elizabeth was a pleasure to work with. She was kind, attentive and responded quickly to my many questions. On the day of the event, Janella and Chris met our every need. They were organized, respectful of our guests and took the utmost care to make sure everything was just as it should be. The food was absolutely spectacular (my guests are still talking about it!) and no cup of coffee was left to go cold throughout the entire event! I even noticed a member of the staff going around to tables before our guests arrived to make sure there were no marks on the silverware. It is this type of focus that really elevates a venue. The atmosphere was perfect and the attention to detail was of the highest quality. If you are looking for an intimate and beautiful location to host a special event - look no further.

If you have ever been to the Colette downtown, disclaimer it is a very different experience in the Yorkdale location. You defiantly feel like you‚Äôre in the mall so in terms of ambiance it‚Äôs not great. It‚Äôs like being in a slightly better version of the food court. The food was good though and I think for a mall this is a great place to go. We tried both versions of the high tea, I don‚Äôt think the oeelin upgrade was worth it. If you do love the experience of high tea I wouldn‚Äôt recommend this particular place just because ambiance plays a big part in the enjoyment of high tea. The food itself was good so we‚Äôll probably come back as a lunch or dinner option if we are walking around there.

(*brunch was at Colette on Wellington)Went for Sunday brunch on my birthday, and it was worth every penny! It is a bit pricey on Sundays so nice for special occasions (or if you can splurge just cause!) but the amount, quality and variety of food you get is so good! Fresh seafood, shrimp and oysters are amazing! I also had a mushroom eggs benedict, delicious! Salads, salmon wellington, etc etc and then desert!!... everything was so good...prepare for a nap after though lol...definitely worth going!

Colette was a wonderful place to host our corporate event. Beautiful ambiance and great service was what made is such a successful event! Thank you to Elizabeth who took the time to review every detail with us and ensured our event ran smoothly.

The decor, ambiance and service in Collete is superb! I loved all of the details inside! The afternoon tea however, was a grave disappointment! üòñ I was so excited to eat there and was heavily let down by the finger sandwiches. I had the smoked salmon, egg sandwich, cucumber sandwich and avocado toast... It says a lot when your avocado toast has the MOST flavour... the sandwiches were just in white bread, had little to no flavour and the ratio of filling to bread was just not what I had expected at all. I actually had to ask for salt and pepper just so I felt like I was eating more than plain bread. The desserts on top were all chocolate based (except the macarrons)... And I'm not a very big chocolate lover... but there were no other options. The scones I will say were delicious! I enjoyed and asked for more, but strawberry and marmalade are your only jam options...

Pros:
All you can eat afternoon tea
Food items were done well

Cons:
Parking at Yorkdale always tough
Not as big a tea selection as other afternoon tea...

This place is great! 
I actually found this place because I was looking for a chill place to grab drinks with a  group of friends and since a lot of us like...

This was a really unfortunate evening.  We went to celebrate my girlfriend's birthday. So we decided to check out  craft for dinner. The menu looked great. As we went in the hostess explained that they were booked starting at 6 for the Raptors play off game. We told her that was no problem. The server Kim took our drink order quickly. And the beers were brought over fast.  They were delicious.  The server then took about 25 minutes to even take our food order. In this time we watched another table have their entire meal. When we ordered an app to start and our meals. The app was brought out with the mains.  This was very disappointing. On top of this we sat with our entire meal with empty water glasses. We were not even offered any additional condiments to go with the burgers and fries that we ordered. The food was delicious. But the service was atrocious. At the end (an hour before their bookings filled up)  we were  asked if we wanted dessert or other drinks. We said that we were unsure. And the server Kim proceeded to bring us the bill.  Very disappointed by this horrible service that brought down what would have been a fantastic meal otherwise.

I've been here twice now. The beer list is great, and admittedly I haven't had food so don't take that into account.

Now, if you sit on the bar wood the service is pretty good, fairly prompt. HOWEVER, when we sat at a table the service was absolutely horrendous. 10 minute wait to be approached (due to "changing sections"). 20 minutes to get a drink. Asked for the bill and had to eventually just get up and find our server to ask again. Sadly, from other colleagues I've talked to this is par for the course.

If you're going with one or two others to sit on the bar, sure. If not, absolutely don't go here.

If you‚Äôre looking for a place to go for a drink after work or even to watch a game this is definitely a place to try. The service here is great with over 100 beers on tap so something for everybody. The food can be a little pricey but overall everything I‚Äôve tried there is good. I recommend their appetizers and the breakfast Benny was very good. Quiet on the weekends based on it being in the business district. Recommend to try it out and see for yourself.

Amazing experience here!! Food was incredibly delicious and the staff are second to none! Will come back again and again!

Manager Kevin and server Brittany (she‚Äôs new) - absolutely above and beyond! They made our night! Go...eat here. Drink here. You won‚Äôt be disappointed!

CRAFT always manages to accommodate, despite the insane rush at peak hours. Hosts are coordinated with servers and servers stay on top of each of their tables. Atmosphere is bustling but not so loud as to impair conversation and I've yet to meet a beer enthusiast who couldn't find something they like on the menu. Specials are concise and high value, and even the food is great. As a meat-free preference I find lots of options on the menu.

reviews.text:
Mano and Nick, our servers, were amazing. So attentive to detail, told us some of the history of the place, took some nice pictures for us and even surprised my Mom with a slice of cake for her belated 65th birthday and Mother‚Äôs Day. So very thoughtful and kind. 
I had read mixed reviews regarding change of ownership, quality of food, service, etc...I have to say, there was not one thing where we could find a complaint. 
Oysters, outstandingly delicious and fresh. 
Our steaks were cooked to perfection. 
The sides, perfect portion for the 2 of us. I‚Äôve never tasted more delicious, of all things, Brussels sprouts!! 
Cocktails were great as well!
Management came by to check on us...overall a great dining experience. 
We will be back. 
Thank you.

Amazing experience if you like that old steakhouse feel and look. The menu recently changed, not as many options as there used to be!!! They always have great specials. Make a reservation if you are going on the weekend and double check the hours if you are going late. 

The Calamari, grilled is amazing!!!
Caesar Salad for two, made fresh in front of you!! 
The Peppercorn steak for dinner!!!

Great wine selection as well!!!!

Went here for my boyfriend's birthday dinner and had a great time. The steakhouse is nicely furnished and wasn't too chilly inside either. I ordered the lobster pasta and a meat hoard on the side as well. Lobster pasta was great but i wish the meat board had some more bread as well. 

The mustard spread was a favourite for the meat board. My boyfriend ordered the 12oz filet mignon and it was cooked to perfection. Thanks for the delicious dinner ü•∞

Absolutely amazing from start to finish -  We take a lot of our clients here and always leave feeling full and fabulous!! 
Truly a turnaround since PnP took over and revived the venue. I definitely recommend this restaurant for any special occasion

Great experience, fantastic food and attention driven service. We‚Äôve been coming here for years and really enjoyed the recent renovations and menu changes. We had the oysters to start which were delicious and fresh. We then shared the chateaubriand which was finished off table side. A little pricey but definitely worth it for a special occasion. We will definitely be returning.

I was at David Duncan House for a staff holiday party with my company, and it was quite an enjoyable and memorable night. 

I've been to DDH on many...

Unfortunately I had to put at least a star in order post. It's really zero star. 
The worst restaurant of all time. I odered a medium well done filet...

Service by staff was great, Monday Mules are amazing.

Stopped in for lunch, beautiful interior but could use a little more light to make it pop. Good atmosphere and friendly staff. 

Chicken club arrived cold, which would have been fine if it arrived a little quicker than it did. The aloli could have used a little more seasoning and a higher quality of bacon would have been appreciated on this $16 sandwich.

Definitely will come back in the summer time when/ if the patio is opened up.
Beautiful rooftop seating. Can‚Äôt beat $1 an ounce wine! Loved the gluten free cauliflower app as well. Can‚Äôt wait to come back for a full meal.

lic_profile: Diwan's elegant interior evokes the luxury of a private Syrian home in the early 19th century.  Sumptuously decorated with wooden panels inset with mirrors, the room extends the Museum experience to diners: the panels are original and form part of the Aga Khan Museum's Permanent Collection.  Diwan's floor-to-ceiling windows offer a stunning view of the formal garden of the Aga Khan Park designed by Lebanon-based landscape architect Vladimir Djurovic, who visited the world's historic Islamic gardens for inspiration.

Master Chef Mark McEwan and Chef de Cuisine John Kovac offer a menu that highlights flavours and fragrances from the Middle East, North Africa and the Indian subcontinent. Prepared with local and international ingredients, the menu celebrates the many textures and flavours of traditional cuisine with unexpected twists on spicy and savoury dishes.

reviews.text: The food was very good. I started with carrot soup and then had Butter chicken with a side of saffron potatoes. The saffron potatoes were exceptional and everything else was very good. The service was attentive without being annoying and my server was super helpful.

Lovely place to meet for lunch. They have lovely wines by the glass we started sharing the sizzling tickka shrimp it was really sizzling when it arrived @ the table delicious. I then had 12hr braised pie short ribs really nice & tender. My friend had whole Mediterranean sea bass she really enjoyed it. I had honey moon dessert with a cappuccino. Everything was wonderful it was not to noisy so we could talk. 1st time there would return many interesting choises on the menu.

Beautiful setting and great atmosphere on Valentine's day. Live clarinet player and a huge 5 course meal was great value. The dishes were very unique and the braised lamb shank was outstanding. However the swordfish skewer as part of the salad was under cooked.

Dining at Diwan was a great experience and restaurant's 300-400 years old decorative artwork and middle eastern music makes it so unique. Food is definitely what you would expect from the best in Toronto. Items in the menu are specifically designed to go with the theme of the Museum and the temporary exhibitions. In our case, menu was inspired by the Emperors & Jewels temporary exhibition. Starter, main course and desert were all really tasty and great. Make sure to spend the day at the Museum to not only try Diwan but enjoy the permanent collection and temporary Exhibitions.

A beautiful place to spend time with your family, friends or that special person. The food is top notch, service is professional, and the atmosphere is serene. Highly recommended. I can‚Äôt wait to dine here again.

Really impressed!

reviews.text: Our server was extremely friendly and knew exactly what to recommend based on our preferences. Everything he recommended, we loved! The restaurant is beautiful and the food is delicious and full of flavour. I would definitely recommend going there for a special occasion or date night.

Great ambiance!  I took out a group for business dinner here, and we all enjoyed the food.  The food price is decent for the quality.  Service is good too but our server was clearly split thin as the night got busy.  Overall, a good experience.

Even thought I was here for business dinner, based on what I noticed seems great for couples, date night dinner as well.

Very stylish place as expected. Nice environment for some good conversation with few glasses of wine. Food was so so. My order of veal came with 2 piece of meat. One was over cooked a bit. The greens were also a bit too well done.

Great Greek food experience right in the heart of downtown Toronto.  Not terribly pricey either, but if you hit the wine and somewhat exotic (but awesome) beer selections they offer you'll reach your dining out budget cap quickly.  
I attended a corporate event with about 20 people and the service was very slow that evening even though the restaurant wasn't that busy.  My waiter missed an offered refill that night, but the food was amazing and cooked perfectly - so it was almost worth the wait.  I definitely would go again to give them another chance at better service.
Fantastic food and wine. Good for a business lunch or a catch up dinner. Do the calamari!  Great service and greater food.

Don't they realize, gratuity is at the diner's discretion especially when we were a group of four (two adults and two kids). Fail.

reviews.text: We enjoyed an excellent brunch at Fabbrica yesterday with a group of 8 friends.  Besides good environment, good food, we really enjoyed our waiter Robin, he is a breath of fresh air.  Next time we will ask for him specifically!

Food was good. Service started badly. Server seemed to have forgotten our drink order, had to be reminded.  Service was better after shift change. Would go back for food, hope for better service next time.
I love this restaurant. Semi-formal, laid back but very professional. One of my favorite places for a hearty Italian meal. Definitely recommend.

The restaurant had a nice atmosphere but for the price we were disappointed with the food.  I had the Bolognese, it was good but for the price I expected the pasta, the tomato sauce and the basil to taste more fresh and be more flavorful.  They also had veal parmigiana but it only came with 2 pieces of veal instead of the regular veal and pasta, for $30 you wouldn't expect to have to order a side separately.  It was good but too pricey for what it was.

My husband and I dine at Fabbrica very often as it is one of our favourite restaurants. The food is delicious and authentic, the vibe is modern yet classic and the staff is very friendly and approachable. I also had my bridal shower at the restaurant which was a very memorable experience. We highly recommend this restaurant!

reviews.text: Excellent service from friendly staff. The atmosphere is upscale yet laid back. The food is delicious and flavourful. Some unique twists on traditional foods such as quail eggs on breakfast pizza from a wood-fire oven. The coffee was great as well, though the real star here is the food. Toilet paper is above average, it is 2 ply, and of reasonable softness, better than mall or store quality, there was no roughness to be found here.

Food is always good but service is always lacking. Been here 4 times and three out of four times, service was extremely lacking.

When entrees came out, no wine or water was topped up, no fresh pepper or parmesan offered, cutlery was just being landed, and no one came to check up until we called our server over. 

It's really disappointing because I keep wanting to give Figo another chance but I think this is it. I'm not sure if it's because we are all dressed casually that we are not getting attention - the one time we got good service was when I came after work in work attire.

Beautiful interiors and ambiance. We had dinner here and if you‚Äôre here for photos I‚Äôd suggest going during lunch or brunch, as the lighting at night is very dimly lit. 

We ordered a variety of appetizers, pizza and main. Our favourite was the fried zucchini, calamari and Margarita pizza. The seafood pasta was good but could use a bit more seasoning. Everything was decent but nothing extraordinary. They do also have a fun cocktail and drinks menu. 

Service was what we‚Äôd expected and overall it was a good environment for friends gathering and cute interiors.

Loved this place, so classy and so pretty. I loved the food and service, although wished they had served pasta for lunch. That was kind of a bummer since I‚Äôd gone mainly to have pasta ! But definitely a sweet spot !

Just had our fourth memorable meal at Figo. We love the casual, airy decor but it's the food that really keeps us going back. The heirloom tomato dish is one of the best starters in town. My partner has had both the striploin and the short ribs; both are delicious and I would happily have eaten a whole bowl of the zucchini side that came with the ribs. I sometimes shy away from ordering fish because it can be tasteless, but Figo cooks and seasons it perfectly. The total bill usually comes to around $130, including a shared app, drink each, two entrees and two desserts, which is what we expect to pay for a thoughtfully prepared meal in a casual, upscale place. We live in the West end of Toronto and there are tons of great restaurants nearby. But we'll happily hop on the streetcar again soon to eat at Figo!

Excellent service, great pizzas and a fair price. Will definitely come back.

Central location, very well decorated, makes a mean fizz, great for eating...
Such a beautiful spot! My friend and I went for an early brunch on a Saturday morning. We reservations so we didn't wait at all. The interior is stunning....

Unfortunately I had to return to Figo for another friend's birthday. But I kept an open mind!

Chef Vito Rizzuto and David Brace combine their years of experience to capture the essence of simplicity with flair.

reviews.text:
The Italian restaurants around the area tend to be hit or miss, depending on if they cater to families or go for high quality, I have found Five Doors North to be a great in-between. The atmosphere is very relaxed and open, with gentle lighting and casual seating. The food was very good, and the prices were very reasonable. 

Service was somewhat slow but that was okay as there was a large group in our area and the staff were very friendly. The bathrooms however were very small. 

Overall I was very happy and I will certainly be back in the future.

The drinks were good too.
The place has a bit of echoes especially near the back of the dinning room.
There is a nice selection of alcohol at the bar.
Loved our experience! Staff were knowledgeable, attentive and sooooo nice! Food was amazing would absolutely go back!
Staffs are very friendly! Food is great! I like their pasta and risotto.

reviews.text:
I'm debating my review for a long time. I haven't been this disappointed at a restaurant in a long time. The reviews were good and I was expecting a different experience.

They didn't have 3 dishes available, which is hard with a small menu. One of the dishes was the dish they're well known for, the octopus. They didn't tell me until after the order was placed so there really wasn't anything else I wanted to eat. I ended up get the grilled sardines instead which were just salted and grilled. Really boring and overcooked. I'm fine with a simple dish but then it's really got to be good.

We got a soup and burrata for appetizers, and a chocolate cake for dessert. All of which were average, nothing special.

The only saving grace for this restaurant was the rabbit pasta. The sauce was really delicious and rich. Sadly my husband also got 3 bones in his pasta.

The place was completely empty during our visit at lunch, I think that's says a lot... I wouldn't go back and I wouldn't recommend it.. sadly.

Overall the experience was lovely, decor great. The reason why I removed one star is because my meal , braised beef rib was as tough as shoe leather. A great disappointment. The restaurant did not charge me for it, but still unfortunate to look forward to dining in a place like this and be served something not remotely chewable. The 3 other guests in my party did enjoy their meals.

I went to Winterlicious 2019, it was my first time at the restaurant and I loved it. The food is so delicious and the staff is amazing. The place is cozy and comfy. I had an amazing time there. It is perfect to celebrate a special occasion like a wedding anniversary.

I have no regrets and I will come back again some time.

This restaurant provides a fantastic cozy atmosphere along with delicious food. The staff were very polite and the owner walked and talked to every table i could see. True professionalism!!

There's definitely a lot of pride with this place.  The food was great and the presentation was incredible. 

I will return!
First time there and we only had apps, they were fantastic and the atmosphere was intimate and chic. I will be coming back for mains. Great for date night

I think this experience with my beau has cemented this place as one of our favourite restaurants for more formal couple dinner dates.

Location: 4.5/5

perfect for a date
food was delicious and the venue is cute and quite
I'm surprised not many people know about this place

reviews.text:
You can reserve the first seating of weekend brunch at 10am. There are 5 bar type of spots you can grab otherwise or wait at about 1045am.

It's all fresh local and the menu changes depending on the ingredients they get. It's the basics but well done. It's simple and tastes good because all the ingredients are all excellent.
Great food. Excellent service. Our waiter was great...busy night he was by himself and never missed a beat.

I have dinned here on numerous occasions and have always had very friendly and attentive staff and delicious food. This particular visit they were also very accommodating to my mom and I as I brought my infant son with us in a stroller. WI'll definitely go back with my son again!

Amazing place, small and very romantic, the food is delicious and the service is excellent. Good prices for the food & drinks and the size of the dishes is very generous.

Fully recommended to have a romantic dinner or chill with the friends, you can park your car on the street without any problem

Also ask got the zuppa of the day!

Great atmosphere with a good selection of Italian dishes. Between me and my friend we tried 2 of their salads, pasta carbonara, and gnocchi. The portions are really big, so we had no space left for desserts. Food was really yummy. Both main courses were a bit too salty though (and normally I love salty food, but even for me it was too much). So maybe ask for less salt when placing an order. Staff is extremely friendly, so I am sure they will be happy to accommodate

reviews.text: Great place! Awesome food and awesome story. Would definitely recommend the chicken tacos and guacamole. The churro was a great finish! The Lola margarita was also a nice change from a classic!
Amazing food and even better service! Ernesto was enthusiastic, warm and passionate for what he does.Would have rated this 10/5 stars if possible.

FondaLola is one of the unique restaurant I've visited in Toronto and known for having such a beautiful cozy backyard patio. 

Stepping into FondaLola feels like a trip to Mexico due to their beautiful 
 rustic materials, painted ceramics and treasures brought from Mexico.

Staff are very welcoming, attentive, and excellent service. And the food are exquisite. We came early for dinner time and ordered homemade tacos, traditional Mole, delicious guacamole and few cocktails. 

Definitely one beautiful restaurant to dine in and experience the relaxation from the city- especially when your visiting Toronto.

While the food here tasted quite good, the portions seemed mediocre. Some of the tacos were essentially meet and some cilantro. While I appreciate the simplicity of this, more flavor and more toppings were required... especially for the price.

The service was okay, though it was eerily quiet the Saturday night I dined. 

There are much better Mexican restaurants in Toronto.

Loved the tequila! The margaritas were good but i would have loved a frozen margarita! The fish tacos were delicious.  The guacamole and nachos were great but the portion was not very big. The atmosphere and the customer service were great!

So the hottest waiter with all silver head and bodacious lips and a mean Hispanic accent works at this joint :-D 

Ok back to the service..

This is an absolute delicious restaurant. @fondalola specializes in Mexican food. Therefore, if you want authentic Mexican food in Toronto this is the place...

reviews.text: Came here after a concert. Food was fantastic. I had the Mexican pizza. Owner was really nice, came over and checked on us, chatted with us about our night and even sent over some complimentary shots. Nice little spot and reasonable pricing. Will definitely be back next time I'm in Toronto.

Food was good, service was good, atmosphere/patio good, beer list was terrible. I know it's not supposed to be a beer place, but it's downtown Toronto in 2019, there should be at least one or two rotating taps with local breweries on. Nothing really stood out about this place unfortunately, definitely nothing I'd list as great. They did seem to have a few decent cocktail deals, but again, nothing too special. Don't get me wrong, I would go back because it's only a few minute walk away. But definitely not somewhere you need to seek out if your not living really close by.

The food was mediocre(had chicken fajitas, nachos, and wings). The fajitas are served with six small soft tortillas which doesn't make a lot of sense to me for a couple of reasons. It is sold as a main course but comes with six tortillas which would seem a better fit for the starter menu. My main issue is that the fajitas are very saucy so it is impossible to put one together and hold anything in place. This is where a full size tortilla would work much better.

reviews.text: Visited here on Sunday for a late dinner and was surprised by how amazing the food was. Was not expecting it to be such a quiet yet unique restaurant but it was. The garlic shrimp and angel hair marinara was perfection and the 6-hr roast brisket was honestly the best I've had. Told our server that we would definitely be back again!

Location: Close to all theatres and concert halls. Pay parking in the area.
Service: Very good and attentive service. If you have the show to catch, the staff always makes sure to time food service properly.
Food: Good food, but not fantastic. Generally fits the price tag. From favourites: lobster bisque and escargots. Selection of pastas and steaks are good, but nothing special. Portions are big. Desserts are ok too.

Conclusion: We stop by from time to time before the show to enjoy our favourite dishes. Would recommend as a casual place to eat from time to time.

This long time restaurant serves as a good venue for theatre goers to enjoy a decent meal before the show. 

The quality of the food is good. The price is higher than what you are getting in terms of quality but that is attributable to its proximity to the theatre. 

The greeter is generally friendly. The table service is acceptable but just that. 

The atmosphere is good without being too loud in the primary dining room.
Very good food.  I love the lunch specials here.  Try the lobster and crab soup!

Amazingly quick service if you're going to a show.  The lobster and crab soup is amazing with the pastry on top.  New York Steak with peppercorn sauce is delicious.  Two course dinner is a great deal.

reviews.text: The decor is beautiful and I really like that it is organized as smaller rooms as it makes the experience more intimate.  I did not like that no one informed me of the Mother's Day pricing, so it was a bit of a surprise when I got the bill.  Considering I called 3 times prior to the visit it would have been nice to know that was $15 more per person.  The tea itself became too strong too fast.  The food was average.  Not my favourite high tea experience, but still enjoyable for the moms, which is what truly mattered.

Windsor Arms afternoon tea is the best in the city in terms of the food. The sandwiches, sweets and scones are always fresh and incredibly tasty - 5/5.  Service is okay - 4/5.  If you prefer,you can pick up the afternoon tea to go. As a side note, the correct term is "afternoon tea" and not "high tea".

Stopped by for a colleague's birthday celebration. The initial thoughts after entering was that the surroundings looked and felt dingy. U could see obvious dust build-up all around. Service and food (bar) were horrible. I sat there and waited to be acknowledged. Still was told to wait, without being offered a menu to peruse in the meanwhile. Ordered the bison burger with sweet potato fries. Fries came soggy af and dripping with oil. Burger patty tasted like it has been frozen for decades. Would not recommend.

Afternoon tea previously has been such a treat to indulge in with my daughter on Mother‚Äôs Day. Unfortunately, this year the Windsor Arms was disappointing for several reasons. It felt like being on an assembly line and being in a mechanized cash grab of a day and given the sharp increase in pricing for Mother‚Äôs Day service, one would hope they could maintain the high level of service befitting a five star hotel. The service was cold and impersonal and there was little attention paid to us as customers. The food was stale and a step down from previous years. Their afternoon tea service used to be the best in the city. Can‚Äôt say I would ever return for tea. Definitely put a bit of a damper on a special day.

Previously had brunch and high tea at Windsor Arms Hotel. Brunch was great! It was buffet style, with delicious items to choose from. For high tea, there were interesting tea selections, and filling tea sandwiches. I was able to have opt for dairy free food items, which was very pleasing. Glamorous decor. Highly recommend!

reviews.text:
Came here with my family and our server (Ali) was really unfriendly. He seemed really impatient, even though we asked 2 questions when deciding what to order! My sister asked if one of the dishes was vegetarian, which was met with a really rude and sarcastic remark. My mom asked if the dish she wanted was very spicy and could be modified - again, was responded to in a very rude manner. I usually don't care about service as long as the food is good, but this really was a stand-out experience in terms of rude service. The waiter was so impatient, rude and seemed like he wanted us out of there. If you hate your job THAT much, quit - or at least, don't work with people! I was taken aback at how rudely he was talking to us...

On the plus side, food was AMAZING. Best butter chicken I've ever had. Biryani was too spicy for me (but that's personal taste). 

5/5 for food, 1/5 for service

The food was good. 

The service was mediocre at best. We were a group of 5 and ordered individual items. My Friend asked for separate bills and the server said "its very hard" why don't you calculate and i will charge separately. I checked the bill and it wasn't our bill to begin with. Then I insisted that we need separate bill and server said "I will have to do it 6 (counting my 3 yrs old which i mentioned will not be paying his own bill) times, its will take very long for me", I said that is fine, we can wait. He came back with the bills, handed me the bundle and said "now you can sort it out who's bill is which"... I mean are you serious? you are the one who took our orders and should know who ordered what. 

Anyways, then he charge an extra $10 on the credit card, I checked and pointed that out and he sounded irritated, did another transaction, again, wrong amount, no apologies, but even more irritated reaction by him .

Long story short, you cannot charge me 18% gratuity (yes it came in the bill) for such bad service. This is the very reason tip is based on customer's discretion and experience.

It isn't that often that I am impressed by an Asian restaurant, but I was. The washroom were clean, the floor & seats didn't have food on them - my pet peeve! The decor & ambiance was lovely. The service was good, but the food was fabulous! The combinations of ingredients & flavours were yummy. Reusable straws! I was very disappointed that they didn't have the tamarind cake even though it was on the menu at the restaurant. The online menu was a little different also.
Can't say enough  good things. Friendly service, great ambiance and the food is absolutely delicious!  Did I say absolutely delicious! Guarantee you will enjoy!
Impressive decor + great food + excellent service. Loved every part of my lunch 2 course meal. I will be back to try dinner

reviews.text: A cozy place downtown with a cool vibe close to the fashion district. The food was good here their cornbread was delicious.  Jodi and Shaky provided excellent service. They have jazz music on Mon. nights Wed. reggae night, Fri. local music and on sat a Live DJ on site. A great place to have a quick meal with a view.

Place has a cool vibe, nice dining atmosphere. Kinda like a comfortable garage. Service depends on server. Ours had two people, one table, one order for beer to start. She forgot. Placed an order for warm and cold appetizers to be brought to table as ready. She blamed kitchen for timing order wrong. By now, main food would have to be delicious to curb our building sour appetites. Unfortunately, food is prepared like someone in the kitchen forgot they're open and rushed cook time. Recommended if you're neither hungry nor thirsty.

We went here for dinner, was seated quickly and served tasty tasty food.
The place has a great vibe right down to their vinyl-like menus.
I ordered the Cajun fried okra and Caribbean curried veg stew. Both were super flavourful and made vegan. The one thing that was a little concerning; I asked for vegan meals and while the base was, I was still served creamy coleslaw and dipping sauces that were not vegan friendly. Lucky for us, my husband loves slaw, but a lot of food still went to waste.
If someone asks for vegan, it should all be vegan. 
Other than that, the curry was super yummy and their hot sauce has a great tang to it. We‚Äôll be going again on a music night for sure.
One of my favourite brunch spots. The smoked salmon benny is amazing. I see some negative comments on the service, but I've never had any issues.

reviews.text: It's a tiny, cozy place that serves simple but amazingly testy food. I asked for a steak done rare. I got a tender, tasty piece of almost raw yet warm meat. Delicious! The wine they serve is local, i.e from the Niagara region, which isn't my favourite, so it could be better for me.

Absolutely lovely service and delicious food. It's nice knowing you're supporting a pro-learning environment and sustainability efforts. Everyone seemed to be enjoying themselves (staff included). Will definitely be back. Thank you for a lovely time!

I was pleasantly surprised.  Wasn't planning on eating here but stopped in due to some changes in plan.  Glad I did!

I had the turkey sandwich with fries.  The sandwich was big and filling.  The fries thick and well salted.  Overall I was happy with my meal.

My partner had the tofu flatbread.  He really enjoyed his meal as well.

Wines were good, food was not. My croquet appetizer was cold in the middle. My main course vegetables were hard and not blanched correctly. My dessert bread pudding was hard and not at all moist. The saving grace was my meat which was cooked perfectly and just fell apart.

Very comfortable and smooth experience. Perfect if you want to stay in the area. The cafe/bar has good food and great daily food and drink specials. A definite diamond in the rough.
Unique hotel design. It was very reasonably priced. The room was clean and we'll designed.

The bathroom door couldn‚Äôt fully close which was fine while I was staying alone but if I was not, it would be awkward. Bed was comfortable, room was very clean and nice. The walls between bathrooms are awkwardly thin, could hear the person next to me as if that bathroom was a part of this unit.

There is a smell in my room which reminds me of a funeral home. I mentioned it to the older guy at the front desk and he laughed at me and assured me noone had died in there recently..... As if things could not get worse, there was a party or wedding or something which kept me awake till almost 1 o'clock in the morning. When I got up to check the "continental breakfast", it consisted of cereal, milk, coffee and what I can only assume was orange juice (looked more like egg nog). That is not worth 5$ in my opinion. All the warning signs were there, but I still decided to eat a snack the next day. The "sliders" were more like garlic and ground meat slapped together and cooked. Although they tasty, they were way too heavy on the garlic. I ended up being sick the day, which I attribute to the sliders or some combination of what I ate and drank at the hotel. My martini glass was dirty, the ketchup bottle had ketchup all over the side, the list goes on. To make matters worse, I had to go up to the bar and ask for a glass of water, then I had to go up to order my beverage, again to order my food, and lastly to pay my bill even though they have handheld machines. By the way, I was the only person in the restaurant... The lack of service and quality at this place is astonishing. I am surprised they are still in business. I will not be returning.

reviews.text: Haven't been here for a while but the food was just as good as I remember it. Had some pasta, pizza and even a vegan dish - all were really good. Even the leftovers the next day! They make feel welcomed and take really are of you and you can see it from the vibe and regulars that keep coming back. Love this place!

My boss is a regular in here. We were having casual late lunch meeting. And the server had been back and forth waiting to take the order. But we were focusing on talking, rather than checking on the menu. They never gave up on coming back. Even after the food came, they kept on asking if the food was fine, if we need to refill drinks, etc. Excellent customer service! They have vegan dishes. I admire their salad. Definitely will go back.

I had previously dined at the King St. location and had great customer service, so I was expecting the same here. Nope. 
Came here during a lunch period and it wasn't too busy. The staff were not attentive to us but looked after others with care, it took forever to even receive water, and to have it refilled. I don't think it's asking for much to receive equal attention.
We ordered the calamari, which was straight from the freezer and the batter was not good at all, it was even uncooked in some parts.
Pasta and pizza were alright, you can't really mess those up.
The new plant base menu is delicious , I am glad that I have the option to come here now. Service excellent.  I am coming back for sure .

Great atmosphere. There was a large choice of food options including gluten free for our group of 25. Service was very good. Food was delivered on time and there was no mix up with anyone's order.  Likewise when it came to paying our bills. Our server was professional and efficient. There were 4 birthdays celebrations in the restaurant last night and each time, everybody joined in with the singing.

reviews.text: Went here for my birthday. The pasta was average. Not bad but could be better. The ambiance is nice especially after a tiring round of shopping in Yorkdale Shopping Centre since it's within the mall. Their drink menu is better than their food which is nice. Our server was very polite and attentive as well. I would go back!

This is a fantastic spot to have a meal if you are at Yorkdale. Spacious and you can make reservations. It is accessible with a handicap bathroom on the first floor which is great. Also they do a great job for food sensitivities, I've brought friends here who cannot have gluten or nuts. It's always been easy to accommodate groups here. I like the salads but the pizza and pasta are popular. This place is great if you are at the mall.

I have been here several times and each time never been disappointed with the quality of food and service. 

All the staff I have encountered have been patient, kind and charismatic. And not the awkward kind of charisma! They are always informative whenever I or friends/family that I take with me have questions.

I can tell the food is cooked to a high standard and the setting of each plate really adds to the initial wow feeling you get when you receive your food.

I would definitely recommend this place whether you are looking for a longer sit down experience or even just a quick drop in and out.
The food is epic. We loved everything we ate. Great service and nice atmosphere. Server had British accent which was lovely. Wow mind blowing food and desserts.

Small portions, indifferent quality ingredients, bland flavors. Not bad, not good. I'd give it three stars if the prices didn't make me feel like I'd been robbed.

reviews.text: Terrible sight line unless you are dead centre on the stage. Drinks too expensive.  Not my favourite venue. Only reason it gets any stars is the sound system seemed decent.

For being an upscale jazz club and for how much you pay, I was definitely expecting better food and service. There are definitely better jazz clubs in Toronto.

Completely just stumbled onto this place looking for a nice place to grab late night drinks. We didn‚Äôt know they had cover so bring $20 with you if you do plan on coming. The staff are super friendly and welcomed us in knowing we aren‚Äôt huge jazz fans. 

Not a huge jazz fan and never actually been to a jazz bistro. However, I have to say this was definitely one of the most memorable nights. Super cool ambience and the Steve Koven Trio put on a lasting performance.

Food was also filling, we got the vegan and seafood boards. Both birds had a good selection of different foods to try. The drinks are also a lot stronger then expected (that‚Äôs a good thing ;)

Overall great night and will be remembered!

I was pretty much under dressed but still I had the best service from the hostess, the server, and everyone. I'd definitely go back. Good execution of French Bistro staples, lovely location and beautiful room and patio. Wine selection is good but leans toward the showy and expensive and misses the good middle range French offerings.  
If you are very picky about the food I would rate this as equivalent to a local bistro in Montreal and second to Le Select for Toronto.

I normally never write reviews, but my experience last night left a bitter taste in my mouth.

I had ordered a glass of wine for a nightcap at the bar. When I received my glass, I saw that the glass was dirty with remaining lipstick marks on the rim. No big deal, so I simply relayed this to the bartender with "Hi, I noticed the glass is dirty. May I please have another one instead." To which, the bartender snatched the glass from me, turned and slammed it on the back counter.

I was stunned that this was her reaction. No apology and the attitude?!

To my horror, she then proceeded to try to transfer the wine content from the dirty cup to a new cup. Gross! At which point, I motioned for her to stop and said "nooo". This caused more fury from her - more slamming, dirty looks - to the point that when I received my new glass, there were wine drops dropping down the side from her aggressiveness...

La Societe, is this the type of experience and service you want your customers to experience? Do you think this was professional of your staff at all?

This is a great location with the style and atmosphere of a French cafe. The food is generally very good and I've enjoyed the two meals I've had there but the service is a bit lacking. Both times have been for lunch and the restaurant is never full but the food does take a while to come out, which is why I dropped a star. I would still recommend the place and will most likely be back again, if in the neighborhood (visiting the ROM).

lic_profile: Praised as one of the "Ten Chefs of the Millennium" in 2000 by food & Wine magazine, Susur Lee is still at the top of his game.  Between helming three restaurants in Toronto - Lee, Lee Kitchen & Kid Lee - and overseeing his prestigious TungLok Heen in Singapore, Chef Lee makes numerous television appearances and travels the globe as guest chef and consultant.  Balancing the epicurean traditions of China with the classical techniques of French cuisines, Chef Lee improvises a daring and original culinary aesthetic. Frequently appearing many of Toronto publication's "Best of" lists, Lee offers a menu inspired by the convergence of land and sea with seasonality in mind.  From the bar comes a sake driven wine list and fresh-to-order cocktails with handmade ingredients.

reviews.text: This is THE best restaurant I've ever eaten at. Every time I am in TO, I hit Lee's up for their amazing coleslaw and amazing gluten free vegan options. The only problem is trying to get a reservation because it's always busy.

This restaurant is overrated and not worth the price. We got the tasting menu (mine was vegetarian), and the goat cheese tart was way too sweet (marmalade overpowered all the other flavours) and so was the palette cleanser (felt like eating a spoon of raw sugar - the server even asked me if I wasn't eating it because it was too sweet and that they hear this from customers a lot!). I got the vegetarian spring roll and my friend got the cheeseburger one. Hers came in a nice bowl on a pedestal, easily accessible. Mine came in a caged dish with handles over it on four sides. The chef recommends eating it with the lettuce wrap - how are you supposed to put your hands through the handles to eat the springroll, while the sauce is dripping down your fingers and you're trying to hold it over the plate within the cage??? Too bad there was a lack of thought in the execution since this item was actually delicious. A simple plate would have been fine. The sauce with the asparagus was very salty. Overall, the presentation of the vegetarian dishes was not as well done as the meat dishes. The staff were friendly and knowledgeable, but the flavours and presentation could be improved. I would not recommend coming here.

Great restaurant. It was busy and getting reservations was not fun but the atmosphere made up for it. The server was very knowledgeable and knew the menu like the back of her hand. The menu is limited in options but the food is good. Singapore slaw is probably the best item on the menu. It‚Äôs a must. cheeseburger spring rolls were great! The award winning roasted chicken should not have won any awards. It was not good. Would eat here again.

Overall average experience. I definitely expected much more based on my friend's exaggerated recommendation. The prices of the dishes are not proportional to the quality of the food. Nothing mind-blowing or memorable. The crispy salad was yummy but still somewhat expensive for what you get. Not an every day spot but may be worth visiting if you're already in the area (don't go out of your way).

I didn‚Äôt find this restaurant memorable in any way ‚Äì neither ambience nor food and wouldn‚Äôt come again.  The seating is not good. The tables are very close together, small and without tablecloths.  The restaurant is very busy and loud so it‚Äôs not great for a romantic night out.  I had the Singapore slaw, it was different but not so memorable that I would want to try it again. The rest of the meal was nothing special. For dessert I had the signature French and Chinese Tong Yuen. Interesting presentation but left a too-sweet aftertaste that lingered and was unpleasant.  Service is fine and efficient but gives the impression of an assembly line.  The servers rattle off ALL of the ingredients in the slaw and repeat it at every table around you.  Maybe this place is good for a casual drink with friends on the outside patio.

reviews.text: Stumbled upon this place while walking around and the entrance was inviting so we went in. We had a large group but the staff were very accommodating and quick to make a table for us all. Staff suggested fantastic drinks and the food was delicious. We ordered a wide variety of dishes and all were devoured. The decor of the place is very cool too with windows to the beer making area on the way to the washroom. Will for sure be back

Went for brunch. This was my first time here and the thing I noticed right away was that even though the dining room is downstairs, the area is very bright with natural light.
I got the carrot cake pancakes and they were ok. They had a much smokier flavour than I was expecting, to the point of them tasting like nothing but mesquite smoke. The portion size was perfect, I wouldn‚Äôt have been able to eat anymore smoke-flavoured breakfast food. 
My friends all seemed pleased with their choices.
I like the old school feel downstairs. Seems to have some old building artifacts built in to the decor, very cool. Staff was very attentive and accommodating. Very easy place to hang out and relax.
Great place. Their late night specials are spectacular. Their $4.50 beer after $10 is what, brings me back. Also highly suggest the pretzel. Quiet place, great patio.
Great food, friendly staff. Do a great four trio beer 6 oz each for $10. Yummy soft serve ice cream cone with UK Cadbury flake chocolate. Meet dietary restrictions.
Great spot in liberty village if you're looking for great beer and delicious food. Came here for a Raptors vs bucks playoff game and was really surprised to...

reviews.text:
Got the all you can eat seafood menu.

Pros:
‚Ä¢ Most of the seafood served was absolutely delicious. You can instantly taste how fresh and thoroughly done the food was.
‚Ä¢ The lady serving us was a gem. Very attentive, always smiling, and served us as fast as she could.
‚Ä¢ A live jazz band generated a vibrant atmosphere around the place.
‚Ä¢ Honestly thought the price was very fair for the quality and quantities served.
‚Ä¢ Very neat inner decor.

Cons:
‚Ä¢ The food could take some time to get to the table, but that's because of it's freshness.
‚Ä¢ Thought the lighting in the place was way too dim.

All in all though, I really liked my experience. Will definitely come here again sometime in the future!

Nice ambiance and music. Decent food and wine. Excellent service. We had the Fish Rodizio which we could not finish as we ordered appetizers too so will not do that again. Unfortunately, we could not take any home so it was such a waste.

Best seafood that we have ever had. Highly, highly recommended. The all you can eat fish was excellent too and more than anybody could finish. The host is wonderful and genuinely cares. Reservations are required especially on Saturday nights. Make a plan to try this place, you will not regret it.
Amazing place. Great food, great vibe and awesome live entertainment Brigido! Can't wait to come back again! Highly recommended!! ‚ù§Ô∏è

reviews.text: We loved this restaurant.  We found it by accident as several trendy restaurants had no availability and this restaurant did.  It was a treasure to find.  We loved the service, the restaurant was sparkling clean and the food was excellent.  We will definitely be returning!

Came here to have some drinks at the bar. My boyfriend asked the bartender for some shots of tequila and the bartender said "this tequila is expensive." The group of people I was with and I were all annoyed by the comment because we felt he said that because of our skin colour. (Brown) We spent over $100 on drinks and so my boyfriend paid and gave $5 tip because he felt that the bartender didn't deserve a better tip because of his attitude. After, my boyfriend asked the bartender for a napkin and the bartender told him he could wait and mentioned how my boyfriend only gave a $5 tip. My boyfriend was irritated but proceeded to wait for the napkin. I was sitting at another part of the bar and the bartender came by and said idiot under his breath, aimed at my boyfriend. We believe this establishment is racist. We will not be coming back here ever again. I suggest you find somewhere else for drinks.

Nice Italian restaurant offering traditional fare with a slight twist.  If you enjoy seafood it a great place to get fresh fish that is well prepared.  Decor is elegant/chic and it has the service to match.  Enjoyed the meal and would go again.

This little spot is kind of hidden  but that's more the natural order of 100 king office workers looking south vs north; probably due to magnetic field anomalies. 

Regardless we had a really cute and funky waitress who served us delicious Italian food. 

The bacon wrapped dates and seabass were amazing. 

As far as the atmosphere is concerned, this is a good location if you want to have a conversation as the soft walls dampen sounds and that important if you're trying to convince a customer to give you lots and lots of bucks.
A wonderful restaurant with amazing food. The servers were delightful and kept in check with us throughout our stay. I'd definitely visit again.
Lovely Italian restaurant in downtown Toronto near the Hilton and Sheraton hotels.  We come here for dinner when we are staying at either of these places...
I'm honestly so ashamed to admit that I've lived down the street from Little Anthony's for 6 years and never gave a second thought to it. I finally went...

I was invited to a business dinner here with 5 others, and we were treated to excellent service, beautiful decor and great food. 

We were there for 4 hours...

reviews.text: This was a great dining experience. The vibe is very relaxed, and the service attentive. The cocktails are well made and the wine list well chosen. We loved the variety on the menu, and having been to Italy seeking the best food, this was a great find. The grilled octopus was amazing, as were the two pastas we tried, and my pizza. Dessert was also too good for my own good. GREAT coffee to end the meal Loved everything about this place!

Kale salad and beef tenderloin were great.  Gnocchi was pretty tasteless.  I'd give the food 3.5 stars overall.  What's bringing down my review is the quality of the service and cocktails.  It is a wine bar, so can't be too judgy about the cocktails, but service was super slow, and unprofessional for a place with a fairly high price point.  So many other great restaurants in the city so probably won't be returning.

Great food, but service could be a bit better. We were told that we had to vacate the table by a certain time which we totally understand. But if this is the case food service should be faster. We noticed the next guests/reservation actually come in and it made us uncomfortable since it wasn't our fault.

This place has been around for years, which speaks for itself in this city. I really enjoyed the organic Beau's Seasonal beer on tap though they have a strong cocktail list with staples like a Martini and Old Fashioned. Loved the cozy atmosphere and mazing food (I shared the mozzarella starter, a perfectly cooked pasta special and pizza). It's the perfect place to catch up with a girl friend, take your mum or have a low key date night. Will be back asap.

How we didn't know about this cozy place that's been around for ten years, I can't say. Michael, co-owner, makes us feel welcome, like old friends. 
Great wine list to explore. The food, Italian and delicious.

What a nice find in the lakeshore west end 
Great atmosphere , super nice staff and the food was great 
Not much more to add

If you are in downtown Toronto, highly recommend this restaurant.

Amazing food. You will never experience better service anywhere else than here. Caring people at this restaurant. Overall amazing experience

reviews.text: Food was absolutely delicious! We were there on a Sunday night, so it was quiet and intimate, but I can see it being really loud and energetic on a Friday or Saturday night. I will definitely go back again!
Hidden gem on the Danforth. Fresh delicious dishes served with a smile. We love the colourful patio and chill Cuban vibes. Highly recommended!

Went out for my birthday with a friend for dinner. Made online reservation. Happened upon Cuban Carnival. Live music, samba dancers, fixed menu, and mojitos all night long. The owner and chef came out and danced around with a whole pig. Such a great night! What an appreciation for food and for life. The owners here are the nicest people and work so hard. I love this place. Been a few times now and always glad I came. üíñ

Let's start positive. The food. The food was delicious. Scrumptious. Delightful. We had a group of four, sat out on the patio for a late Saturday dinner. We ordered the platter appetizer which was every bit enjoyable. Dinners were fantastic too, I had the lamb, everyone else was pleased with theirs as well... But that's as far as it goes. For a Saturday night with "live entertainment" the place was empty. So the atmosphere lacked. We ordered drinks, a mambo loco, which promised to be a concoction of alcohol, tangy pineapple juice and hot sauce for a kick. It was just burning spicy rum... Very disappointing. Dessert was even more lack luster. I had shared the chocolate cake, which simply ended up being a slice of Costco's tuxedo cake: at the same price as if I had bought the whole cake. My friends has the flan and the creme brulee which are hard to mess up, yet we're bland and the creme brulee was over cooked. The most disheartening part of the evening however was the speed of service, especially in a nearly empty restaurant. Our appetizer and drinks weren't served to us until we had been there nearly an hour. Mains were slow to arrive as well, and dessert just seemed the be the "icing on the cake". Somehow the bills seemed to be at the table within minutes of dessert being served though.

Had such an amazing time with the family. Kids loved the food and the music just warmed our souls.

A definite return in the future.

Can't wait for the warmer weather to enjoy the patio
Had the Confit de Canard with Yuca fries and the Bistec a la Planta - New York Steak. There was only one other table dining and felt a little dry like the...

My wife had the sea bass and loved it.  My steak was very good....

reviews.text: Mantra on Don Mills is my all time favourite restaurant in Toronto. The staff made me feel so at home and every mouthful reignited my passion for Indian cuisine. Cannot recommend enough!!

Had an excellent visit here. The food is tasty and the menu options are perfect for sharing. We ordered a main (tandoori chicken) with I believe 3 shared apps. The service was great and the ambience here is also very good. Would recommend and would visit again.

I went here and it was absolutely delicious. The service was fantastic! I was a fan of the ambience. The decor was beautiful and I really like the bar in the middle. It was cozy but not too jam packed. I asked for recommendations and I was not disappointed. The server was helpful and checked to ensure we were enjoying ourselves. Something unique I tried was the butter chicken baos- which I‚Äôve never thought could be so good! I‚Äôll be back here for that and there‚Äôs so many other things still left to try on the menu. I usually park in the metro parking lot when I go there because it‚Äôs a quick walk over.

I had lunch with my family here on a Saturday. The place was almost empty. Only one other family was there in the restaurant. The ambience is unique. The food was delicious but expensive. Added bonus that it's located inside CF shops at Don Mills which makes it a nice family outing.
Mantra has a beautiful atmosphere and the food was really good! My server was very nice. Overall experience is 10/10.

Nice atmosphere. Cool vibe. Food is great, trending to amazing but not quite there yet.

lic_profile: Located in a building originally built in 1910, the newly renovated Maple Leaf Tavern strives to recreate the look and feel of a true community tavern. With a focus on working with local suppliers and an elevated menu created by Scarborough native, Chef Jesse Vallins, Maple Leaf Tavern is has become a neighbourhood destination in East Toronto.

reviews.text:
This is my favorite spot in the area. Amazing drinks, fun bartenders. I've tried most things on the menu. The burgers are amazing. You can split the rib eye with someone and you'll still be stuffed. Scotch eggs...all kinds fo great stuff and a great atmosphere. It's a great building. 
They also have a REAL kids menu - not just the usual frozen chicken fingers and mac and cheese you find everywhere else. At most places we just order our 3 year old something from the regular menu since the children's menu is so awful. But here, they have great choices for kids, which we really appreciate.
Great value! Reasonable price for very good food. Tartare was tasty and fresh. Famous for their burger, it was a solid pick. Atmosphere is very nice. Staff did a great job too!
Wonderfully friendly staff and great food. I love the atmosphere as well. I wish there were more places like it.

This is the first time I didn't want to write a review because selfishly I don't want people to know how good Maple Leaf Tavern is! Hands down the best brunch I've had in Toronto. Impeccable service and extraordinary food and drink. We both had Lattes and shared the daily scone (maple almond) and it came with cream and blueberries. We had the Brunch to Share for $22/person which included toast, scrambled eggs, thick cut bacon, sausage, corned beef hash, baked beans, potatoes, roasted tomatoes and mushrooms. We couldn't decide what we liked more because everything was phenomenal... Not one dish was a misstep. Also came with 3 sauces... Highly recommend the brown sauce and the hot sauce. So much food - - generous portions. Can't wait to try dinner. We will be running back again and again!

Consistently great service (especially the bartenders), top-notch cocktails, and delicious food. The rotating sausage sharing plate is always awesome, as are the fish cakes, and the burger. Go between 3 and 6 on Thursdays and Fridays for "Tipple Time" drink and snack specials.
The atmosphere in the Maple Leaf Tavern is warm, dark, and cozy. You really leave the outside behind and have a chance to focus on food and...
Place: such a fancy tavern with a lot of character. The owner was adamant about not having any TVs in the place because he wanted to encourage people to...

Fantastic establishment !!! Their burger is arguably one of best in city and the tartar is a deconstructed bigmac !!!

White tablecloth service or relaxed...

Chef Chris Locke utilizes his British roots to create innovative dishes that highlight the bounty of Ontario and Canada. Marben prides itself in using only the highest quality ingredients from local source and suppliers and craft all breads, condiments, and sauces in-house.

reviews.text: This place was SO good. We had an early dinner in our first night in Toronto and it was some of the best food of the trip. Inventive, unique, and beautiful, our meals were not only delicious, they were pretty. When we arrived the chef was cooling dozens of beef fat brioche buns and, seeing me ogle them, he brought one over for us to try. I died. It was amazing. My meal was the chicken leg and my only complaint was that I wanted more. It was not quite enough for me. But the wine was exceptional and the food left me wanting more rather than feeling so stuffed I couldn‚Äôt move. Overall, a very cool vibe and an awesome meal. We‚Äôll be back!

First time in Toronto..this place was AWESOME. Great service, great mimosas, and fantastic food. Our server Blake was amazing. Bartender Dan was hilarious & Karen (I think how you spell it) was super friendly and a great host to us.  HIGHLY recommend.

First time coming here and ordered their burger. Fries were delicious but I can't say the burger was. It was a large piece of meat that was super filling, but it lacked flavour and was pretty dry.

Wouldn't recommend as you can spend $22 for a better burger elsewhere.

Great service, first and foremost!
However, 6 of us shared 2 bottles of $50 wine, each had a beer, shared 3 appetizers and got the 55oz porter steak family style.... our bill was $1000. And that 55oz steak? Was a $30 roast. We requested it cooked rare... we received it cooked medium. If you want to sell a $300 portion of ‚Äústeak‚Äù, please serve it bone in... I personally do not believe this was a steak at all. It came cut into 12 thin roast beef-like slices. Really disappointed. Would not recommend anyone order this gross misrepresentation and over priced ‚Äúfamily style‚Äù serving.
Amazing service! Great staff, thanks to Zane and Chris, we felt very well cared for.  Food was excellent. Great atmosphere. Will be back!

In this country no one accepts this kind of behaviour. Not gonna go there ever and hope, they gonna learn some manners.

Friday afternoon 6pm came here with two friends. We were the only customers. 

Ordered one veg dish + one chicken dish + three pieces of naan. 

Price is around $10-15 for each dish and $3 for naan. They serve wine and beer.

Taste is good, not too oily. Naan was served in slices. 

Portions could‚Äôve been a little bigger for the price we paid.

Service was great (it helps we were the only dine in customers). There were a few walk-ins; another table arrived later on.

It seems to be a family restaurant, or at least it has that vibe.

The facilities were clean; paper towels are provided in the WC.

Great place for casual evening gatherings with friends.

Had Chicken curry, onion kulcha, and garlic naan. What a disaster! Not even close to Indian taste. Onion kulcha was like a sandwich that too half cooked. Curry was not at all tasty. Please consider the richness of Indian cuisines and reassess your cooking.

Delicious food, friendly service, and comfortable decor. Portions are reasonably sized, which is good for guys like me who have to watch their waistlines but just can't stop themselves from cleaning their plate. I'm definitely adding this one to my regular rotation!

reviews.text: Over the past couple of years, this has been our favourite restaurant for a nice evening out - and we live 30 minutes away. We love the ambiance, the food has always been very good, the staff nicely balance attentiveness with allowing us our space, and the prices are quite good. My wife cannot eat garlic, and only a few things that are either slow-cooked or marinated end up on the exclusion list, which says that most dishes are prepared fresh.

Unfortunately we decided not to dine here on 5/3/2019 as we were told by waitress upon arrival we have 2 minutes to order as kitchen is closing early due to a slow night. We arrived at 9:40pm while stated closing hours  are 11pm. I can understand it being any other weekday closing early, however a Friday night there should not be any excuse to close early. We ended up dining elsewhere and spending a combined $100 for two people as we do not limit ourselves when dining out; a lost opportunity for this restaurant.
Everything in this place is great: ambience, staff and food. We really enjoyed our meals.
