lic_profile: Michael's on Simcoe, located in the heart of downtown Toronto, is an upscale, modern steak house with an Italian touch. Specializing in premium beef, seafood and handmade pastas, carefully selected ingredients are sourced from trusted suppliers who only offer the finest of products. White table cloth service is complemented by valet service five nights a week, a gorgeous bar and lounge offers live music four nights a week and the exquisitely designed dining room is accented by a fireplace. The menu is enhanced by Wine Spectator award winning wine list featuring nearly 700 offerings.

reviews.text: The service was amazing, as was their whiskey selection. Food quality was superb. My wife and I enjoyed an amazing meal hear. They split dishes up so that we could have our own tastings. The selection was extensive. Being able to select local beef as well as USDA prime or Japanese Kobe was a treat.

I went to Michael's for my girlfriends birthday dinner and it definitely lived up to the hype. It was outstanding in every sense of a dining experience. I had the Kobe steak which was presented to me with a special knife of my choice. It was a really awesome experience. I would definitely recommend trying it out at least once.

Want to impress your date or coworkers?  Take them here.  Want to go broke on delicious food? Go here.  Want to grab a steak and a beer then this isn't your place.  It's a really fancy place to eat but I just couldn't justify eating here unless it was a VERY special occasion

reviews.text: Tartines and mussels were quite tasty, fries were good but kind of salty. The price is very reasonable at lunchtimes. Recommend!
Quaint and cozy restaurant. Food was okay however overly seasoned perhaps. Staff was friendly.

Ambiance 4 / Food 5/ Service 5
Their price is also amazing. You will not go wrong with any choice of main course. All are impeccable. I should know, I tried them all.

Food was good but service can be improved. We waited 45 mins for a reservation. When seated and served our appetizers we didn't have our utensils and napkins. When dessert came, they got one of them wrong but they made up for it by giving one on the house.

I have come here quite a few times over the years (around 10 perhaps) and I have to say that the food has really gone down hill. My last two experiences there were with large groups who ordered multiple courses and all of us were disappointed with some aspect of our meals. For instance one of my favourite dishes is their escargot, and the past two times I have had it there the quality was not as good as it was before (not as creamy, watery). I had their duck and the skin was barely browned and hardly any of the fat underneath was rendered. My creme brule was liquid at the bottom. My mom had the pate, which used to come with a delicious multigrain toast, and now is served with a basket of untoasted grocery store imitation french loaf. I don't know if they switched chefs or management but I don't think I will be heading there again any time soon. It feels like someone is trying to cook french food from a recipe without any of the skills required or knowledge of what the end result should be.

lic_profile: Miku Toronto, Aburi Restaurant's first east coast location, is situated at Bay and Queen‚Äôs Quay. With over 7000 square feet, a raw bar, sushi bar, large patio and private dining rooms, Miku brings contemporary upscale design to the southern Financial District. Corporate Executive Chef Kazuya Matsuoka along with Chef de Cuisine Michael Acero and Head Sushi Chef Kazuki Uchigoshi bring Aburi Cuisine to Toronto combining traditional Japanese flavours and techniques with local, East Coast elements to create a truly unique dining experience. The menu focuses on Aburi Sushi as well as fresh seafood, respecting the natural flavours of the ingredients while adding a signature Aburi twist. Japanese and European inspired desserts made in house create the perfect ending to the culinary experience. The menu is complemented with signature cocktails, wines, and an extensive sake list. Knowledgeable staff is always happy to make suggestions on pairings that will please your palate.

reviews.text: As a Thai person, this restaurant is hands down one of the best Thai restaurants in Toronto!!! The food is amazing and taste authentic Thai. There are so many traditional Thai dishes that you can't find in any other Thai restaurants. You can tell how good the place is by the amount of people lining up. Trust me, it's worth the wait. Plus, the restaurant is so well organized that you'll get you table within 20 minutes, no matter how busy it looks. All the staffs are super nice, friendly and helpful. Moreover, the restaurant is so well decorated. The owners, who are Thais, must have paid attention into details that even the plates and bowls they're using are from Thailand. The place is such a cozy and fun place that it's so perfect to chill and hang out with your friends. Highly recommended!!! If you are in Toronto, make a reservation in advance or just go. You don't wanna Miss it.

Wow, what can I say about this restaurant? Hands down, the best sushi I've ever had. The staff was very professional, nice, polished, and well dressed. Our waiter, Elbert, was accommodating, caring, and a great gentleman.

The mixed sushi platter I had was described very well to me and each piece was unique and delicious. This is a must try if you like sushi. I will definitely be back here. This was such a pleasant experience and we left full and happy. Keep doing what you're doing, we need more places like this!

Spectacular Japanese cuisine and an inspiring environment. The torched sushi makes it a destination and one of the top spots for Toronto sushi. Conveniently located near the docks to centre island, so a great spot to meet friends before popping off your island day!

Lunch of the weekends is also great if you want to avoid the work crowds.

Miku is a higher class Japanese restaurant down by the Toronto waterfront. Although it's very big, and prices are more expensive, the service and quality of food is extremely reasonable for the cost. There are many big tables, and booths at this restaurant. Great for group gatherings! They also have a very large sake collection. The salad on the menu is actually one of the best non sushi items to order, you won't be dissatisfied.

I enjoyed the Premium Zen lunch set - I would recommend that they space out the plates (perhaps by temperature) so that food can be consumed at a slightly more relaxed pace and without concern that something won't be warm when you eat it.  I can see the experience being great if you are in a rush at lunch though.  The preparation of each plate was nice and the torched sushi was a highlight for me.
What can I say about miku that probably hasn't been said by other guests...I'm not really sure but it is one of the best restaurants my gf and I have ever...

Amazing breakfast dish as part of a local food tour. Would highly recommend the eggs and the tortilla chips cooked in tomato sauce. They tasted like tomato sauce but were still totally crunchy. Absolutely amazing. Also had Mexican Mimosas which is orange juice mixed with Dos Equis.

Hate to say it but it was actually the worst meal I have ever had. Food tasted the way dog food smells. Went on taco Tuesday and my girlfriend and I have been sick ever since. Been two days and my stomach is still turning. Love Mexican food but this was a really bad experience. Staff were nice and drinks were good, but I feel sick just thinking about the food.

First time at this wonderful Mexican spot and I must say I was very impressed with the taste of the food and service I received. The server took his time to explain the dishes and even suggested some great things on the menu for us to try out. The price was reasonable. I would definitely return back to this restaurant.
Tasty food, great atmosphere, and excellent service! Was there with a group and the bill splitting situation was completely taken care of by our server with even having asked about it.

Initially I had plans to come here during summerlicious but plans fell through and my friend and I ended up coming here on a late Saturday afternoon.

Savour unforgettable flavours from handmade pasta to fresh fish in the elegant dining room that flickers with candlelight. Mistura has an extensive wine list and a list of creative and refreshing cocktails and martinis to accompany your dinner. The friendly, professional staff will make you feel welcome and comfortable while you enjoy the entire dining experience.

reviews.text: Great place for real authentic Italian dinner, Nonna's Lasagna is my favourite. Great wine list, great atmosphere. BEST ITALIAN IN TORONTO.
Dinner was amazing tonight! Every time I go I keep remembering why I love this place so much.   Besides the delicious food,  the staff and owner are just wonderful.  I can‚Äôt wait for my next visit.

Amazing food. Great service. 

Quiet location with some intimate areas. Nice place for a quiet meal.

Went here over the wknd to celebrate a gender reveal. The staff was really nice during our dinner and the manager Nick was very helpful while we coordinated the dinner. The service was great however the food didn‚Äôt match it wasn‚Äôt the best Italian food, my guest found it very bland.

I‚Äôve been to Mistura many times, every special occasion has been celebrated here and that‚Äôs due to impeccable service and quality of food. 

There really are no words that would do their food justice; the balsamic glazed lamb are a family favourite.  I don‚Äôt know if decadent is an appropriate word to describe the seafood risotto, but it is just that.  The fritto misto is light and crisp and their pizza is to die for. 

I would have never thought beet risotto would be SO good, but here it is. Their pasta? It‚Äôs the best! They really over look nothing. This matched with impeccable service makes Mistura my go to for any special occasion or when I‚Äôm in the mood for 5 star service and food. I absolutely love it! Paulo and staff you don‚Äôt just do it right, you do it right every time! 

Thank you!

lic_profile: Montgomery's is a modern day Mom n' Pops restaurant driven by local ingredients and great wine & beer. Recently ranked as one of Canada's Top 100 Restaurants in 2019 and No.7 in Post City's Top 50 Toronto restaurants, Montgomery's sits at home in the creative West Queen West neighbourhood. This unique family run restaurant is owned & operated by husband & wife duo, Chef Guy Rawlings & Kim Montgomery Rawlings. Guy utilizes creative cooking techniques, alongside traditional methods, to design a menu that focuses exclusively on Canada's ingredients. With a career spanning over 19 years working in kitchens in Toronto, Montreal, New York, Beijing, and England, Guy is admired by chefs and foodies alike for his passion for local ingredients, love for foraging, fermenting, preserving and making all things from scratch including the delicious in-house baked sourdough bread & cultured butter that the restaurant is getting renowned for. With an elegantly warm, yet minimalist dining room, Montgomery's is a space that cooks creative, delicious, forward-thinking food.

reviews.text: Outstanding service! Ordered the chef's tasting menu and was absolutely delighted. We were served a variety of dishes, and each and every one was created with thoughtful care. Will definitely be returning, and recommending to friends and family.

Had a great time here last week for my dad's birthday. The wine/beer list was very well put together, and the service was great. The chicken liver/neck dish was incredible, and I was surprised at what they managed to do with celeriac. The trout was perhaps the most perfect piece of fish I have ever had. Will come back in the future for more special occasions.

Came here after seeing it on Canada's top 100 restaurants for 2019 and felt disappointed by the experience. Service was great, but the portions are small and unexciting. The food is meant to be shared, which is great for trying new things. However, the food wasn't anything special. Just got a fillet of fish for 28$ with some sauce. It was okay tasting, but for the price it be nice to have something else included with it such as vegetables/rice etc... wouldn't recommend if you have a big appetite.

I was really excited for this after seeing all the positive reviews and it is a unique set up. I also believe in their concept of sourcing locally for the menu and the restaurant is hip & trendy. I recommended this place for a work function dinner. We had a couple great bottles of wine, but realized the restaurant doesn't really do cocktails because lemons/bitters cannot be sourced in Canada. We ordered the set taster menu, but the food took incredibly long. The server tried her best and she was lovely, but at the end of the day when it has been 2hrs for the seating and we still haven't had our mains, it is a bit unfortunate. The food was good, but it wasn't out of the ordinary. My favourite was the pate that was a part of the appetizers.

We attended a Nicholas Pearce wine event there recently and were very impressed with their staff who were extremely attentive yet not intrusive. The food was not part of their regular menu as it was specifically chosen to pair with the four wines that were being poured. The chef (Guy Rawlings) created outstanding and unique dishes which were a perfect match for the wines. Prior to the event, Kim exchanged emails with me to see if we had any food sensitivities. The atmosphere was chill, the music eclectic and not loud. Probably not to everyone's taste, but if you're craving a unique food experience, highly recommended.

This is the most underrated restaurant in all of Toronto. I have been to all of the top 10 list restaurants, all of the must try places, all of the...
Montgomery's is located near Queen/Ossington - easy to miss if you don't now what you are looking for. I had been wanting to try Montgomery's for a while...

reviews.text: Moxie's has always been a staple at Scarborough Town center and it's  a great place to go to after shopping before or after a movie. It's simply a 2 minute walk from the mall and the  theater with ample parking provided, if needed. The decor, food and service is usually pretty good. A few times it was a little on the bland side. I think they need a bit of a revamp on their menu. But all in all its a great place and would recommend.

Honestly, I've came to this Moxie's location for YEARS, and the service and food has been fine. But tonight in particular, my friends and I came to celebrate a birthday. Our waitress started off very rude, was giving us mean faces and didn't care to tend our table well. We tried not to look into it much, but our drinks were late as were our food, sauces and extra condiments. One of my friends was not happy with her drink and asked if it was possible to be remade and her answer was "I can do it again but it's going to taste the same regardless." Like who says that? Lastly when we were paying, many of us didn't care to tip her since she was so rude and not very helpful the entire night. When she realized they weren't tipping her she gave very mean glances at us. I decided to tip her and her mean glances continued but I got a thank you while the others didn't. Overall this waitress was TERRIBLE and I wish I got her name but unfortunately didn't. Moxie's you need to step up your hiring game.

Last evening I ordered 2 orders of Red Thai Curry. I‚Äôve ordered this so many time in the past few years (most from the same location). Well, it‚Äôs changed but the price didn‚Äôt. 
The veggies are all slivered now. No substantial vegetables. There‚Äôs no green beans now. 
The sauce is being thickened with some artificial ingredient. It‚Äôs not worth the money now. Maybe they‚Äôve got a new cook?  
I‚Äôll try another location but Scarborough Town Centre, we‚Äôre done!!
Dude who answered the phone was rude. Asked for a bit extra ice cream for my sticky toffee pudding because the cake to ice cream proportions are not good. The guy on the phone was mean and unhelpful.

Moxies is always a great place for dinner/deserts/meeting up with friends. Their process are slightly higher than the other places in the area but the food is delicious. Loved their salmon ($29) and their white chocolate brownie ($9) is the best dessert ever!

reviews.text: Amazing burger! Truly one of the best I had in Toronto so far. The bun, the meat, the fries were all really delicious. Service was really good. Location was fantastic. I understand it is in Yorkville, which is kind of an upscale neighbourhood, but the place is a little too expensive. Overall really good experience! :)

Great restaurant that's accessible and close to work and school in the downtown area. The patio has great views, and there a wide variety of options on the menu. Portion sizes are great for the prices, and you definitely get your money's worth on the main courses. Check out this spot if you're in Yorkville and looking for an enjoyable lunch!

Best burger I had since I moved to Toronto last year and tried 10+ places. Went to Museum Tavern because of the many reviews and blogs talking about this burger and wasn't disappointed. Museum Tavern is a nice place, not your average burger joint. About the burger itself: very tasty burger with two patties and amazing cheddar cheese. The quality of the meat is outstanding. The only thing that can be improved is the size: it's a rather small burger and the patties were a bit thin in my opinion. I'll definitely come back to try again.

Well after a great day at the Museum to end up here was the best way to top the day. We both had the burger, which has been rated as one of the best in Toronto.... Well.... They weren't wrong! The burger was amazing! And the ton of fries they give you with it!! My mouth is watering just thinking about it again! The stuff are friendly and and we're never far to make sure we had everything we needed. This place was great! I will be back again and again!
Everything amazing: the view (if you seat outside) the drinks (we tried the Moscow Mule) and the food! Our tuna burger and lobster roll were A-MA-ZING! Truly recommend!

What a gem.

lic_profile: Myato Gastropub is a fusion tapas bar and restaurant that focuses on both food and drink, exploring the boundaries of Korean cuisine. Cocktails and cuisine are paired in a unique way to create a different, yet familiar, Korean bar experience. The chef's approach to the menu is constantly evolving, using new techniques and ingredients with traditional methods to highlight her Korean roots and Western experiences. The space is a combination of rustic modern and traditional Korean features that preserve the history and characteristics of the building. Myato aspires to provide guests with a space, service, and food wrapped with care and effort as one would, when giving gifts to their loved ones.

reviews.text:
Product/Service: 4/5
Great service and food. The black sesame chicken was definitely the winner.

Location: 5/5
Really close to Bathurst subway station.

Price: 4/5
A little expensive, but they make it up for the dining experience that you get.

Atmosphere: 5/5
Nice and cozy. Great for catching up with friends, dates, or hanging out for drinks.

Came here for a friend's birthday. I loved the feel and atmosphere of the space. The staff were very friendly and helpful to our table of 7! We got our food within a reasonable amount of time and it was really good! Just definitely come back here. Didn't know this place existed until my friend had her birthday dinner there. Great time!

Myato Gastropub is hands down one of my favourite restaurants to visit when I'm downtown. The food is so delicious that I often try to arrange my meetings with friends there. 

I absolutely adore the elegant ambience that the interior design creates. Whoever did the interior designing deserves applause - the way that the wooden elements harmonize with the various wall textures, and lighting design adds to the overall dining experience. 

I love the spatial design as the tables and seats are spread apart well enough from other patrons, which gives me the comfort of knowing that I can have private discussions with whoever I'm dining with. 

I tried a few of the house-made concoctions, and I was impressed. I forgot the name of one of the drinks I had (I think it had yuzu in it?) but that was so tasty, I'm looking forward to ordering it again. 

Lastly, I sincerely appreciated how friendly all the waiters were. When I asked for their opinions regarding a few dishes, they were informative and thoughtful. 

I strongly recommend this place to anyone looking for a good meal, atmosphere and time :)

Went here with a large party on Saturday night and everything was amazing. Our server did a fantastic job. The cocktails were definitely worth the money. Try any of the rolls. You won't be disappointed. I'll definitely be back!

Great restaurant to share some tapas at with with friends! Definitely recommend getting the dragon roll that‚Äôs on fire, super cool. The drinks are really damn good as well and the overall vibe is chill, not too uptight. Definitely recommend if you want to try a little bit of everything, and if you enjoy sharing food with friends!

lic_profile: A cozy, romantic jazz bar & restaurant, N'awlins is located in the heart of the entertainment district and offers a variety of Cajun-Italian cuisine and live jazz & blues music. The patio is perfectly situated for watching the excitement of King Street West. With close proximity to theatres, it's a perfect spot to enjoy dinner & drinks before or after the show.

reviews.text: Was there on Saturday night at the N'awlins with my daughter.  Its a nice cozy jazz bar and the servers are friendly.  The jazz band was simply fantastic. Had an enjoyable evening. Will definitely come back again.

Food was music in my mouth. Barkeep had a nice touch with the drinks and felt approachable. Interior makes you feel transported out of time and place. I loved the balance of fancy/casual as someone who generally prefers the low-key. An elevated way to unwind.

Atmosphere is wonderful. This place delivered on so many levels as I've been trying to make it here the last 3 times I've visited TO. It was worth the wait. Service was great and the live music added to the experience. The escargot was the first time I've had it and I would highly recommend. Will come back next time I visit. Thanks!

Just wow!!! Anniversary dinner, totally winged it with no plans and found this little gem of a place! Amazing food, amazing music, pleasant and friendly servers, did I mention the music?!?!  10/10 would come back, thanks to the Blackburn brothers for a great performance
Delicious food, great service and warm atmosphere. The live music is incredible - feels like you're in New Orleans!

reviews.text: Very cool place with a great atmosphere. Alot more authentic and overall good vibe. The quality and appearance of the food is fantastic. The open kitchen is a great touch everything looks fresh and inviting. Only problem is the price definitely a more expensive place, not sure it's worth it in every aspect. I would definitely come back and try something else. Lunch menu and roll selection is a bit limited.
Best date spot in Toronto.  If you want to impress your partner, come here, as there is a real traditional Japanese vibe.  My date loved the sushi, I loved the steak.  Awesome!
Great service and great food. I have been going here for years and have never been disappointed. The teriyaki salmon is amazing!

This restaurant feels very traditional...the ladies are wearing Kimonos and the men are also dressed traditionally...you feel that you are in a Japanese restaurant.

The attention is 100%...they are making sure that you are very well taken care of.

I recently celebrated my birthday there...so thank you for the Green Tea ice cream with the birthday candle...it was a nice touch.

You made my birthday special
We come here all the time for our company functions.  The sushi here is amazing.  My favourite is the sushi spring rolls.  Must try!
I come here quite often during my stay in Toronto when I'm looking for grilled food (to Ata) and sushi fix. I would recommend my friends to come here for...

Overall, the prices are as high or sometimes HIGHER than Ja Bistro...

reviews.text: The atmosphere and vibe was good. But the food? The grilled octupus was too fishy and wasn't fresh at all. There was nothing good except the pizza we ordered(mushroom). I don't understand why it has such a good review on google. Maybe my expectation was too high.

Great service, food was excellent, fun atmosphere.  Sat at the bar, great scene.  Staff was great, everyone came by to see how we were, very attentive.  Food was excellent.  The tortellini in particular was incredible.  Highly recommend.

Excellent place and professional service, great atmosphere. Some dishes, as a pork chop, was absolutelly amazing, however some like veal were plain and not unique. You expect a bit more for the price you pay. During reservation, I have mentioned a Birthday event, but was overlooked by staff probably. Overall 4 out of 5. Thank you.

Atmosphere was fine but I feel scammed. They have half-off wine on Wednesday except it is only half off a selection of bottles starting $140 (so $70) and it is not applicable to their cheaper bottles which start at $50. They structure the menu so the 'half off' bottles are well displayed and their sign makes no comment it is only a very small selection of very overpriced bottles. 

I could have walked a block away to another place and paid 60% less. 

It just sleazy to advertise a bait-and-switch.

Amazing dinner and service.  The wine list is enormous but not overwhelming. Bryce was our server and he totally took care of us throughout dinner.  We‚Äôve eaten in lots of nicer Italian restaurants but this one is near the top of the list.  Would highly recommend to anyone looking to have a wonderful meal

reviews.text: Watched the Raptors game 3 at Northern Maverick and was pleasantly surprised. The space has a nice industrial feel to it and service was good. Nice to see a variety of snacks outside of the usual bar menu, but they were pricey for just being okay. Would like to come back to try a flight of their beers on the patio though!

We had the pleasure of having our wedding and reception, which was planned from abroad, at The Northern Maverick Brewing Co and we could not have made a better choice. 

The communication was very smooth and quick, and when we had our walkthrough, everybody involved was helpful and excited about our big day. 

On the day itself, they helped set everything precisely as we wished for and the service was one of the bests we have ever had. The staff continuously checked if everyone had food and/or drinks, the kids were taken care of when needed, and we (the bride and groom) barely had time to realize when our glasses needed a refill. 

Wonderful atmosphere, delicious food and excellent staff!
I went here for a beer on a patio and wasn't disappointed. The beer was a good price and they have a good atmosphere. I would definitely go back.
Samuel and Harley served us, amazing friendly service. Great  beers. A bit more shade on the patio would be fantastic :)
Been twice and unfortunately negative experience both times. 3/4 full pint, over 1 hour wait for food and generally lacklustre experience. Nice patio and location though.

reviews.text: A beautiful restaurant that is a quick drive to or from the airport. The food/service are both top notch. Dishes that were well prepared, flavourful and esthetically pleasing. Definitely recommend this place to eat. The chef was also great, knowing we had two vegans in our party he went out of his way to elevate their experience as well - with a special dessert at the end.
Didn't eat there just had a few drinks.  The bartender was an amazingly friendly guy.  Very personable
Nice location.  Good service.  Tasty meal.

We had vouchers from Canadian Airlines for dinner here and, although they stated that the value was $15 including tax, the restaurant charged us an additional $5 because "of the way they calculate the value".  Could not win the discussion that this was not accurate or correct.  So I took my complaint to the hotel front desk where, after assuring me that they understood and agreed with me, went to discuss with the restaurant manager and came back stating that all is ok now and will credit my account.  I, thus, offered my credit card but they said "no need; we have it online".  Yesterday I received my CC statement and found that they actually did NOT credit my account.  A scam going on there???
Fabulous service and food. Our server Erin was great. Nice place to chill!
Good food and great service. In the Sheraton Hotel Airport and Conference Centre and the hotel is a great location and good amenities. The Olio has a really...

reviews.text: Had a great experience. The service was good, and the food was delicious. The atmosphere is very warm here. The prices are a little on the higher side for what you get, but the ingredients are high quality and there is a good variety in the menu. The desserts in particular were wonderful! Overall, a great place for a special occasion.

Beautiful decor and amazing service. We had the pleasure of chef Omar come say hi to our table which elevated our guests experience to a whole new level. The kids thought he was he was super cool.

Food was delicious and arrived in a timely manner. The kids loved their calamari, sweet potato fries and spaghetti. 

Great ambiance, we will definitely be back.

Changed menu since last visit. Nothing really  appealed to me. Had a pizza. Was so so. We were with others who had also dined there before and also struggled with food selection. Weren't overly impressed either. Hope O & B will change their menu a bit. Always enjoyed food. Nice restaurant atmosphere and waiter was very good and attentive.

Went to celebrate our birthdays...3 of us and was hoping to have something really special. 
Not like it used to be. Was honestly disappointed with the quality of the food.
1.  Fried cauliflower appetizer 
2. Fried calamari appetizer
3. Crab and cod cake
4. Liver and onions
5. Daily fizz (drink)

Cauliflower was blanched first but was so overcooked, it had no texture, like mush.

Calamari. For $15 and the small portion, you'd expect better. Thin rings with a light coating, and a dusting of spices. 

Crab cake...decent.

Liver and onions came with green scallion mashed potatoes.  My liver was hard to eat because of the veins left in it, not to mention it was burnt.  Server didn't ask why I left half my meal untouched.
Too much raw, large chunks of scallion in the mashed potatoes...a little off putting.

The nice part was that they brought us each a celebratory cake for our birthdays. 

I was really hoping for a great meal...maybe next time.

Nice place for quick lunch.. tremendous variety in food options.  Had Jerky chicken and loved it. Excellent blend of tastes in a single plate. Staff was courteous enough to make our lunch experience worth cherishing.

Visited June 1 for dinner. 
The server Shahzad was very friendly and seemed to be a vegetarian himself. Would definitely come back again.

The tree-lined candle lit patio is the perfect place to sit back and savour ONE's culinary creations and unique signature cocktails, all the while taking in Yorkville's bustling and exciting street life. With dishes that will amaze the palate and an energetic atmosphere, ONE is sure to be an experience to remember.

reviews.text: Upscale restaurant, comfortable seating, delicious food, vibe is great. Service can be a little better. Ordered burger with Caesar salad but the salad served was mixed greens so had to ask for replacement. Waitresses are polite. They have one tv screen at the bar which is good to catch up a game in a top notch restaurant.
Stupendous.   Wonderful service.   Great food.  Glad I wasn't paying, but I would go back.   Nice environment.   We sat in the Neil Young private room.  Very nice.

Pictured is Avocado toast with 2 poached eggs and Pork Belly with Waffles.
Food was excellent; however, the coffeeless cappuccino (3 sips the rest foam) and watery latte did not leave us satisfied for this brunch meal.
Our waitress could have been friendlier as well just in general having less sass.

The food here is what you would expect from a restaurant of this reputation and price range. I've removed one star for the service we received. We felt like the waitress was talking down to us, and there was a whole discussion about whether we truly truly understood what Mulled Wine was. We were trying to be respectful even as she continued to give us attitude. Hopefully this waitress will learn to be less condescending with ONE restaurant's other guests.

As I suspected, the food was outstanding; pleasantly surprised by how friendly the staff was.  Consummate professionals who understand fine-dining, but also carry an uncommonly warm and generous spirit.

reviews.text:
could not have enjoyed our experience more. We were 7 on father's day. Our server was lovely and knowledgable. The food, for such a big establishment was tasty and plentiful. We will definitely be back. Oh... the decor is stunning. Recommend this place highly. Michelle was our server.. 5 stars.
thank you, you definitely stood out amongst your competition.

Enjoyed our business lunch there. Staff was great and attentive. Solid wine list. Food is quite good as well. Really enjoyed the mushroom ravioli. But it did come cold though. All three dishes. Even the coffee we ordered was lukewarm. Other than that great place.

GREAT happy hour, well priced drinks. Food seems like a better deal than it really is, portion sizes are very small. Service was good, and the interior design is so beautiful. But, the food is not outstanding. I encourage you to check out the happy hour, but the food needs to step it up a few levels.

While for the most part our main server was lovely, there was a lot left wanting out of our experience last night. We were sat directly beside an open window in torrential rain. It wasn't until an hour into our meal when the floor became dangerously wet that a server came over and shut the window. Service was spotty and it was hard to get anyone's attention. When we did order, drinks took over ten minutes and servers couldn't remember who ordered what. There were only six of us. They'd hold the tray and stare blankly as we organized the drinks among ourselves. Furthermore, some drinks came and others didn't. To ensure everyone was charged for what they received, we all asked for separate bills. The server looked annoyed and said it would just be easier if she bring us one bill and we work it out among ourselves. Quite unprofessional in my opinion. Food was fine. Nothing to rave about. Likely won't be coming back or recommending it to anyone.

My first time ever at Oretta and definitely not my last. We were seated straight away by our wonderful, charismatic and helpful server Garrett who took his time to suggest us dishes that were suited to our dietary and personal needs and preferences. The service was fast, friendly and above standard. We were seated on the patio and the heater was provided AS SOON AS we felt a chill (which wasn't even expressed to a member of staff). As well as this the food was delicious and the cocktails were memorable AT LEAST. 5 stars plus an extra 5 for over all experience.

I'm so delighted my girlfriend brought me to this place.

Really love the Aperitivo hour at Oretta, the instagrammable decor, the cute dishes that keep you...

lic_profile: Inspired by Italian roots, influenced by Canadian Heritage, the Paese menu is a testimony to its philosophy. Paese's chefs use traditional Italian techniques to create dishes with modern appeal, the result is Italian inspired combinations that are comfortingly familiar and yet distinctly unique. The menu is complemented by an extensive wine list, having received the Award of Excellence from the Wine Spectator for over 20 years. Conveniently located in an uptown neighbourhood on Bathurst Street near the 401, Paese's warm wood and grey tones with sound of light Italian music in the background make it an ideal setting whether you are hosting clients or dining with loved ones.

reviews.text:
Sincerely some of the best veggies I have had in a while! Highly recommend their very colourful cauliflower steak. Thought their pizza was solid, but would much quicker come from some veggies or their miami ribs and a bottle of wine. 

Surprised it took me so long to check this place out. Not only do they have one of the largest wine cellars in the city, but their mark up isn't nearly as high as basically every where else.

Great service from the wait staff as they are obviously very well trained.

The private rooms upstairs are very spacious and open with lots of natural light and private bathrooms and coat area.

The food is good Italian.

I love Paese and yes, it is off the beaten track but then again many wicked places are hidden gems and this is one. The wine cellar is one of the best the city has to offer and the passion of the chefs excels. I have always had great attentive service. In the photos below are some of the great eats that I have had but the menu is always changing with the seasons. Positively Italian with a love for Ontario products. One of my loves is the huge emphasis they put on accommodating Vegans, Vegetarians and Gluten Free peeps with top of line menu experiences. I am so addicted to the zucchini ribbon pasta with vegan Bolognese. They can‚Äôt get this off the menu. Desserts are killer I just ate mine too fast to snap a photo. Next time, here‚Äôs hoping. Follow me @joannasable on Instagram

Always wonderful to visit. I'm welcomed with warm hospitality each time I come to dine. The food is always exceptional with choices varying from traditional to unique. The cocktails are done with care and the wine list provides much diversity. Service is alway a cut above. I look forward to my next meal at PAESE followed by tiramisu.
Great restaurant, high quality food for a fair price. Definitely a go-to Italian restaurant for couples and families alike

 Food : flavourful

I have since been back twice since then and the food is excellent. Both times the staff were incredibly friendly as well.

Such a great place, I will be back many more times.

We had our Sunday lunch and the staff, Michelle and Jeff, were so amazing and kind! The food and private room was great! Unfortunately, a few people could not make it. Unlike every other Oliver and bonacini restaurant, we were charged for people that weren‚Äôt there. The manager, Oliver explained to us that we should have said we had less people and just have more show up. Oliver told us to book for 20 people and would have accommodated more people the day of. Extremely unpleasant dealing with the management and forcing us to pay more. Anyone looking to book an event at this restaurant, always say you have less people coming and underestimate your numbers.

reviews.text: So perfect for brunch! Lovely patio in the back with some shade from the sun, if needed. Food was high quality and well prepared. Service was excellent. My new favorite spot!

Great restaurant. We went for breakfast and there was a small queue. Place seems popular.

The portions are not big for the price but the dishes taste great. There is a focus on the main dish. We got the omelette with mushrooms, asparagus and Greek cheese as well as the salmon. Both were pretty good, so was the coffee.

Amazing service & food!  I had the pleasure of arranging a company event with the help of Jillian at the Peter Pan Bistro.  She was quick to respond, extremely accommodating and helpful.  Once the event day arrived, Rebecca and the rest of the staff were extremely helpful to ensure the night was seamless.  Our employees are still talking about what a fantastic time they had!  Thank you, Peter Pan Bistro - we will be back :)

Great little cafe arrived with 30 people and they handled it with out a sweat was very impressed with service. Great food, had the croquet madam, it was a little different to what I expected but light and tasty great version. Coffee was great.

Simple and done right. It was nice to see a bistro being a bistro keeping to the value of being a bistro simple menu, clean food, and big bold flavors. Service was exceptional to the exceptions of a true bistro. And the decor was fierce. I'm glad I made this stop on my trip.
Great place for a quiet bite with my kid over lunch. We both had special dietary requirements. The service was exceptional. The food was delicious and met...

reviews.text: We came here as part of a bachelorette weekend.  To be honest, despite liking Italian, it's never my go-to food choice, but I went along with the plan and...

Absolute disappointment in service, food is...meh...  

Restaurant was cold, unnecessary air conditioning.

Service staffs were forgetful and just not...

YUM!! Piano Piano offers amazing Italian food with a fun flair that never gets old!

The restaurant is well decorated and very spacious, which creates a...

Excellent food, poor service 
Server seemed disinterested in us and was neither attentive or informative. 
Seemed to have forgot a part of our order, and never acknowledged it. 
Food was fantastic though!
A beautiful space like Piano Piano would benefit from a higher standard of service

Wow! This place is a keeper. Great space, high ceilings keep conversation to a background buzz. Fantastic pizza with perfect crust and just the right amount of topping to give an intense flavour and not mush up the crust. Portions can be extremely generous so consider taking the rest home. I'd go back. Highly recommended.

We went to Piano Piano last night for my sister's birthday celebration & were thoroughly impressed! The service was amazing and they went all out to ensure we had felt special. I was extremely impressed with how accommodating they were to my vegan diet, and they were very generous and even brought me food items to ensure I wasn't left out (fruit for dessert for example). The food was delicious and atmosphere was on point. Best of all was our server Mark, he was one step ahead of us the entire time. Thank you for making it a special evening, we will be back!

Food is excellent- you will not be disappointed! Great atmosphere and cool, modern decor. Originally came back again because of both the food and the atmosphere BUT this time I really wanted to mention the exceptional service that my boyfriend and i received. Servers walking by were very attentive to tables whether it was an empty plate, used cutlery or empty glasses... but having said that, Ryan really made this experience a memorable one. Not only was he super friendly, and always folded our napkins, but he was also very knowledgeable of wine and made GREAT recommendations for what to eat. We took his advice on everything and boy did he not steer us wrong!!!! My boyfriend and I were debating which dessert to get; Ryan suggested the Lemon Cheesecake (to die for amazing!) above the cappuccino ice cream- and he ended up bringing us both options, with the ice cream taken care of by him!!! We cant thank Ryan enough for this wonderful experience and we will definitely be back soon!!

Really enjoyed my experience at piano piano. If you're going in a group, I recommend sharing a couple of dishes. Everything I tasted was delicious. We had the pappardelle pasta special, veal, octopus, fun guy pizza, and garlic bread. All were very tasty and the wine recommendation was spot on. Service in general was really good and it was nice to have the waiter make suggestions for food/drink based on some of the dishes we were thinking. My wife is also gluten & dairy free and they had plenty of options for her. Left very full and satisfied. Look forward to next time!

reviews.text: My favourite steakhouse in Toronto! The new owners are from Alberta and get the best AAA Canadian beef for the best prices! I always get the 18oz Cowboy Steak on the sizzling hot stone, the Mediterranean salad to share, and the cod cakes to start. And a bottle of Portuguese red wine, all at a lower cost than other "trendy" restaurants. Geary Ave's best kept secret!

An out of the way location on an industrial street this restaurant, and several others, have created somewhat of a newish destination in the city. One consideration...parking can be somewhat limited so consider Uber on the weekends.
The restaurant was not busy tonight so our reservation for four was honoured right on time and we were seated immediately. Our server - Lief - was extremely professional, efficient and pleasant. It's a family business so they are concerned that everything is right. We started with shared grilled calamari and battered shrimp...both excellent. Then we had the cowboy steak (18oz. and good for sharing) served on a sizzling platter...delicious. The steak is served with fries. As sides we had a Mediterranean salad, and roasted veg. For dessert we shared an apple blossom (pie) and a chocolate mousse...both delicious. The prices are extremely reasonable. The wine list by the glass is very limited but that wine is acceptable. There is a full bar and a wine list by the bottle.
Overall an excellent experience and one we will repeat.

Absolutely fantastic food and service! The staff is so welcoming and very friendly. Our server was so sweet and took the time to explain some of the items on the menu to us with a smile on his face. We tried the chorizo, grilled calamari and cod cakes. They were all beyond amazing!!!! I highly recommend this restaurant to anyone looking to have some delicious food.

Great value for money, and excellent service. I had mussels and they were absolutely delicious, I also had the special which was risotto, which was the perfect consistency and full of flavour. if I could give it 4.5, I would as the calamari was a little rubbery and for me lacked seasoning, but everything was delicious.  Our new local and we will be back.
Came all the way from London. Didn't disappoint.  Wine is great. Food is superb. Dessert is a total bonus to the end of the meal.
An out of the way location on an industrial street this restaurant, and several others, have created somewhat of a newish destination in the city. One...
Fantastic food and great prices. Service was top notch. Went for a friend's birthday and was not disappointed. Definitely a gem!
This restaurant is just around the corner from my workplace.  It has been a great lunch spot with really good food and fast and friendly service.  This past...

reviews.text: One of my personal favourites in Riverside. The food is delicious and unique, and the drink options are great. Hooch hour makes for a fun time. My only criticism is the cover fee after 10 pm on weekends for people who just want to eat in their restaurant area.
Good spot for a bite with something for everyone. Unfortunately menu items seem to be out pretty frequently. Look out for late night weekend dining as the dining area changes over to a dance floor.

Took my friend out for her birthday here a few saturday‚Äôs ago. The staff are amazing! The food was incredible and they have really reasonably priced drinks.  
Went again this past Saturday night a bit later in the evening and did not realize this place had a DJ. Was a really good mix not just all top 40‚Äôs. Everyone was so friendly had a great dance floor going on.  such a good time will definitely be back!

Great location, great service, great drinks and very delicious food!

Hooch Hour is great (5-7pm each day) all pints/drinks are on sale.  The food though, is where Prohibition shines.  If I ever feel like a burger in the city, this is the one I measure all others against.  They really put a lot of thought into it, right down to the bun.

Their nachos are legendary for a reason, you really can't go wrong. 

It's high class pub food, made with quality ingredients.

Service : 
The lack of professionalism from the staff is mind blowing. I am not sure what the target age group is at this establishment, but they talk and treat their customers like underage kids at a rave. Save yourself the embarrassment and don‚Äôt bring out of town friends here.... there are much classier places just blocks away.... like Broadview hotel.  

Food/drinks :
Mediocre at best
Went there for brunch on a Saturday. Pleasantly surprised as I never would have thought brunch at a pub would be so delicious! Only downside was alcohol...

Food was amazing!! Drinks were fine and our server was nice. 

The French toast blew my mind. They put chocolate covered bacon on it!! What?!? The bread was...
It's still my birthday for a few more hours so my best friend and I decided to visit a second Prohibition Gastrohouse location; the other one which I like...

reviews.text:
Delicious food had my coat stolen at this venue - eventually had it returned. It would have been nicer for them to have put a number on it.

Food was excellent but I felt that the wait staff always pressure you to order more than you need to get.

Food: delicious food! Every dish was so tasty as well cooked. I‚Äôm really satisfied. 
Service: service is good and really focus on customer needs. 
Location: The restaurant it‚Äôs a bit dark which I don‚Äôt like.

Recommend!!

Oh man. The food was so tasty. The lamb lollipops, the prawn app, the garlic naan, the sticky toffee pudding with roasted marshmallow ice cream!! Every bite of every dish we ordered was amazing. Highly recommend.

Had a great dinner with 6 people.  Well priced and wide variety of dishes available.  Service was attentive and courteous, knowledgeable of all dishes and able to make good recommendations!

Will definitely be back!

Pukka is the first fine dining experience that I've had with Indian cuisine and it did not disappoint. I like that their menu has a variety of wine, cocktails and beer. Our server Christine was really helpful in describing the  menu items as we had lots of questions! Overall, a really enjoyable experience. I'll definitely be back!

reviews.text:
Been there with my wife for dinner without a reservation. The live music was good, not so loud that it wasn‚Äôt possible to talk and not so quiet that you wouldn‚Äôt hear it. 

There are good options in the menu, and the staff is knowledgeable and helpful, without ever being intrusive. The pasta was well cooked and nicely presented, and the ‚Äúagnello‚Äù (lamb) roast was literally falling from the bone, rich and juicy. 

The wine list is also good enough, for an Italian place this far away from Italy.

My wife and I will definitively come back again.

I've been here before and it has been great and yesterday was no exception. I had a risotto, my mom got seafood pasta and my dad had chicken Parm with pasta.  My parents didn't finish their food so we took it home to go so I could eat it the next day.

I started to eat the pasta and it tasted great and then I took a bite of the chicken and the texture felt super off to me, it was hard to bite or chew. I look at the chicken and half THE CHICKEN IS RAW! What!? How ? My dad ate half and just thought it was crunchy, and I'm pretty sure his crunchy was just raw chicken that was hard to bite through or it was thin enough and was cooked.

I took photos to show the difference in colour of chicken. One is white and the other translucent.... I'm really off put by this and sad to say I won't ever come back to this place. Raw chicken on mother's Day of all days....

My husband I frequent this restaurant often and have never been disappointed. The food and service are always excellent. You can tell that the staff and owner really care and always make us feel welcome. We have tried many items on the menu and I really loved the Seafood Linguine I had when I was there for Mothers Day. We have sent many of the friends to this restaurant and they love it too.

Pasta was a bit of a let down. Meek sauce and lack of flavour. Had the cinghale and it was unexciting and boring. They skipped the cheese for my dish, the server was nice to me but overall quality of service could be improved (loud clearing, dropping things etc). Wine list could have more authentic and newer Italian wines.

Enjoyed the atmosphere and food was delicious. Goes the extra mile to make Micky Mouse shaped pizza for the kids! Have dined here 6 times and every time are met with friendly staff and served a great meal.

reviews.text: The food was outstanding. Very flavorful and complex in texture. Atmosphere was ideal for a date, with low lights and music. Service was spot on, attentive and polite. Our server also made excellent recommendations.  Will definitely be going back again soon !

Had a great time here. They had a nice variety of oysters and also had great deals. Service was good, servers were attentive, and the food came out pretty quickly. The sticky toffee pudding we had for dessert was a bit of a let down, tasted more like a warm fruit cake, but everything else we had was amazing. Would definitely come back again.

Located in the historic and picturesque distillery district, Pure Spirits Oyster House & Grill offers a lot of reasons to keep coming back. From creative cocktails (try the Canadian old fashion) to the friendly and knowledgeable staff, this place is on my go-to list when I'm craving seafood and feeling like spoiling myself. But even if you're on a budget you can still get an amazing experience at Buck a Shuck Tuesdays. There's no limit (believe me!).

Identity crisis

First visit with friends and greatest impression of restaurant was that it doesn't seem to know if it's an oyster bar, steakhouse, or pan-Asian restaurant. The food was all competently prepared, but not particularly memorable and pricing edges this otherwise average restaurant into finer dining territory. Good value it is not. Not a recommend; there are better oyster bars, better steakhouses, and better pan-Asian restaurants in the city to choose from. Service was friendly, attentive and well timed.

Very fresh seafood, great choices we had the seared scallops.. amazing, rainbow trout so good and the Squid ink linguine all highly recommended.  Various cocktails, craft beer. Great staff. 
Side note: I have many food allergies, and I have to  say the Chef did an amazing job modifying my selectionüëç

Great ambiance and good food. Not surprising that it's pricey because it's located in the Distillery District, which is very touristy.

The food is served in hand hammered copper dishes, lushly perfumed with saffron, citrus, rose petal and mint. Familiar foods such as lamb, beef, rice and chicken are exotically transformed into the leanest kebab, heavenly mixed rices and magical stews by the mysterious tastes of pomegranate, cardamom, sumac and traditional herb blends.The Persian table is a gorgeous collage of colours, textures and aromas complemented by a selection of wine, beer and Persian cocktails and enhanced by the display of original artworks exhibited on the walls.

reviews.text:
High quality Persian food here!

Service was extremely friendly but a bit slow! 

I really enjoyed the atmosphere there. 

I didn't care for the appetizers...

Seriously good food. 
I've had Persian food only a few times so I'm not an expert in this food but my friend who I went with knows Persian food. She said it...
I wanted to order faisan jun (not sure if I'm spelling that right). Are used to date a girl from Moran and her mother used to make it. Delicious. Hadn't had...

One of the best restaurants I have ever been, if you want to taste a delicious food you've never tried, that's the place. There is just one risk, you might be addicted so be careful. The prices are very convenient and the environment is awesome. It reminds me of the old Persian empire where you feel like you are a time traveler üòâ. As a 7 star Google guide and someone who has been in three different continents, that's my place.

To be whisked away to a different country by a restaurant's atmosphere is exactly what walking into the queen of Persia is like. The enchanting music and smells are your guides as you wait for your meal. Speaking of meals, the portion sizes are more then generous and the taste has a home cooked love and care infused into it. All this to be topped off with some of the best service you could imagine. Treat yourself and go experiance a whole new world.

Absolutely lovely food. You can tell the owners try so hard to give wonderful service and a great experience. Love taking friends here who have never had Persian food! Very unexpected and delicious flavour combinations.

One of the best Persian restaurants in town. Great food, very nice decoration and excellent service. 
I just highly recommend them to improve their ventilation system.
What a delightful place this is. The lamb kubideh is simply glorious and the deep, rich flavours of the eggplant stew made my mouth do a little dance. Highly recommended.

reviews.text: During the chaos during the Raptors parade that just passed, there was a devastating event that caused a stampede to occur and for my friends and I to run away from the dangers the event brought. We ended up at this restaurant and Louise (the owner) and her lovely daughter and staff took us in during times of fear and kept us safe and secure. We were offered food and water as we waited for the event to pass. Louise and her family and staff reminded me that there is still greatness in the world, and I will definitely be back for a proper meal at this restaurant. The service was excellent and the food was beyond words. We appreciate you, Quinns steakhouse!

Nice restaurant that is accessible through the path and lots of seating. Decent selection of beers and good service. I haven't had a chance to try their steaks yet but the wings were good and would go back.

Been here 2 years in a row for my birthday, and i have not been disappointed. The service is fantastic, and the Apple crumble is amazing! The staff here care for their customers, and their well being - which is not something I've seen at most  bars, especially in the City. Thank you to the bartenders this past Saturday night for the (literal) Cherry on top of my birthday! I'll see you again in September this year, or March 2020! :)
Amazing atmosphere and and good food. Service wasn't the best. Waitress was impatient and rude.
Good service and good food. We had an enjoyable meal in a great atmosphere.

reviews.text: After being offered a position in this new restaurant and having been taken away from a permanent chef job , I was retrenched 1 week short of 3 months. They said they can't afford me. They contacted me to meet them for an interview and made promises that they never kept. They let go most of the original staff including the Head Chef, Assistant General Manager and general Manager. The owner was from Germany and on his visit kept saying I'm doing a great job. Then they gave me notice. Not a good way to treat their staff after we helped setting up the restaurant.  The owner might have a lot of money, but that is not the way to get a good name . I enjoyed working there while it lasted. They just needed staff to help set up the restaurant and after they used us , let most of the staff go. I should never have left my other job. This proof that the grass is not always greener on the other side and never trust what your employer tells you. It is all lies

Long over due review but here it goes.

Came in with a family friend from Taiwan and ordered a ton of dishes to try. The staff picked up on this and even sent us a few "samplers" their chefs whipped up on the house for us - what a nice little treat!

Food speaks for itself (as you can see from all the other reviews, it is excellent) bur really wanted to highlight the service here - the service really pushed this review to a 5 star. Way to go Ricarda's!

The vision behind this experience is inspiring. Thank you for providing 4 generations of my family around a dining table and I, a wonderful afternoon. We delighted in your delectable cuisine that is serendipitously perfect in menu choice, quality and portion. The 3-piece jazz ensemble was intoxicating. Once again, thank you.

Got Sunday brunch today. Excellent service, impressive setting and ambience with lots of space, high ceiling and plenty of natural light. Good supply of a variety of high quality food and drinks. Simply outstanding.

I wish I could really do no stars- but apparently these people lost our reservation of 20 people that we made 1 month prior. Absolutely terible as I was actually excited to go to a place and have a nice meal to enjoy with the kids happy and playing.  
They even had the nerve to charge us more  when their website had clearly stated less for the meal. 
Too good to be true! 
Thank you for ruining our Mother's Day

lic_profile: Rodeo Brazilian Steakhouse offers a unique dining experience that includes an amazing assortment of prepared fresh daily salads on their appetizer table and a wide assortment of perfectly cooked and seasoned meat served Brazilian-style on large skewers. Enjoy an old Brazilian tradition in Toronto surrounded by bosa nova sounds while sipping on delicious lime caipirinhas.

reviews.text: This place was absolutely stupendous! I went for my birthday and the food was scrumptious! The staff was super friendly and accommodating. The food is super high quality and well made. The ambiance is really cool. Really enjoyed my experience at Rodeo. Would definitely come back. 10/10 would recommend.

Absolutely incredible food. They have ~17 types of meat they bring around on skewers and shave some off for you. All tasted absolutely amazing. Very friendly and welcoming staff. 
Salad bar is good but you're cheating yourself out of more meat by eating any of it. 
I went on a weekday so it wasn't busy and they came back often with more food. 

Dessert was a roasted cinnamon pineapple which tasted more like Apple pie than cinnamon. Very good. I highly recommend going here. Although for a weekday dinner it was $48+tax.

What an amazing restaurant.  It's your traditional Brazilian steakhouse.    The food was amazing.  Salad bar was fresh and had a lot of options.   They had a hot bar, cheese station, raw bar, and salads.   There was this amazing portobello mushroom in balsamic and goat cheese side I loved.  
The atmosphere is open with a jazzy feel.  There's a stage where live jazz bands perform.   The staff was really friendly and super attentive.   Great date spot or with a large group.   Don't get for at least a few hours before.   Also don't fill up on salad bar as their meat selections are amazing.   Highly recommend.

Amazing experience. We were 4 on a Sunday night. Food was exceptional all around, drinks were excellent and I don't think I've ever been more full after leaving a restaurant in my life. Our waiter was wonderful as well. What a great experience, I will come back time and time again.

Loved the food 
Loved the service.
Super/Very friendly staffs. üëå EACH AND EVERYONE OF THEM. 

The live band and the dancers were super entertaining and I liked how they were interactive with the their guests. 

You guys rock! Keep up the good work. Will
Definitely go back.

 Firstly, we were greeted in such a lovely manner and escorted to our...
Dined here and was luckily enough to be served by Lydia who was an absolute doll! She is a true professional and made our experience complete. The food was...

My first time here and my experience was great. The food was very tasty and my waitress, Ingrid, was super nice, very knowledgeable, and provided exceptional service. The environment was very relaxing as well. I was surprised to see there were no booths with comfy lounge seats for such a nice place. The tables were pretty basic for the high price of the food. My next visit to this place will be reserved for a very special occasion, only because of the price, but this is definitely my favorite steakhouse.

The restaurant is upscale.  A casual attire feels adequate but you won't feel out of place in a business suit. The food is very good and better than average. The steak is just right. The lobster is done to perfection. The Voodoo shrimp is memorable. It's the kind of restaurant that business people will like to go to. For 2 people, expect a bill of over $300.  Parking was not a problem but I can see it being a issue on a busy day.
Love this place. A bit pricey but you get what you pay for. Delicious steaks and sizzling plates are my favourite. The staff could not be friendlier. Can't wait to go back.
I totally recommend the seafood tower. My streak was over-cooked but still very delicious. they offered to change it and I refused! Cheese cake and chocolate lava was okay but not spectacular

Is there anything anyone could say against this place. I don't think, its simply a 5 star steak house. It was the best i ever eat anyhow. Unfortunately i will probably never go again and was there because my bosses invited me. I cannot spend 85$ for there cheapest Steak and 15$ for an oven potato. Nevertheless it was a great experience.

Buzzing with youthful energy and 90‚Äôs R&B, the space features graffitied walls, funky lighting, and double-height ceilings. The eclectic menu offers a variety of modern Asian sharing plates, each with their own playful flare, as well as an extensive and spirited cocktail list.

reviews.text: An appropriately ambient location that specializes in authenticity and zero tolerance for cutting corners. Staff is highly knowledgeable, well trained and engaging. Meals are prepared quickly and are intended to be shared amongst others. If you're in Toronto, you should visit. Better yet, bring a friend or two. They will thank you later.

We‚Äôve never had a good dish here, because they‚Äôve all been GREAT. The food is phenomenal, as is the service. The only disappointment that amazing dishes get replaced by other amazing dishes on the menu from time to time.

This is a lively happening place with very tasty dishes.  The BBQ Pork bun is my love at first bite.  It's so different from others, light crispy but soft shell with super flavorful fillings.  The Peking duck is so succulent and deliciously different from the traditional version.  Then there is the leg of lamb in a flavor exploding saucy broth together with udon noodles.  What a fantastic combination!  There are so many more items on the menu, I wish my stomach had more room.  Definitely next time!  The staff is well trained for great service.

Nice ambiance. The food is okay. I was seated at the "chef's bar" and was not impressed with the friendliness of the chefs. A friend of mine was literally mocked by the one chef for asking for a piece of bread.

AMAZING!!! Beautiful atmosphere, clean, but most of all DELICIOUS!!! MasterChef judge and winner join forces at this amazing spot. Go here. You will not regret it. This is authentic Chinese food. You will not chicken balls with red sauce here - thankfully!
I haven't had a whole meal here, just the dumplings and they were very decent. I've heard the food is overpriced but I really can't say. Seemed expensive....

They couldn‚Äôt have been more accommodating given that we weren‚Äôt eating on this occasion, and that we had a tiny dog in tow.  Our server Brian was truly exceptional.  Attentive, efficient and charming, and made fast friends with our small canine companion.  We will be back next week ;-)

We had an excellent group dinner. We were in the upstairs dining room which is very spacious, airy and light. Really a great spot.  The food we chose was an assortment of vegetarian and non. Everything was excellent and the service was very attentive.

The scones were my favourite. I had scones a side of creme fraiche and apricot jam. These scones were flaky and buttery. They were so tasty!

The service here was really up to par. I loved the server's patience with our orders and her attentiveness. Excellent brunch spot to hit on the weekend.

I had my bridal brunch here and I absolutely loved it. Its a beautiful restaurant and our hosts were very accommodating and very frierndly. Great service and definitely recommend this for special events!
Portions are incredible especially the lamb! We ordered nearly all of the apps and they were delicious. Very professional and knowledgeable staff. We will definitely come back again.

I arrived here for their weekend brunch looking to try their breakfast menu. The restaurant is quite spacious so we had no problem getting seats.

I ordered...

reviews.text: I have come here for both work functions and individual dates.  The food is quite good and the service is decent.  However, for some reason, whenever I am with a group, we are always seated at table 14 or 15 - by the kitchen which they try to sell as being cool because you watch the mozzarella being made.  However, you have to contend with other patrons coming by and standing by you or knocking your chair because they are watching the mozzarella.  Aside from those tables, I enjoy the restaurant.

I was here recently with my family. I will say the service over all was very helpful, fast and accommodating (we asked to move initially). I had their butternut squash ravioli and it was absolutely delicious. And very filling. I had their charity bread, but it wasn't as good as I remembered it. I wasn't really enjoying the powdered parmesan on top. I also found the location to be very dark. I understand mood lighting is a thing, but a touch more brightness I feel would be slightly more comfortable. But really not that big of a deal at all. I do prefer the charity bread and the ambiance of the Square One location better, though it's been a while since I've been to that location. Over all we enjoyed ourselves and the food was good.

Absolutely amazing fresh pasta. I ordered the gnocchi, and it was the best I have ever had. Everything that we tried was delicious. Even the children's menu items were fantastic. The service was friendly and quick. I cannot recommend it enough.

Great selection of Italian food for lunch. I tried the gnocchi and it was delicious. Their coffee is really good and brewed to order. Very fresh. The restaurant is effortlessly casual. Comfortable place for a quiet lunch and they have space to accommodate big groups as well.

Amazing food. The service is also very good, very friendly.
Loved the green sangria üç∑üç∑!!
I'll definitely go back.

reviews.text: We went in on a child-free date. It was a lovely quiet environment (on a wednesday) with lighting that was perfect. The food was very delicious. Like any...
Great place for having good conversation but agree with most that the food is only average.  In fact, I enjoyed my appertizer (grilled calamari) a lot more...
Went for winterlicious dinner. Food was very sub par especially considering the price. I wish I was exaggerating in saying I'd rather go to McDonald's. Not...
Excellent food. Really recommend it. Only drawback is that it's a bit dead in terms of atmosphere. But it's delicious.

Both times we were there - for dinner and then for breakfast while we stayed at the hotel - it was not busy at all. Lovely environment. Perfect lighting and interesting features to draw the eye. The dinner food was great. The breakfast was pretty ordinary (and hence very overpriced). While we enjoyed it and the convenience of it being right in the hotel (so we didn't have to leave the building at -17¬∞C ) I would not choose to go there for the restaurant itself.

My guest and I accidentally arrived to the restaurant very late due to a misunderstanding (probably an hour or so before closing), but the service was absolutely fantastic and I never felt rushed throughout the meal. Our dinners tasted wonderful, and the calamari was easily one of the best I've ever tried. The restaurant is also beautifully decorated to the point I'd probably return just to eat a meal in their lower lounge area. I also saw that they're apart of Summerlicious this year, so I'm hoping to return for an earlier dinner next time!

Outstanding service - genuinely polite and attentive.  The restaurant is inside the downtown InterContinental Hotel with a choice of indoor and outdoor dining. It was a tough choice as they were both very appealing. We ended up staying indoor and enjoyed the modern and contemporary decor and nice ambience.  Food presentation was good and with just the right portion. Taste was excellent.  $43 per person Summerlicious deal - exceptional value. I would actually pay regular price for that. A very pleasant experience.  5 Star.
The food is amazing and the restaurant is extremely clean and our waiter Thomas was very helpful and nice to us. Would definitely come again.

reviews.text: We came for brunch on a Saturday, and had a good time! We made reservations for 12:30, ended up arriving a 15 minutes early, and were seated...

You can either have the BEST brunch in town, or one that's just mediocre. Continue reading for a breakdown. 


Wait time (Sunday morning 11 am): 20 minutes...

OH MY GOD
Hands down to the best brunch in Toronto, GTA, and maybe Canada!! 
Please try their beef brisket and the blueberry pancakes (which are to die...

I went once a bout 2 years ago and it was fabulous, so I was very very disappointed when I visited on Saturday. I was with a large group, and multiple menu items were sold out by our 830 dinner reservation. I was told that the pasta special was a cream base, so when it arrived and it was tomato based I was very disappointed. It was very bland, and pretty tasteless. I was really really disappointed. The server seemed really sorry for how incredibly long things took, and the fact that everything was sold out. I would suggest that management go over what is in the food with their staff, and make sure that things are available when a 14 person reservation is coming... or just stop offering large reservations to avoid disappointment. Patio is so beautiful, so it is too bad that the food was not good.

This place is spot on! 

The service flowed, the artichoke and calamari appetizers were delicious plus the black bean burger did not disappoint :-).

The yum scale was off the charts for me and my party!

Well done Smith -
Cute little place to go for brunch. Unfortunately was sat outside on a cooler day but was made up for it with decent food. Portions felt small and left hungry, staff were friendly.

We came here for brunch and had the breakfast pancakes and the brisket hash. Both tasted great!  I would definitely recommend this place. The pancakes are different than your standard pancakes and maple syrup, so it's a refreshing change.

Scrumptious brunch spot in the Village. The waitstaff was terrific. I had the hash, and my companion the chicken sandwich. Both were good, though the portions were over large. The cinnamon bun was perfect!

reviews.text: We absolutely loved it. First we wanted to have dinner at Sidebar but the waiter was so rude there so we just left and came across Soulas. Frome outside it looked good so we decided to give it a try and absolutely loved it. Awesome service, delicious food and fresh vegetables. The calamari was the best we ever had. Live music. Absolutely 5 star.
Great food served in very generous portions. Nice quiet music, you can actually talk with your company! Friendly staff and owner make sure your visit is pleasant. Would recommend.

We have always had a great meal here but especially if Soula is there, you are in for a real treat. She always remembers you and makes you feel as if she has been waiting for you. Welcoming, traditional home style Greek food with a contemporary flair.

The ambiance and service was good. However the orzo pasta that came with the Lamb shank had an excessive amount  of Tomato sauce. The vegetable moussaka was primary mashed and chunked potatoes loaded  with Tomato sauce. Tomatoes are in season and the chef was generous with them!

Soula creates a great atmosphere anywhere! Great business woman that I've known for 20 years! The entrainment was a live Greek band and a belly dancer. The ambiance was amazing! Decor like you wouldn't imagine. Very stunning place to visit. Very welcoming place that offers great food, great drinks, great atmosphere which all lead to a great time! Couldn't have asked for better service! Will visit again very soon. My date and I were very impressed üëç
Welcoming staff and excellent cuisine. Came here with my mom on a Friday evening. I was thankful I made a reservation since the place was full - a good sign...
We sat out on the patio and it was nice but the plates were dirty from maybe the planted flowers so good thing the plates were turned over. We had two...
Came here on a weeknight and it wasn't too busy. This place used to be PAN and they changed the name. The dinners are on the pricier side but the portions...

reviews.text: Southern Accent is great fun!  The restaurant recently relocated to College & Ossington and brought its New Orleans flavour with it!  They have awesome whiskey tastings on occasion where customers can come in for a lesson in great whiskeys!  On Tuesdays, they have a psychic in-house that can do a 10 min reading for $20 (& the great thing is that they'll just add it to your bill!)  The food is tasty and fun!  The decor is eclectic and colorful!  A good date spot!  Definitely a great night out!

Great ambiance and vibes, fantastic service. The calamari was - eh... (I‚Äôm super picky about my calamari though). The mains were not bad, really liked the sauce for the shrimp grits but overall meal felt a bit heavy. The jambalaya was good but the Cajun chicken was what made it pop, too bad we only got two pieces. It was definitely a hearty meal.

Very nice restaurant with a very nice decoration great food and service. Looking from outside it looks more like a normal bar restaurant but nce you get in, the bar has a very cozy ambient while the dinning room is on the back with a superb decoration. Food tastes very fresh and the menu got a lot of options ... The Jambalaya I had was amazing! The house hot sauces will gave a special kick! Drinks from the bar are very well made with a very nice presentation! Highly recommend a visit...

My top 3 favorite restaurants in Toronto. Still miss their previous location on Markham St (RIP honest Ed's era), but they kept their atmosphere and great food. Love their sauses and cook book I bought there.
Hot Stuff! Not a lot of options,  if you go as a group.. someone is going to go hungry. If you all love the Cajun go for it!

While I miss the charm of the older location and all the history and memories made there, what can we do? The Honest Ed's block got sold. 

The new location...

Gord and I had supper this evening at Southern Accent.
