Follow-up review:
The team went to Speakeasy today, to give the restaurant another chance, and we were all very pleased!
- Our server was very attentive
- The food was delivered promptly
- Everybody was happy with their order
Big thank you to Harry for the follow-up!

Original review:
Incredibly slow! After we were seated for lunch (on a weekday), a server took our drink orders and we got those after a normal wait time. But we waited another 20 mind for our food orders to be taken. It was another 30+ minutes until our food arrived.
Uniformly, the food was no more than decent.
Servers were all smile-free, and you'd be hard-pressed to call them "service-oriented".
The place was certainly not full. So no excuses.
Do not waste time here...

Industrial chic meets retro pub vibe, tucked away in the financial core. Excellent, attentive service from pleasant servers. Good beer selection, however they're best known for their cocktails. 

Food wise, we only ordered shareables. Kitchen was efficient, which turned out to be handy because it was so good we ordered seconds! That deep fried mac and cheese... *heaven*

My coworkers and I often end up here for drinks and we've never been disappointed. The drink menu is extensive and everything I've tried so far has been amazing! The atmosphere is a little dark, however it's not a huge deterrent. Highly recommend!

A little pricey, but the food was great - had the turkey burger and it was delicious. Too bad I couldn't say the same thing about the service - took the waitress about 10 minutes after we sat down for her to even notice us and that was after we asked her if we could order something.

APRIL 2019 - I went back again (the food was delicious) and the service was completely different than my first visit.  Emma, our waitress was very friendly, down to earth and made us feel very welcome. The food was delicious. Had the turkey burger (again), as well as the corn fritters and fried mac and cheese (both apps) and they were fabulous.  I would definitely return, if not for the service, for the food.

Had never been inside before, but had to make last minute reservations and we weren't able to get a table on the patio. 
The interior is a bit underwhelming, and while it'll still satisfy your craving for a cold beer after work on a Friday, it doesn't really differentiate itself much from the other options in the area.

Definitely a busy place to go for after work drinks - it's packed!  It's located in the financial district, in the Scotiabank building plaza.

reviews.text: I can't say enough amazing things about this place!! I had my wedding after party here - reserved 4 booths - and when I say that Charisse pulled out all the stops - this girl made the evening at STK for our group. She made sure our tables were ready - set up - the high energy - and the sparklers on the drinks - just wow. The music was bomb that evening too! Had everyone dancing. She made sure from the months prior that we were organized and always informed. We had a fairly large party and many of my guests expressed how this was the best wedding after party they had ever attended. Don't think twice about booking your special event - it's got something for everyone and with Charisse, you're in good, capable hands. She'll go over and beyond for her clients. If I could give more than 5* I would.

Love the happy hour specials and the vibe here. Great for grabbing drinks with girlfriends after work. Service is excellent, the bartender came to check on how we liked our drinks and could tell I didn‚Äôt really enjoy mine (nothing wrong but it just too sour for my taste) so he replaced it at no charge.
Beautiful decor and great ambiance. Big size martini, delicious strip steak with sides of mashed potato and Brussels sprouts with bacon. Everything was perfect. Very high quality! A must!

The food was excellent and our server was lovely. The atmosphere was a bit busy for my taste. Everyone seemed a bit run off their feet. Overall a nice dining experience, all the seafood was fresh tasting and delicious. Funny enough no one got a steak lol.

A few friends and I wanted a fun place to celebrate a birthday and I‚Äôm so glad we were able to get a table. The atmosphere is awesome for a group setting especially if you are looking you have a fun night out. We had a wonder waitress named Amanda who took care of us all night and made some great recommendations for entires. The food was fantastic, the truffle fries are a must. Overall great experience and highly recommend, I‚Äôll be going back.

reviews.text: What a great little gem of a restaurant! Warm and welcoming, the food is delicious and the flamenco performances, out of this world!  Can't wait to go back!

One of the best Paella I've ever had. Paella is hard to get the flavours right and not make it too bland or overly salty and this place did it right, it was perfectly seasoned, meat was moist, seafood was well cooked and I really loved the crispy bits of the rice stuck on the bottom of the pan that you can scrape up. I also really loved their appetizer of bacon wrapped date with honey, I could eat a handful of those and still want more. They've also got some great cheese and meat charcuterie boards and some delicious red sangria. They've also got live entertainment on certain days and all they ask is if each person spends a minimum of $30 which I think is very reasonable for authentic and delicious food and entertainment of Flamenco dancing.
What a gem of a place! Cozy ambiance,  great, friendly service and  delicious food! To top it off you get an amazing Flamenco show! Loved it!

I can't say enough good things about this place! The food is delicious and timed perfectly. The atmosphere transports you to Spain but the incredible Flamenco dancing will take your breath away and leave your heart full. Highly recommended.

OMG! I ABSOLUTELY recommend this place for a date. I've been in Barcelona and in Other (pricier) Spanish restaurants in Toronto. Although I had some good experiences elsewhere, I felt usually let down by something. Embrujo, on the other hand, consistently gets it right; great wine, fabulous sangria, best paella I've ever had, good coffee and fabulous desserts. They have a WONDERFUL life flamenco show (check the hours!). I've been going to Embrujo on special occasions and to celebrate anniversaries for the past 3 years and have NEVER been disappointed and to top it all up...the prices are also quite reasonable!!!

lic_profile: The Carbon Bar offers southern-inspired fare and cocktails in a casual space inspired by the storied past of a rock 'n' roll discotheque, an upstart TV station and media giant's studio. It's the place where fun loving aficionados, gourmands and bon vivants meet to share snacks, plates and platters delivered with impeccable hospitality.

reviews.text:
I absolutely love the ambiance here. The cocktails are INSANELY delicious and they usually take on classics with a unique spin. Staff is always amazing! 

The only reason I didn't leave 5 stars is because I was a little disappointed with my Lobster Roll when I was in last week. The lobster itself was cooked beautifully, I just think if you're going to price it at $48, it shouldn't be 70% bun and 30% lobster meat. I just ended up wanting more meat, with a slightly less-dense bun. I probably wouldn't order it again, but as it's a BBQ-centric restaurant, I should've just ordered the platter like I have every other time before and enjoyed tremendously because they do meat VERY well. Not to say they can't do seafood - my Argentinean shrimp was delicious, as were the oysters, and another person in my party ordered a fish dish and seriously contemplated licking the plate. 

All in all, it's an amazing place to come with a group, or even on a date. Would definitely recommend!

Great upscale barbecue with a twist. Best Manhattan I've had in ages and great craft beer on tap. Love the industrial but somehow cozy interior. Can't say enough about the great service. Keep up the good work.

Carbon Bar is a great place for dinner with friends. The atmosphere is amazing and it has an upscale but relaxed vibe. The drinks were all amazing and I particularly enjoyed their Old Fashioned. The prix fixe menu is actually a great value, especially if everyone at the able orders. Our waiter made sure that we had a huge variety of dishes and the 6 people at dinner could not finish all the food we were brought. The staff was very attentive without intruding on conversation or interupting. I will definitely be returning again for some more of their delicious food.

Food is fantastic. Make sure you go on a cheat day. Lots of meat and amazing sides. Go with friends and do the Pit Master Platter to enjoy a bit of everything. Love this place. Cocktails are awesome too.

Came for a bachelor party. The dinner was excellent. Service was exceptional with a private room. Staff were helpful and receptive. There was even a Mussolini style balcony inside the actual restaurant for the private room. Food was better than casual, smoked/BBQ cuisine dishes; drink menu was vast for the whiskey assortment. I recommend for a special occassion for guys and girls if classy, but not formal, is desired.
Update: we went back last night. Same great service. Same great food. My bf was disappointed the Mac and Cheese was off the menu but we tried the croc...

Service was amazing. Space was quite open and lots of room. Recommend making resos ahead of time.

Reservations were made in advance, but was...

The Chase is a nice beach-side style restaurant in the heart of downtown Toronto. The decor reminded me of sea side brunch restaurants in Miami. Ultimately, this is offset by the heavy corporate vibe that emanates from every corner. Not surprised as clearly this restaurant is well situated in the financial district.

The service was okay, if a bit abrupt. Not overly friendly, or professional as they were just hanging around in a corner when it wasn't so busy. When it was finally time for our waiter to take our order, the responses were short and abrupt. Not very welcoming. Our waiter even forgot our appetizer.

The food was very good. Albeit, a bit overpriced, but that's the premium you pay for dining where you dine. I wouldn't be surprised if most of the clientele pay via company credit card as opposed to personal funds, which is what allows them to charge more. Oysters were fresh and delicious, and the cashew goat cheese is a must have for any and all cheese lovers.

Overall, the pricing and the service is what brought this place down from a five star. If service was outstanding, I wouldn't mind making this a five star, as the food quality can justify and support the pricing.

I have been here twice, both times were for dinner. It is one of my top three fine dining choices in Toronto. The staff are all amazing. 

I had dinner with a couple of family members the other night. At first we were seated at a table right across from the kitchen. It was a bit loud. At the same time the restaurant was packed and I was not sure if they could move us. One of the managers, Ester, was absolutely amazing in finding us a cozy corner table and made the world of difference in our experience. She checked on us a few minutes after we moved to our new table. Our server, Maven (I hope I remember her name right) was absolutely phenomenal. The other staff were also fantastic. The food was delicious (I must say I liked the dishes I from my previous visit more). All in all, the service and courtesy they provide at the Chase is exemplary.

Thank you to Ester, Maven and the other staff whom I did not get a chance to ask their name.

Great place for a fine dinner, oysters and wine. If you‚Äôre a beer or whiskey person, this is not your best bet. The place has a cool rooftop as well with enough space in the ground floor to host private events too. The oysters were very fresh and the tuna ceviche added that extra zing next to it. All in all, a recommended spot for both a date and a semi formal outings.

Ive been here twice now, both times for dinner. The most recent visit was for my best friends birthday which they helped make really fabulous. We ordered oysters which both times were really great and super fresh. As well as we ordered the steamed mussells & grilled octopus which was incredible. For seafood, this is my favourite location in the city. The service is impeccable as well. I look forward to dining here again.

Great service, great food and the roof top area has a good view of downtown.  Recommend checking out the food here! Get ready to drop some $$ though because their prices are high. Also there's vallet parking available so be prepared for that as asking around here isn't the greatest. 
There's also a bar here wide a selection of drinks!

reviews.text:
Pros: As someone who doesn't eat Indian food often, I thought the food tasted great. It's not too spicy so you can actually taste the flavours underneath. The fish curry was my favourite. The staff seem friendly and patient.

Cons: It took forever to get our food (~1 hour), and our server didn't come around often enough (we sat in the patio). A few times through the meal we had to go inside to find a server ourselves.

Probably would just order takeout from here next time.

I have been to the other location in Mississauga a few times, and always enjoyed dining there. This location (even though smaller) was no different, and actually service was better here (which is not quite there in the Missiausaga location, though still satisfactory). The food is amazing, with decent quantity per serving. Everything we ordered was great; this was probably first time eating Indian Cuisine for some people in the group, but everyone loved the food. Location is great and ambiance is very cozy. One thing that I would advice the management would be, to renovate/ clean up the approach to washrooms (looked very run down), but washrooms were clean, so no issues there. We were a big group, stayed there for a good amount of time, and were not rushed to order or to pay, which was appreciated. However, this was on a Wednesday, so need to go back during a busy time around weekends to see if the experience remains the same. Will definitely be going back!

This has been my second visit to The Host. The first one being in Markham. The quality of food and service is great. I would recommend place for Indian fine dine. Their prices are reasonable for the quality. Thank you for hosting us well The Host.

reviews.text: Ordered lunch through Ritual. Originally I was told that it would be 20-25 min., which is cool, at least I continue working until it was ready. Then five min later I received a message from the Office Pub saying good news, your order will be ready sooner, only 10 min. So I go to pick it up at the designated time and there is only one server running around and only one cook. I waited 10-15 min . before the server even asked my name for the pickup. And when she brought it to me it was the original time (20-25 min) so why bother telling me to pick it up sooner? She then made an excuse that she was the only one there, and there was only one person in the back....how is that my problem? Just don't tell me to come earlier then to sit there and be ignored. This was my first time ordering from The Office Pub with the intention of possibly doing a few office functions there, but given my first experience I think I will pass. I gave it two stars because my chicken pesto wrap and salad was good, so I'll give them that.

Very clean, very nice atmosphere. Even on a game night with one server (who was also on bar) we were regularly attended. Fried food could've used an extra thirty seconds in the deep fryer but very tasty nonetheless.

A great pub I've been to multiple times, the servers are a bit dismissive and less friendly than the other Office Pub location, but overall you'll have a good experience here. 

Good beer selections, TVs all over so this place which is great for watching sports, and it doesn't feel camped. The wings at this location are also very good.
This location is great. It gets busy but not too packed. Karaoke is so much fun, and the food is good too! Cheap drinks on the weekend.

First time going to The Office Pub on King.  I enjoyed most of the dishes, staff were friendly, and it was kept tidy.  -2 stars for not having all of the dishes on the menu available.  My table ordered 2 different dishes, and 1 drink from the menu that they didn't have.  Also, when we finally chose a meal they could make, they made substitutions without informing us.

Went last night for a birthday dinner. Absolutely amazing food...chef and the team are clearly committed to quality food and flavours. Drink menu is expansive. Definitely give this place a shot, you won't regret it!

Amazing brunch, outstanding service! We loved the cozy atmosphere, and they happily accommodated a baby with a high chair. Every single thing on the menu is delicious and unique. Eggs poached perfectly, vodka smoked salmon was the best. Would come back again and again!
Love the patio hideout. Unexpected menu from the diner. Great service. Good food. Robust variety of beer. No complains.
Great food and great service! I went here for brunch and the flavour of the frites is phenomenal - the onions are a perfect add-in. The patio in the back is a quaint little space. Highly recommend!

reviews.text: Went here for my wife‚Äôs birthday. Cool place and tasty food. Dishes were little bit too simple for the price.

Fantastic meal and excellent service.  My steak was cooked perfectly.

Note, their crab cake is not the best.  Texture was similar to a overcooked hamburger.

I have loved oysters and shrimp for quite a long time and so while staying overnight on my own before an excellent presentation by Fidelity Investments at Roy Thomson Hall I decided to cross the road having heard they had a happy hour special. Buck a shuck oysters and $2 jumbo shrimp. Enough said. It was OUTSTANDING!!! I will make this my next stop when in TO and also look at what they offer for dinner too. If it is anything near the service and quality that I found yesterday then they have a fan for life.

Shoutout to server Liz and server from Newcastle, they are amazing. Decor invokes the elegance of elite lounges with a modern twist; leading to a gracious and relaxed atmosphere. One of my favorite places to 'think' or be with friends and clients. The food is excellent. Happy hour outstanding. Not sure how they do it.

Love this place, has a great happy hour special. Thursday night service from both the hostesses and servers is awesome, would highly recommend to anyone looking for a fantastic hangout place with yummy oysters and wine!

Came here during the happy hour, which they serve oysters for $1 each and prawns for $2 each. 

They have the biggest oysters I've ever seen... Big and...
Great service, meh drinks and food.  Our waitress was wonderful and very attentive.  However, the food was sub-par.  The filet was delicious, but the fried...

reviews.text: I wish I had come before! I've heard good things for years, and it was fantastic, even on a quiet, rainy Wednesday evening. Enjoyed our anniversary dinner as well as joining in the belly dancing show. Food is fantastic and a wonderful staff. Worth every penny.

WOW, what an evening! I cannot express how overly impressed I was by our overall experience yesterday evening. From the moment we arrived to the moment we left, the customer service provided by EVERYONE was exceptional - incredible attention to detail, ensuring that my friend‚Äôs birthday celebration was perfect. We were served by Anton, who continuously went out of his way to guarantee we had a great time. Beautiful decor, spacious and comfy eating areas, welcoming and helpful staff, friendly belly dancer who let our birthday girl dance with her, delicious food, exemplary customer service - there was REALLY nothing more we could have asked for! 

Thank you to everyone at this establishment, your efforts were not in vain!!

I had my birthday dinner at this restaurant last night and to say it was amazing is an understatement. From the moment we walked in, we were kindly greeted and our coats and bags were comfortably stored in coat check. Our waiter Anton was absolutely wonderful. Form providing delicious dinner suggestions, to mouth-watering drinks, and finally exquisite desserts, he completely elevated our dining experience. The rest of the staff on site were also extremely gracious and welcoming to our party, checking in appropriately to see if we had all we needed to enjoy the food and the show.

And last but not least, the belly dancing was unbelievable. The dancer we had was so hypnotizing. She was extremely skilled and so entertaining. She brought me up for a chance to move like her and it was the highlight of my night. I wish I could give this restaurant more than 5 stars because I was significantly pleased. I will be back again, without hesitation.

Great food, excellent service. Very friendly staff. Good for group of people and also for couples. Like the belly dancing show. It brings a little taste of Morocco. Over all great feel. Service is quick and servers are so nice. They help you with the menu. Love the sitting area.

Amazing experience! We went there for the Saturday 3 course meal and it was a beautiful service. Everything from the food, the belly dance performance, the staff, the servers, the manager, everyone was well mannered, very polite and very friendly. The food was so delicious that we definitely over stuffed ourselves :). Little touches like the complimentary Moroccan tea at the end of the meal were very thoughtful. The ambiance was cozy and very welcoming. Definitely going there again, soon!! Well worth the price and very well maintained!!!

I came here for winterlicious with a friend. We haven't had Moroccan cuisine before so we were both interested in trying it. 
The decor of this restaurant...

The atmosphere is lovely and that's about it. The food was mediocre at best and it was warm'ish when served.

Had an amazing time only because of the...

The drinks are good, with plenty of selection for a beer, cocktail, or wine lover. The food selection is also impressive, although they could improve the quality in some respects. Overall a fun place to spend a few hours.

Delicious cocktails!
I recommend asking what the special of the day is as they are quite creative and taste great.
The food was good and for a reasonable price.
Will definitely come again!

This is a really elevated on experience. The burger is incredible, it's like they ground a rib eye or something to make it. Incredibly flavorful. Looking forward to creating excuses to go back and try more of the menu and taps. Salivating writing this review üòâ

The food is really good. We had the handchoped burger (which they cook as rare as you like) and all components of that dish were delicious, the fries, the burger and the homemade ketchup. We also had the braised beef on horseradish mash and it was absolutely delicious. The ambience is nice, we sat at the bar. Some cool decor. Nice selection of beers on tap. The only downside is that it get pretty loud when it's busy.

Amazing place for a drink. Place has nice sitting and great bar for drinks. It has a huge list of beers from all over the country and also many imported beers.

On rotation they have different beers on tap which is amazing to try different beers from the city.

Also the pricing is also quite good compared to other places nearby.

Have not tried any food but heard its good there.

reviews.text:
Sunday brunch is one of the best in the city. Huge selection of foods and bottomless mimosas. Very beautiful ambiance and atmosphere. You can spend a few hours here on a Sunday enjoying with friends. It is a buffet style selections include: omlete bar, seafood bar, meats, cheeses, deserts, pancakes, and more. 

Warning: this does not apply to brunch on Saturdays which I found to be average. You should definitely book a few days in advance as the Sunday brunch usually sells out.

Not great service, fairly average food, tiny portions (I've never complained about portions at any restaurant before). Plus, as an added bonus we got to witness the chef, manager and others swarm the table of 2 next to us all while our server vanished. I had to interrupt the chef's patronizing and ask him to move so that I could find our bottle of wine and refill our glasses. He seemed like it was an inconvenience. We're guests at the hotel and it is quite nice. Toca less so.

went there at 5 pm for dinner with a friend. I had the wild mushroom soup and the ribeye. My friend had the filet and a beet salad. We finished with a  3 cheese plate. The steak was very tasty and the side of mushrooms had lots of flavour. The steak was mid rare with a very tasty crust. Service was very good. I was not a fan of the chairs. There was no where to rest your arms, they were not soft and comfy. I like a very comfy chair when I dine. I would go back and try the pasta next time.

Delicious food and presentation - the signature ravoli is a must try! 

The staff is incredibly friendly and accommodating. An overall, excellent experience and we will definitely be coming back!

Thank you Toca!
Decent brunch. Not sure if it was worth it for the price but the environment is good for say a nice brunch with one's mom or grandma
All your can eat brunch before Mother's Day. I love how much oysters that we can have plus unlimited mimosas. The oysters aren't as big but is super fresh....
I came here last week for a birthday brunch- and let's just say it definetly did not live up to all these positive reviews. In all fairness, I went on a...
Ok, so this place is not a 4. But it's not perfect either. But it's definitely not a 4. Are grace marks allowed? Can we bump up the score out of generosity?...

reviews.text: I came here for lunch on a Tuesday afternoon and the weather was amazing so the view was incredible.  We were seated at the window seats facing the lake...
My friends and I arrived during a rainy evening so the view wasn't the best looking from the 36th floor. Upon arrival, we were greeted by two friendly girls...

Decided to give this restaurant a try with my two friends after finding this restaurant on the app Pepper. 
Upon arriving I made reservations to sit at the...

Stopped by while in Toronto. The view of the city at night was awesome. Service was great and I enjoyed my dinner. Love Italian wines and selection was very good compared to some other places in the area. Will definitely recommend and will be back. Was definitely worth the price.

The ambience of the restaurant and views of the city were phenomenal! I recently had a large group dinner for a special occasion and I had the best time. The service was great, the chef came out to introduce himself to the table. I had a 6 course meal and was very impressed. My favorite dishes were the lamb and the halibut paired with the red wine. I will absolutely come back! 10/10

Recently attended a tasting of the upcoming menu. Everything was excellent. Dishes were plated well, and the food was outstanding. The Gnocchi was exceptional. The staff was very accommodating with our large party.

Views from the restaurant are some of the best in the city. 

If you're in the area, or are planning a function, definitely consider Toula..

The views are amazing. Watch the ferries back and forth to the island or the airplanes land at Billy Bishop. The food was good. Friendly service. Note the restaurant does not rotate or didn't when I was there.

Toula is a beautiful restaurant with breathtaking views located on the 38 floor of the Western Harbour Castle. I attended as a guest for a birthday dinner. As a vegetarian I typically am limited on the selections and variety of options, and was anticipating that however even with the tasting menu, the chef was able to accommodate. Surprisingly the food was delicious and plated in an aesthetically pleasing manner! I loved everything from the elegance, to the views of the CN tower/lakefront, to the food and the service. Absolutely breathtaking views at sunset! The only downside is that you need to take the stairs and go down a level for the bathroom. Otherwise my evening was perfect. I can‚Äôt wait to go back.

We went to the Trio Restaurant for Saturday dinner. Trio Restaurant is located in the Novotel hotel. The dining room is beautifully decorated. The...

The general ambience of Trio is kind of relaxed. Seems like a place to meet up with a colleague. I actually went there for winterlicious this year and found the food okay. The appetizers and entree were good but felt like it was missing something. However the cannolis were amazing! The servers were pleasant as well. Cocktails were pretty mediocre.

Probably the grossest breakfast buffet I‚Äôve ever seen. All the plates were filthy. Had to ask for replacements, which were still not that great.

Fruit was all shrivelled and way past edible. Hot items were luke warm and stale like they were cooked two days ago. Ended up eating a piece of Nutella toast and paid $20. Don‚Äôt waste your time here.

Would not recommend. Food was tasteless and horrible. Terrible staff. The server had to come back to ask what we, table of two, ordered TWICE. When food arrived, it was "dropped off" like a fast food restaurant rather than placed down and stating which dish is which. FISH WAS VERY DRY AND TASTELESS. Highly suggest to just eat around the area and avoid this restaurant.

After reading mixed reviews about the restaurant, I hoped that winterlicious menu would make the difference. And my hopes never came true. The soup wasn't hot, spicy shrimp with brown rice lacked brown rice (the white was there instead), mahi mahi with crabmeat wasn't even close to expectations: the fish was very dry and tasteless and crabmeat was hidden somewhere as a a great partisan! And similar disappointments with desert: cr√®me br√ªl√©e was overcooked and chocolate lava cake was mostly dry. The first ever disappointing winterlicious experience. You probably should stay away from hotel restaurants in general (unless you stay at the hotel, of course, or if it's a Ritz-Carlton or similar).

reviews.text: We love everything about this restaurant, including the food and the staff. Although the restaurant fills to near capacity due to the Toronto Opera House next door, we we were treated as if we were the only patrons. We celebrated our 20th anniversary tonight at Tundra because my wife loves this restaurant... and it's clear why. Can't recommend enough.

Love the breakfast buffet here, the overall vibe is a subdued relaxed lounge, it's a nice accessible place but not much life to it. Often you'll not be seated as the host is typically missing, it also may take some time before you're greeted or served. Overall it's lacking in customer service, the staff seem unhappy. However the sliders are unique as they're made with thinly sliced slow cooked barbecue roast beef, topped with coleslaw and served on a brioche bun. If you're looking for customer service there are other places close by. This location is however, accesible via the PATH.

It was roughly  1:40pm, I work in finance on Bay Street and I was at the hotel for a conference... the Bank of Canada‚Äôs Lynn Patterson was presenting that afternoon at 2pm and I was early so I took a seat at the Tundra bar to wait 10mins before walking in to my meeting... the waitress approached and asked if I wanted something  and I said no I‚Äôm waiting a few minutes for... before I could finish she cut me off and said ‚Äúwell this is a bar sir, so sorry no you can‚Äôt wait‚Äù and she walked away before I could respond. I stood up and left... this is a very pretentious place because of how she acted in my opinion and I feel I got that response because I‚Äôm black and it didn‚Äôt look like I fit in. Didn‚Äôt matter that I was in a suit or anything... this is often the experience as a black man in Toronto in these types of places... you‚Äôre treated like a second class citizen. The workers here need to be trained to get rid of their biases in my opinion... this wouldn‚Äôt have happened if it was an older white or Asian male in a suit... you know what I mean... anyway that‚Äôs my two cents on this place. Cheers!
Food was great. Price a bit high. Staff simply excellent. Friendly and attention to detail. Quinn and Jason are fantastic waiters!
Great bar! Singer is good. Great service

reviews.text: Great service and delicious food. Authentic pizza and flavourful gnocchis. The staff is friendly and professional, the food came out quickly. Great atmosphere for a bite and the music very nice. Several parking options nearby even right in front.

Way too expensive over $80.00 for 2 for LUNCH and it wasn't worth it. My husband had 1 beer and I drank water.  No coffee or dessert. 1 appetizer and 2 lunch mains. Service left a lot to be desired. We weren't even informed that there was a lunch special.  We walk by here all the time and always find it not busy....now we know why and we won't be returning anytime soon.

reviews.text: Amazing night at Ufficio! Shared the grass fed steak, lentil risotto, and octopus with friends and everything was a total hit. Also, the oysters were so fresh and delicious and the service was exceptional.
Fantastic seafood here. The rainbow trout is by far the best I have ever had. Great atmosphere and service is on point. Definitely recommend.

Words cannot describe. I am still in awe. Take a moment to ponder your life and consider where you want it to be. Call destiny, reserve fate, set partner's friend's' and your own hopes of the attainment of this goal, because this is where you want to be. You'll know it, you'll live it. Also yes parking is available no worries.

I‚Äôm looking forward to coming back to Ufficio to have a full service experience. I joined a small dinner party most of the way through their evening. The $1 Raspberry Point Oysters were delicious, and my friends dishes looked amazing, but a bit pricy for the size. The lone ‚Äúhalf priced wine‚Äù of the night was a special treat. Delicious & crushable. 
However a shallow $17/glass pour of another wine left me thirsty for more after my tasty snack. So we ventured elsewhere for another swirl. I will be back to dive deeper at Ufficio soon. A fun & chic dundas west location with lots of potential, and very likely to impress all those who look for great Toronto dining experiences.

reviews.text:
Marco is the best! Their food is amazing. They now cater our lunches at work and it was a success! Eating at the restaurant is a whole other experience, at dinner time I ordered their special lamb and prawn dish and I was blown away. The employees are also very well mannered, informative, and always make the best suggestions if you don't know what to get. If you are looking for a quality Italian dine-in experience this is the best place in Toronto! All the recipes are also 100% authentic. Make sure you try Marco's special hot sauce!
-Shawn L.

Love the food and the customer service is excellent. We‚Äôve seen events here like the painting parties and thought it‚Äôs a good use of the space. We like their calamari, pizza choices and pasta. They have a good selection of wines as well. Check them out.

Had our staff Christmas party here. Pleasant staff but very cramped space with lousy sight lines. Food was okay but we didn't get fed until almost 11:00 pm which was way too late. Not a venue for a large group. They couldn't provide a proper food/party experience. I wouldn't go back even with it friend or two. There is better food and service in the city for half the price.

Came for a date night. Big space with plenty of seating but it still managed to feel private. Large, tasty portions (had the mushroom risotto and the carbonara). Attentive service without feeling bothered. We'll be back!

We came here for a late dinner and literally just had the absolutely best experience here. All the servers were more than attentive, and the manager let us change to music (as it was our anniversary) and accommodated us on multiple occasions and was so kind about it.

Further, we both ordered different pastas and they were both delicious. Perfect for the price point. So impressed and feel totally catered to. 

Fantastic. Highly, highly recommend.

lic_profile: Contemporary, chic and offering an intimate community vibe, Veloute Bistro is located in the heart of the Beach. Veloute follows the terroir farm-to-table slow food movement using locally sourced ingredients. Having achieved the level of Saucier and French cuisine at the Paris Marriott Hotel Champs-Elysees, Chef Fawzi Kotb's menu is designed to inspire and challenge the most discerning palate. Sommelier Alise Matos can help you select from the extensive wine list for the perfect complement to every dish.  Alternatively, feel free to bring your own bottle.

reviews.text: Superb fine dining in a quiet atmosphere. Food is well prepared and tasty. Our part had fish, lobster and pasta and it was all great. Service is professional and a nice touch to have chef come out to ask if we were enjoying our meal. Definitely worth a visit

I went on a friend's recommendation. I am so glad I did! Fabulous food, served with style and great hospitality. Everything was lovely, and for a high end restaurant, very reasonable as well.  I will DEFINITELY be going back.

Visit every year when I go to the Beaches Jazz Festival-always have a fantastic menu and every entree I've had has been phenomenal!! Service is amazing and thoughtful. Even put a napkin on the ground for my purse!!

We've dined in at Veloute and it never fails to disappoint. This weekend, we tried something different and had our family's Easter Dinner catered. It was FANTASTIC! We ordered two different mains (duck and chicken) - both were beautifully prepared and delicious. The sides were equally terrific. While dining in at Veloute is always a treat (the service is excellent), the catering option is now definitely on our list of things to be repeated. Many thanks for a wonderful meal Chef Fawzi!

I am local to this restaurant and I certainly can't say that I moved here to be close to it but I'm thrilled to have discovered it once I did move here. The food is inventive and exquisite the management clearly are engaged with their clients. I hope to be a regular visitor to this wonderful culinary experience.

My favourite restaurant!!! Period! Love you Chef Fawzi and Elise!! We always look forward to dining at your fine establishment! 

-V & Jordan xo

Most items on the menu are $20+ and I don‚Äôt understand why... Banking off the office crowds it seems.

lic_profile: Weslodge offers an eclectic take on the classic neighbourhood bar and grill experience.  The menu explores globally inspired cuisine with a focus on North America's favourites while the cocktail program is known for drinks that are classically rooted but adventurously reinterpreted.

reviews.text: We were walking by this restaurant and decided to try it. The service was pretty good, our sever came by to take our drink orders and then took out food orders. We ordered the lamb shoulder, a burger with fries, a scotch egg, a steak with mac and cheese and the fish and chips. We noticed that the food order was taking a while and so did our server, he came over to us to apologize for the wait before we asked him about what was taking so long. We waited about 45-50 minutes for our food which, sad to say, was definitely not worth the wait and the prices we paid for them. The lamb ($55) was on the under seasoned and under salted which was a big let down as this was the dish that held up the rest of the orders. The burger($18) was really salty and each mouthful needed to be followed by a sip if water. The meat of the scotch egg($8 single egg) tasted slightly on the sour side (not because it was seasoned that way). The steak was a little cold even though it came out on a hot plate, it was also served with "barbecue" sauce, which was really just ketchup with a little chili powder in it, the mac and cheese was pretty decent though. And lastly, the fish($22) was actually pretty good, crunchy on the outside and flaky on the inside, but the fries were way too over salted, and I found myself needing to have a sip of water after every mouthful of them. Had we not already waited an hour, we would have complained to the management, but we were already there for too long and decided it wasnt worth it anymore. The music was also too loud, we had to yell across the table to make sure that we could be heard. Definitely won't be coming back here again.

We have taken clients here on a few occassions in recent years and always enjoy our time. The service has been good as well as the food and drinks. I would recommend others try it out if you haven't done so already.
Came here for a very late dinner. Steak was excellent and the drinks were plentiful. Decor is amazing, takes you out of the downtown core for a moment.

Honestly had the time of my life here.  Great staff. Great service. Great food. And the music the DJ was playing had me in shock with every song because I actually liked them all. 10 stars if I could. Request Eva as your server if she‚Äôs available. She‚Äôs the best!!

reviews.text:
Had a fantastic dinner experience! Second visit here, they have a delicious steak menu, seafood, and daily chef special. I ordered the elk steak (done rare) and it was DELICIOUS, Wow one of the best steaks I've had!! 
Also, did you know if you are on the Wildfire mailing list, you get a coupon for your birthday and they offer a free New York cheesecake! Thank you for the excellent service and making birthday girl feel special!!  Looking forward to coming back.

A very average alternative to other well known chain steakhouses

Dined with friends at this newer chain restaurant which like its larger chain competitors focuses on steaks while offering enough alternatives to keep those who don't like steak well fed. The room, again like its primary competitor, is dark but absent either the contemporary charm of the larger chain or the intimacy of higher end steak houses. Service though slow and challenged with several errors made was courteous and friendly, and the delays and mistakes were each acknowledged and addressed. The food was unfortunately very average. The crab cakes resembled flattened pucks; the exteriors were breaded and the interiors unfortunately lacked texture and resembled a crab paste. Our friends enjoyed the French onion soup. The steaks were competently prepared, but were not stand out. My rib eye was the thinnest I have ever seen. Though claiming to age in house, flavour was likewise not stand out, and either the steak itself or the accompanying flavoured butters were very, very salty. Had the steaks been priced closer to their competitor's, value for the experience would have been acceptable, but at app. $40 and up per steak Wildfire is simply "in the wrong weight class". A great night with friends, but not a repeat destination.

Beautifully decorated with an amazing atmosphere. The staff were one of the most attentive servers I have ever experienced.
Received a voucher as a gift that turned out to be expired but the manager, Jan, honoured it anyway. The steak was exceptional and cooked to perfection. This place is a must if you're looking for a restaurant with great food and amazing staff.

Had a large party here and was really impressed with the service. They had a bunch of servers come all at once with our food which isn't something I have experienced much of at restaurants. It was nice that everyone had their food at the same time and it was hot and all orders were correct. Staff was very friendly and the food was great. I think adding some more cocktails to their menu would have made this a better dining experience.

What a spectacular meal! We chose from the fixed price menu and everything was delicious. The Caesar salad has a unique taste that wows. The steak and gnocchi were out of this world. The copa cocktail I chose had both strawberries and cracked pepper. Unique! Dessert- we chose the ones that are made in house- carrot cake and creme br√ªl√©e. An excellent meal all round!

The carrot cake pancakes are golden! We were seated on roofed patio and it was very hot with the terrace heaters focussed right on our heads, that was the only downside.
Very tasty food.  Service staff quite friendly.   Food preparation a little slow.  Overall would go again!
Everything I tried was delicious (the muscles, crab cakes, calamari, and swordfish). Service was quick and atentive. Very pretty decor, and soothing ambience.
